(46, 'EPIC 2020 (CIVIL)', '2020-10-26', '2020-10-27', 'AICTE sponsored National e-conference on \"Emerging Practices and Innovations in Civil Engineering\" (EPIC 2020) <br><br>\n\n\nDept of Civil Engineering, SRKR Engineering College is organising a national e-conference on Emerging Practices and Innovations in civil Engineering‚Äù, which will be held during 26th and 27th, October, 2020.\n<br><br>\nAiming to promote an exchange of scientific knowledge and experience in the field of civil engineering, the scientific program of EPIC-2020 will include plenary/keynote lectures and session talks as well as paper presentations under several major themes, mainly focused on: Structural Engineering, Geotechnical Engineering, Ground Improvement Techniques, Pavement Geotechnics, Environmental Engineering, Geo-environmental Engineering, Green Materials and Technology, Computational methods in Civil Engineering, Water Resources and Hydraulics, Earthquake Engineering, and Case studies of Structural Failures. We certainly believe that EPIC-2020 will provide a variety of opportunities to exchange ideas and expertise as well as network with worldwide research groups.<br><br><br>\n\nCoordinator: Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju,Professor and Principal, SRKREC\n<br>\nCo-Coordinators: Mr. T. Vamsi Nagaraju, Assistant Professor, Civil\n<br><br>\nContact: Mr. T. Vamsi Nagaraju, \nAssistant Professor of Civil Engg.<br>\nvarshith.varma@gmail.com<br>\nepicconf@gmail.com', 'event_details.php?id=46', NULL, NULL, 'CV', '2020-09-03 13:30:00'),
(47, 'TM 2020 (CIVIL)', '2020-10-02', '2020-10-02', 'Terzaghi Memorial one-day online seminar on \"Recent Advancements in Ground Modification\" (TM 2020)<br><br>\r\n \r\n\r\nIndian Geotechnical Society Student Chapter, SRKR Engineering College is organizing a one-day Terzaghi memorial online seminar on \"Recent Advancements in Ground Modification\" (TM 2020) in association with the Indian Geotechnical Society Kakinada Local Chapter, 2nd October 2020.<br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Faculty Advisor:</b><br>  \r\n\r\nMr. T. Vamsi Nagaraju,<br>\r\n\r\nAssistant Professor, Civil Dept, SRKREC<br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Student Organizers:</b><br>\r\n\r\nV.C.S. Nihanth Varma,\r\n17B91A01H0, IV B.Tech, Mobile: 9100797779<br> \r\n\r\nP. S. Sai Goutham, 17B91B0145, IV B.Tech, Mobile: 9603871036<br>\r\n\r\n     \r\n\r\nN. D. S. Thapas, 17B91A01B6, IV B.Tech, Mobile: 9490648206<br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nG. Yaswanth, 17B91B0120, IV B.Tech, Mobile: 7569221199\r\n\r\n', 'event_details.php?id=47', NULL, NULL, 'CV', '2020-09-21 13:30:00'),
(48, 'SEG 2020 (CIVIL)', '2020-10-05', '2020-10-09', 'Online Five-day Faculty Development Programme on \"Sustainable Environmental Geotechnics\" (SEG 2020)<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nDept of Civil Engineering, SRKR Engineering College is organizing a Online Five-day Faculty Development Programme on \"Sustainable Environmental Geotechnics\" (SEG 2020), which will be held during 5th and 9th, October, 2020.<br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe FDP focuses on geoenvironmental aspects of landfill design and maintenance as well as recent research advances related to application of geosynthetics and modeling using soft computing techniques. The various themes for the FDP includes:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Potential of geosynthetics in environmental infrastructure works</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Impact of climate change on the performance of hydraulic barriers</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Geoenvironmental aspects of municipal solid waste landfills</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Environmnetal forensic application in land and ground water pollution</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Response of landfill liner to chemical solution and its modeling using Artificial Neural Networks</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Decontamination of soil using Electro Kinetic Treatment (EKT)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Keynote Speakers:</b><br>\r\n\r\nDr.-Ing. B.V.S. Viswanadham,<br>\r\nDean (Infrastructure) & PROFESSOR, IIT Bombay<br><br>\r\nDr. Sunil B. M<br>\r\nAssociate Professor, NITK Surathkal\r\n<br><br>\r\nDr. B. Janaki Ramaiah<br>\r\nAssistant Professor, IIT Tirupati\r\n<br><br>\r\nDr. Seetha N<br>\r\nAssistant Professor, IIT Hyderabad\r\n<br><br>\r\nDr. Rabi Narayan Behera<br>\r\nAssistant Professor, NIT Rourkela\r\n<br><br>\r\nDr. George K. Varghese<br>\r\nAssistant Professor, NIT Calicut\r\n<br><br>\r\nDr. Vikas Gingine<br>\r\nAssociate Professor, KLS Gogte Institute of Technology, Belagavi<br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\nConvener: Dr. A. Subramanyam Raju, Professor and HOD Civil<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nCoordinators: Mr. T. Vamsi Nagaraju, Assistant Professor of Civil<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nContact: Mr. T. Vamsi Nagaraju\r\nAssistant Professor of Civil Engg.<br>\r\nvarshith.varma@gmail.com<br>\r\ntvnraju@srkrec.edu.in<br>', 'event_details.php?id=48', NULL, NULL, 'CV', '2020-09-25 13:30:00'),
(49, 'ITLMIS-2020 (ECE)', '2020-10-12', '2020-10-17', 'ECE department of SRKREC is organizing an AICTE sponsored a one week national level online STTP on \"Innovative Teaching & Learning Methods for Inspiring Students\" (ITLMIS-oct2020) during 12th October, 2020 to 17th October, 2020.\n<br><br>\n \nBrochure: <a href=\"files/ECE/ITLMIS_2020_Brochure.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download</a><br>\nSchedule: <a href=\"files/ECE/ITLMIS_2020_Schedule.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download</a><br>\n', 'event_details.php?id=49', NULL, NULL, 'EC', '2020-10-02 13:30:00'),
(50, 'CBTGT-2020 (CIV)', '2020-10-26', '2020-10-31', 'Dept. Of Civil Engineering, SRKREC is organizing AICTE sponsored One Week National Level Online STTP on\r\nCapacity Building and Training on\r\nGeospatial Technologies\r\n(CBTGT-OCT2020)<br><br>\r\nPhase-I: Water Resources\r\n26th to 31st October, 2020\r\norganized by\r\nGeospatial Information Centre (GIC), \r\nDepartment of Civil Engineering\r\nS.R.K.R. Engineering College.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>ABOUT THE PROGRAM</b>\r\nThe purpose of online STTP (Short Term Training Program) on Capacity Building and Training on Geospatial Technologies is to create awareness about the value of geospatial technologies among the decision makers and its utility in their organizational workflow <br><br><b>\r\nOBJECTIVES</b><br>\r\nTo build knowledge and adaptation capacity of geospatial technologies at various levels.<br>\r\nCapacity building in teaching, research and development and use of geospatial technologies.<br>\r\nPromote networking of government, academic, research and industrial organizations.<br><br>\r\n\r\nRegistration Link: \r\nhttps://forms.gle/NhfGDqzDkCQDeTpu6<br>\r\nWhatsapp Group Link:\r\nhttps://chat.whatsapp.com/GFlKgp6I8ZH7RasPmXHrjX<br>\r\nBrochure Link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1kw3_mqvyZMMsm9nRF1iljI17vfJiCvAF/view?usp=sharing\r\n<br><br>\r\n', 'event_details.php?id=50', NULL, NULL, 'CV', '2020-10-20 13:30:00'),
(51, 'CBTGT-2020 -II (CIV)', '2020-11-09', '2020-11-13', 'Geospatial Information Centre (GIC), Department of Civil Engineering organizes AICTE sponsored One Week National Level Online STTP on\nCapacity Building and Training on\n\"Geospatial Technologies\" (CBTGT-2020)<br><br>\n\nPhase-II: Land and Water Management Studies - an International Perspective\n9th - 13th November, 2020<br><br>\nOrganized by<br><br>\n\n<b>ABOUT THE PROGRAM</b><br>\nThe purpose of online STTP (Short Term Training Program) on Capacity Building and Training on \"Geospatial Technologies\" is to create awareness about the value of geospatial technologies among the decision makers and its utility in their organizational workflow process.<br><br>\n\n<b>OBJECTIVES</b><br>\n1. To build knowledge and adaptation capacity of geospatial technologies at various levels.<br>\n2. Capacity building in teaching, research and development and use of geospatial technologies.<br>\n3. Promote networking of government, academic, research and industrial organizations.<br><br>\n<b>Registration Link:</b><a href=\'https://forms.gle/RLpJnNVdKoouDHgs5\' target=\'_new\'>https://forms.gle/RLpJnNVdKoouDHgs5</a><br>\nJoin this Whatsapp Group for Event<br>\n<b>Updates:</b><br>\n<a href=\'https://chat.whatsapp.com/JkRJ4xRH3j2BYHBMagclM5\' target=\'_new\'>https://chat.whatsapp.com/JkRJ4xRH3j2BYHBMagclM5</a><br>\n<b>Brochure Link:</b>\n<a href=\'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Xy5pUgKSK3FJ31fBhlRRaR63WoEv8fDV/view?usp=sharing\' target=\'_new\'>Click to Download Brochure</a>\n<br><br>\n<b>CHIEF COORDINATOR:</b> Dr. P. A. RAMA KRISHNA RAJU, Professor, Dean, R&D<br>\n<b>COORDINATOR:</b> Dr. P.RAGHURAM, Assistant Professor', 'event_details.php?id=51', NULL, NULL, 'CV', '2020-11-02 13:30:00'),
