(83, 'ANNUAL DAY 2022', '2022-04-23', '2022-04-23', '<b>SRKREC ANNUAL DAY 2022</b><br><br>\n42nd Annual Day of SRKREC is to be conducted during 23rd of April 2022.<br><br>\n<a href=\'img/events/annualday22poster.jpg\' target=\'new\'>\n<img src=\'img/events/annualday22poster.jpg\' width=\'400px\'></a>', 'event_details.php?id=83', NULL, '', '', '2021-04-19 03:30:00'),
(84, 'TECH-THON 2022', '2022-05-05', '2022-05-05', 'IT Dept of SRKR Engg College is conducting 12 hours hackathon named TECHATHON on 5th May, 2022, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said. IT Dept HOD Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju had said that interested students should send their concepts by 30th of April, 2022. After scrutinizing the ideas, the shortlisted students would only be allowed to participate in this event. Students from any engineering stream can participate in this event. SRKR CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had inaugurated the poster of TECHATHON. ', 'event_details.php?id=84', NULL, 'https://bit.ly/36M6uPz', 'IT', '2022-04-28 03:30:00'),
(85, 'TECHFLEET 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'Departments of IT, CSBS and AIDS in collaboration with Computer Society of India Student Chapter are going to organize Two Day National Level Symposium TECHFLEET 2K22 on May 7th and 8th. IT HOD Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju is the Coordinator of this event and Dr. I. Hemalatha and Dr. K. Kishore Raju would act as Co-Coordinators and S. Jeswanth Sai and K. Bindu Maduri will act as Student Coordinators.', 'event_details.php?id=85', NULL, '', 'IT', '2022-04-28 03:30:00'),
(86, 'SANKETA 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'The Dept of Mechanical Engg is going to organize SANKETA 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th of May, 2022 Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. SANKETA 2K22 Chairman and HOD of Mechanical Engg Dr. Brahma Raju had said that students would undergo various workshops during this symposium like 3D Printing. Secretary  & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had recommended the students to participate in this symposium actively. Dr. P. Ramamurthy Raju will act as Faculty Coordinator and Mr. Krishna, Mr. Purna Aditya will act as student representatives.', 'event_details.php?id=86', NULL, '', 'ME', '2022-05-02 03:30:00'),
(87, 'TRANCE 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'The Dept of ECE is going to conduct TRANCE 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th Of May, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Secretary & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had wished that this event would be successful. Programme Convener and HOD of ECE Dr. Uday Kumar had said that students would undergo training on latest technologies and participate in various competitions as a part of this event. Prof GVS Padma Rao would act as Co-Convener and Ms. Prathima, Mr. Sanjay and Mrs. Bharathi would act as Faculty coordinators.', 'event_details.php?id=87', NULL, '', 'EC', '2022-05-02 03:30:00'),
(88, 'SANKALP 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'EEE Dept of SRKR was going to organize SANKALP 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th and 8th of May, 2022 Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of the same was being inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Program convener and EEE HOD Dr. Varma had said that Students would be given training on various technical issues and various competitions would be conducted on these two days. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had urged the students to make use of this symposium as a way for their bright future. Prof K. Swetha and I. Swetha Mounica will act as faculty coordinators and Mr. A. Harsha, Mr. P. Vamsi, Mr. A. Aditya and Ms. P. Jhansi will act as student coordinators for this symposium.', 'event_details.php?id=88', NULL, '', 'EE', '2022-05-02 03:30:00'),
(89, 'SPURTHI 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'The Dept of CSE at SRKR is going to conduct National Level Student Symposium SPURTHI22 on May 7th, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by Secretary  & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Program convener an HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar had said that students would undergo various workshops and technical competitions as a part of this event. Dr. M. Srihari Varma and K. Aruna Kumari will act as Faculty Coordinators and S. Yasin and G. Supraja will act as student coordinators.', 'event_details.php?id=89', NULL, '', 'CS', '2022-05-04 03:30:00'),
(90, 'SUPERNOVA 2022', '2022-05-07', '2022-05-08', 'SRKR Engineering College is conducting 6 National Level Student Symposiums under various departments on 7th May, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of SUPERNOVA 2022 the National Level Student Symposium by Civil Department has been inaugurated by Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Principal had said that because of the Covid Pandemic the symposiums were not being conducted during the last 2 years which had an adverse effect on the research and analytical skills of the students. Keeping in view the upcoming academic examinations, in order to infuse enthusiasm and passion in the students, these symposiums were being planned. Civil dept HOD Dr. Prasad will act as convener, Mr. M. Venkat Rao will act as Faculty Coordinator, K. Jagadeep, Pavan Kumar, P. Raju, JNS Raju will act as Faculty Co-Coordinators and M. Saiprakash and K. Bhaskar will act as Student representatives for this SUPERNOVA2022.<br>\r\n', 'event_details.php?id=90', '', '', 'CV', '2022-05-04 03:30:00'),
(91, 'WORLD ENVIRONMENT DAY 2022', '2022-06-05', '2022-06-05', '<b>WORLD ENVIRONMENT DAY 2022</b><br><br>\nWorld Environment Day is to be conducted on 05th of JUNE 2022.<br><br>\n<a href=\'img/events/world_environment_day.jpg\' target=\'new\'><br>\n<img src=\'img/events/world_environment_day.jpg\' target=\'new\' width=\'300px\'><br>\n</a>', 'event_details.php?id=91', NULL, '', '', '2021-06-03 03:30:00'),
(92, 'DST ENTREPRENEURSHIP AWARENESS CAMP', '2022-07-15', '2022-07-17', 'Entrepreneurship Awareness Camp</b> Conducted during 15th to 17th July 2022 at Technology Centre', 'event_details.php?id=92', NULL, '', '', '2021-07-07 03:30:00'),
(93, 'GRADUATION DAY 2022', '2022-07-16', '2022-07-17', '<b>SRKR GRADUATION DAY 2022</b> on 16th & 17th July 2022', 'event_details.php?id=93', NULL, '', '', '2021-07-07 03:30:00'),
(94, 'Blood Donation Camp', '2022-10-20', '2022-10-20', 'The NSS Unit at SRKR Engg College had conducted a Blood Donation Camp where the Civil and Mechanical Engineering Students had donated the blood for a noble cause. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should inculcate the habit of donating the blood right from the childhood. Vice President of SRKR, Mr. SV Ranga Raju, College NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Dr. Brahma Raju, Dr. Varma, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, Dr. Prasad, Physical Education Department staff etc. took part in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=94', NULL, '', '', '2022-10-21 06:12:26'),
(95, 'Clean Challenge Drive', '2022-10-19', '2022-10-19', 'The students of SRKR Engg College had conducted an Clean Challenge drive at Pedamiram Village under the college NSS Unit. Speaking on this occasion, Professor of Civil Engg Dr. Ganesh had said that students should voluntarily come forward to serve in the villages. The students took part in an awareness campaign in the village.', 'event_details.php?id=95', NULL, '', '', '2022-10-21 06:17:48'),
(96, 'Orientation Programme On Academic Project and Research Paper Writing', '2022-10-15', '2022-10-16', 'The Dept of CSE is conducting an Orientation Programme On Academic Project and Research Paper Writing for two days. The same has been inaugurated in the campus by Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Speaking on this occasion Principal had said that it is mandatory for the students to have training on academic projects and research paper writing under the new National Educational Policy. The students with this skill set will have more chances for their career upgrade. Faculty of CSE Dept and students took part in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=96', NULL, '', 'CS', '2022-10-21 06:20:45'),
(97, 'Workshop on LED Lights', '2022-10-11', '2022-10-11', 'Women Empowerment Cell in collaboration with ECE Department had conducted a workshop on \'LED Lightening\'. Plastic Omenium Lightening Technical Specialist and Alumni of SRKR Mr. Tejaswi Challa had attended the same as the chief Guest. Speaking on this occasion he said that, Research is under process on the problems that are arising when the temperature of the LED Lights is high. He shared his experiences with the electronics students. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. BHVN Lakshmi presided over this function. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that it is a matter of great pride that the prominent alumni of the college are visiting the campus and sharing their experiences with the students. The management had felicitated Mr. Tejaswi in a grand manner. HOD of ECE, Dr. Uday Kumar, Women Empowerment Cell Co-Coordinators Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. Hemalakshmi, Mrs. Phatima, Mrs. Bharathi took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=97', NULL, '', '', '2022-10-21 06:21:40'),
(98, 'Workshop on Gender Senitisation', '2022-09-16', '2022-09-16', 'Women Empowerment Cell in Collaboration with Civil Department had conducted a workshop on \'Gender Sensitization\'. JNTU Senate Council Member Dr. D. Vijayalakshmi has attended this workshop as a chief guest and she said that there will not be discrimination in youth when they are completely involved in chasing their goals and respect towards the society. Everyone should be mentally strong and march ahead in reaching their goals. JNTU Women Empowerment Cell Director Dr. Swaroopa Rani said that it is very happy to see the women empowerment Cell performing exceptionally well at SRKR. Dr. BHVN Lakshmi had presided over this workshop and Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dr. P. Ramakrishnam Raju, Dr. Prasad and Dr. Bhuvaneshwari took part in this workshop. ', 'event_details.php?id=98', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 08:43:51'),
(99, ' Basketball Competitions', '2022-08-11', '2022-08-12', '\r\nSRKR Engineering College Physical Education Department had conducted Basketball competitions on the occasion of \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\' to various colleges in Bhimavaram. Speaking on this occasion, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that sportspersons should show patriotism towards the country along with the sportive spirit. These competitions were being held for two days in which DNR College had emerged as winner in B Team and as runner in A team. Cash Awards, Mementoes and National Flags were being distributed to the players on this occasion. Physical Education Dept Staff Dr. Harimohan, Ms. Sarika, Mr. Ramaraju took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=99', NULL, '', 'PE', '2022-11-01 09:56:43'),
(100, 'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahostav Rally', '2022-08-13', '2022-08-13', 'SRKR Engineering college had held a massive rally with 5000 staff and students from college to Alluri Seetharamaraju statue on the occasion of \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\'. Speaking on this occasion SRKR Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that around 50 hoardings of prominent freedom fighters will be installed in Bhimavaram town on the occasion of 75 Years of Indian Independence. SRKR College in association with Women Empowerment Cell and NSS had been conducting many programmes from the last 10 days in celebrating this jubilant occasion and it is the duty of everyone to remember the sacrifices of the freedom fighters and army personnel in this august moment. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, NSS In charge Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, NSS Coordinator Sri. Prasad Raju, staff and students took part in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=100', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:00:12'),
(101, 'Independence Day Celebration ', '2022-08-15', '2022-08-15', '\r\nThe Independence Day Celebrations were conducted in a grand manner at SRKR Engineering College. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had hoisted the tricolour with honour and respect. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had explained various key moments of the Independence and requested the staff and students to keep up the spirit of Independence alive. Vice-President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had asked the staff and students to work hard to keep up the pride of the country and institution. The management facilitated the staff and students who had rendered excellent services in their respective fields. Certificates were distributed to the students who excelled in various competitions conducted on the occasion of \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\'.', 'event_details.php?id=101', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:01:53'),
(102, 'National Sports day Celebration', '2022-08-29', '2022-08-29', '\r\nNational Sports Day Celebrations were held in a grand manner at SRKR Engineering College and various sports events such as Volley Ball and Running competitions were held and prizes were distributed to the winners by the Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Speaking on this occasion, he said that sports will increase self-confidence and zeal through which students may further advance in studies. Physical Education Dept Staff Dr. Satyanarayana Raju, Sri. Harimohan, Smt. Sarika, Volleyball Coach Sri. Ramaraju took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=102', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:05:34'),
(103, 'Free Dental Camp', '2022-08-22', '2022-08-22', '\r\nSRKR Engineering College in collaboration with Women Empowerment Cell and Vishnu Dental College had conducted Free Dental Camp at Pedda Amiram Village under the \'Unnat Bharat Abhiyan\' scheme. Speaking on this occasion SRKR Governing Council Member Mr. Pratik Varma had said that SRKR is committed to serve the rural areas with the latest technologies and developments and dedicated to uplift them. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that as per the directions of PM Modi under \'UBA\' scheme, SRKR is dedicating itself to the upliftment of the rural areas. UBA Cell Convener Dr. Ramakrishnam Raju, UBA Cell Coordinator Dr. Ganesh, Women Empowerment Cell Convener Dr. Lakshmi, President and Vice-President Pedda Amiram Panchayat took part in this noble event.', 'event_details.php?id=103', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:07:03'),
(104, 'DST FDP on integrative research in various fields', '2022-09-21', '2022-09-27', '\r\nInaugural Function of FDP on \'INTEGRATIVE RESEARCH IN VARIOUS FIELDS OF ENGINEERING\' had took place on Tuesday. Professor of GITAM University Dr. Srinivas Prasad had attended the same as a chief guest and addressed the participants. He said that Internships and Start-ups would play a key role in the development of technical students. SRKR and GITAM are playing a vital role in the areas of research in the states of AP and Telangana. Collaborative Research and Training programmes are being organised by both the institutes through which students and faculty may have expertise and develop in their careers. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahma Raju, Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy, Dr. P.A. Ramakrishnam Raju, Dr. B. Ravi Kumar Varma took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=104', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:20:51'),
(105, 'Competitions on national education policy', '2022-09-06', '2022-09-06', '\r\nThe NSS Unit at SRKR Engg College had created awareness session on \'National Education Policy\' and conducted various competitions on the same at Jhansi Lakshmi Bai Municipal Girls High School, Bhimavaram and certificates were distributed to the meritorious students. Speaking on this occasion, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should start focussing on skill development right from the early stages of their career. NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya had created awareness to the students on National Education Policy. School Principal P. Srinivasarao took part in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=105', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:27:09'),
(106, 'National flags distribution', '2022-08-10', '2022-08-10', 'SRKR Engineering College under the UBA Scheme had distributed National Flags to the students of Kalla ZP High School. Coordinator Mr. Raghuram had explained to the students about the freedom struggle, national flag and the inspiring story of Mr. Pingali Venkayya. Faculty of SRKR Mr. Ganesh, Dr. Subbarao, Mr. Jeevan Kumar, Head Mistress of ZP High School, Kalla Ms. Tarakeswari were present in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=106', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:37:42'),
(107, 'FDP mobile applications', '2022-08-08', '2022-08-13', 'The Department of CSE at SRKR Engineering College is going to conduct a FDP on \'Mobile Applications\' from 8th to 13th of August, 2022. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR, Dr. Jagapathi Raju had said that faculty should have experience on latest technologies and they should create interest in students to pursue them further. It is because of Android applications that we are getting to know the latest happenings in the world in a few minutes and it is the duty of the faculty to develop further interesting applications and ignite the students. Blackbuck company expert Mr. Narsimha Kanumuri said the faculty and students of SRKR will be benefitted by learning the latest technologies. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, CSE In Charge HOD Dr. Mahesh, Prof. Dr. Kameshwara Rao, Assistant Professor Mr. R. Seetharama Raju took part in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=107', NULL, '', 'CS', '2022-11-01 10:40:27'),
(108, 'USB Programme ', '2022-08-03', '2022-08-03', '\r\nSRKR Engineering College had conducted \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\' at Primary school of Peda Amiram village under UBA Scheme. Speaking on this occasion, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that as we are celebrating 75 years of Indian Independence, everyone should hoist and respect the national flag at their homes and other public places. UBA Coordinator Dr. Ramakrishnam Raju, Faculty Mr. Meher Ganesh, Mr. Subbarao and Head Mistress of School Ms. Padmavathi participated in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=108', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 10:43:41'),
(109, 'Holi', '2022-03-18', '2022-03-18', 'Holi festival has been celebrated in the campus by IT department in the name of Varna. Students have celebrated the festival on 18th March 2022 by hand printing and signing on banners.\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K. Jeeva Sagara garu, Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju garu, IT HOD Dr. Bh.RK Raju and other faculty appreciated the team.', 'event_details.php?id=109', NULL, '', 'IT', '2022-11-01 12:01:35'),
(110, 'VALEDICTORY FUNCTION OF VOLLEY BALL COACHING CAMP', '2022-05-24', '2022-05-24', 'The volleyball coaching camp at SRKR which is being conducted for the last one month has ended on 24th May, 2022. Speaking on this occasion former national volleyball player and trainer Dantuluri Prabhakar Raju had said that students will excel in the field of sports only through continuous commitment and hard work. Former National Volleyball Player Shivaji Raju had said that studies can land in good jobs at state and central level by excelling in the field of sports and students should give importance to sports too along with academics. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the college management is willing to support the students in the area of sports and that is the reason for many SRKR students being placed in University team for many national events. Sports kits were being handed over to students who took part in this camp. Physical Director of SRKR Dr. P. Satyanarayana Raju had presided over this meeting. Assistant Physical Directors Dr. Harimohan and G. Sarika also took part in this meeting.', 'event_details.php?id=110', NULL, '', 'PE', '2022-11-01 12:17:05'),
(111, 'ORGANIZES PROJECT EXPO', '2022-05-23', '2022-05-23', '\r\nThe Dept of EEE had conducted Project Expo on 23rd May, 2022. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should convert these projects into startups and then only it would be beneficial to the society. He said that students should do projects with minimum investment and maximum results. He emphasized that if students come forward with good projects, college is ready to invest in them and mould them into startups. Special attraction of this expo was the project which will not allow the vehicle to go forward if the driver is drunk and the ECG machine that was developed by the students. EEE Dept HOD Dr. Varma and faculty DVR Mohan also took part in this expo.', 'event_details.php?id=111', NULL, '', 'EE', '2022-11-01 12:21:16'),
(112, ' NEET ENTRANCE EXAMINATION CENTRE @ SRKR', '2022-05-21', '2022-05-21', 'Medical PG Entrance examination NEET was conducted in a peaceful manner at SRKR on 21st May, 2022. This was the first time that SRKR was allotted as the examination center for NEET after Bhimavaram was announced as the district headquarters for the new West Godavari District. SRKR Secretary&Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishant Varma said that it was really a matter of pride for the SRKR to be allotted as the test center and he said that SRKR is ready to host as center for any national level examinations. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that all the arrangements were made for the candidates appearing for NEET keeping in view the temperature and climatic conditions. Total of 152 students were allotted and 137 were present and 15 were absent for the examination. Dr. N. Gopalakrishna Murthy acted as the Chief Superintendent for this examination.', 'event_details.php?id=112', NULL, '', 'TC', '2022-11-01 12:24:21'),
(113, ' GUEST LECTURE BY ECE DEPARTMENT', '2022-05-17', '2022-05-17', '\r\nThe Department of ECE had conducted a guest lecture on the theme Digital Technologies for Older Persons and Healthy Ageing on 17-05-2022. The guest lecture was delivered by Sri.T.N.V.Mani Kumar, Sub Divisional Engineer (Enterprise Business), Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited, Tanuku. In Charge Principal and HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahmaraju had outlined the theme to the students. HOD of ECE Dept Dr. Udaykumar had emphasized the relevance of the theme. Smt.Prathima Gamini, Assistant Professor of ECE Department acted as event coordinator. The Resource person Sri. T.N.V.Mani Kumar has taken session on technical aspects, recent trends and Global insights of Telecommunication. Students of Ist Year ECE and Faculty members participated in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=113', NULL, '', 'EC', '2022-11-01 12:27:02'),
(114, ' BLOOD DONATION CAMP FOR THALASSEMIA PATIENTS ORGANIZED', '2022-05-18', '2022-05-18', 'The students of SRKR had donated the blood for the Thalassemia patients at the blood donation camp organized in the college on 18th May, 2022. This camp was organized by the NSS Unit of the college in collaboration with Indian Red Cross Society, Eluru. Speaking on this occasion Incharge Principal and HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahmaraju had said that it was really a matter of great pride and inspiration that the students are participating voluntarily in this noble event. He lauded the services of the NSS and Indian Red Cross Society. He called the students to donate blood at frequent intervals which is good for health and also of great help to others who are in need of it. NSS Coordinator Prasadraju, Programme Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, Head√Ø¬ø¬Ωs of various departments Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju, Dr. P. Bhavani, Dean-Academics Dr. K. Suresh Babu, Assistant Physical Director Dr. Ch. Harimohan, College Engineer Satyanarayana Raju and other staff members participated in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=114', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 12:29:53'),
(115, ' YES+ DAY CELEBRATED ON CAMPUS', '2022-05-14', '2022-05-14', '\r\nThe People Association of Inner Engineering (PAIE) Cell at SRKR had conducted a student empowerment programme √Ø¬ø¬ΩYES+ DAY√Ø¬ø¬Ω on 13th May, 2022. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should mould themselves in a healthy and spiritual path towards which they can be of immense help to others and the society. It is with this prime objective that the PAIE Cell was constituted. Dr. P. Bhavani Incharge of PAIE Cell and HOD of Chemistry Dept presided over this meeting. Speaking on this occasion guests had said that various programmes under PAIE Cell including Sudarshan Kriya have been done to help the students with the divine blessings of Pandit Ravi Shankar Ji. Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had appreciated the students for being a part of this noble initiative. Personality Development Experts Dr. Subbaraju, Seetharama Raju and P. Ramesh Raju had participated in this programme along with a large number of students.', 'event_details.php?id=115', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 12:34:13'),
(116, ' SRKR STUDENTS EXCEL IN PLACEMENTS', '2022-05-15', '2022-05-15', 'The students of SRKR from different branches excelled in the placements conducted by various premium companies and proved their mettle. The details of the same were released by the Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju on 13th May, 2022.\r\n\r\nShaik Jaffar and Mantena Sriram Varma from CSE had received a splendid offer from Amazon with an lucrative package of Rs.44.14 LPA.\r\n5 Students from CSE had been selected to Wal-Mart at an package of Rs. 23.39 LPA.\r\n5 Students from CSE, ECE and Mechanical had been selected to a software firm Gainsight with an offer of Rs. 9.25 LPA.\r\n\r\nPrincipal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had congratulated the students and wished them all the best for their future endeavors. Placement Dean Dr. Satyanarayana had said that many companies had visited the campus this season and many more are yet to visit the campus. HOD\'s of CSE, ECE, Mechanical and English Departments had participated in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=116', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 12:36:16'),
(117, 'FILM ACTOR & SRKREC FACULTY ALUMNI VISITS CAMPUS', '2022-05-12', '2022-05-12', 'Prominent film actor and former Professor of SRKR Sri. Sudarshan Rao had interacted with the staff and students of SRKR Engineering College on 12th May, 2022. He said that it is only through individual development the society will be developed. Teachers should maintan a friendly relationship with the students. It is the teacher√Ø¬ø¬Ωs duty to provoke anxiety and enthusiasm among the students towards the studies. Every human being should introspect everyday whether he is in the development mode or not through which he will be successful. Everyone should have clarity in their thoughts in language through which he can clearly define himself to others. Everyone should pay proper attention to their mental fitness too. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had presided over this meeting. Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had felicitated the guest on behalf of the management.', 'event_details.php?id=117', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 12:39:04'),
(118, 'Prominent film actor and former Professor of SRKR Sri. Sudarshan Rao had interacted with the staff and students of SRKR Engineering College on 12th May, 2022. He said that it is only through individual development the society will be developed. Teachers s', '2022-05-09', '2022-05-09', 'The Mechanical Dept had started a noble initiative of giving free training to the polytechnic students of SMVM Polytechnic, Tanuku on CAD Design for one week. The training session has been inaugurated at the campus yesterday. Speaking on this occasion HOD of Mechanical Dr. Brahmaraju had said that students should upgrade themselves in accordance with the latest technologies and then only they can land in their dream job. India is today marching ahead in Industrial Revolution and is in dire need of skillful employees from ITI, Polytechnic and Engineering streams and the students with latest skills and technologies will only have a bright career. The dept had already created awareness sessions on Mechanical Engineering at the school level by an initiative named as \'Prajna\'. Mechanical Dept staff had participated in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=118', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-01 12:40:35'),
(119, 'STUDENTS EXCEL IN TECHFLEET 2K22', '2022-05-08', '2022-05-08', 'IT Dept at SRKR Engg College had conducted 12 hours uninterrupted hackathon named as TECHFLEET2K22 where engineering students had developed web portals using the latest technologies like Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning. 10 student groups were shortlisted for this programme from various colleges across the state. The student group from SRKR stood first in this competition where they developed an education portal which will be significant help to the students while selecting the educational institutes where they want to pursue their education. Second place was secured by the students of CSE who developed an android application with latest algorithms which will help the vehicles to detect the speed breakers and major disruptions on the road while driving. Consolation prize was won by the students of Vasavi Engg College, Tadepalligudem who developed a boat which will work with the solar energy and in the absence of solar energy this boat also works on diesel. Secretary&Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Rangaraju, Principal of SRKR Sri. M. Jagapathi Raju and HOD of IT Dept Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju had congratulated the students for being a part of this novel programme and urged the students to make use of AI and Machine Learning through which new applications and apps can be developed for the welfare of the society and this would act as a foundation of revolution of communication. Dr. I. Hemalatha, Dr. K. Kishore Raju, BVDS Sekhar, PRSSV Raju had also participated in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=119', NULL, '', 'IT', '2022-11-01 12:48:04'),
(120, 'Workshop on Strategic Planning for Water Resources and Implementation of Noble Bio Technical Treatment and Good Practice', '2022-11-23', '2022-11-23', 'The WET Centre at SRKR Engineering College is set to host a Workshop on the above topic on 23rd Nov, 2022 with the scientists from European Union and IIT\'s. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Principal Investigator Dr. PA Ramakrishnam Raju had said that SPRING Project was being used in SRKR in collaboration with prominent IITs in India and countries like Norway, Finland, Portugal and Hungary. They have disclosed the list of prominent scientists and professors attending the workshop.', 'event_details.php?id=120', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-22 08:54:45'),
(121, 'Awareness Session on Millets', '2022-11-21', '2022-11-21', 'An awareness session was organized on \'Millets Nutrition & Health\' at SRKR Engg College on 20th Nov, 2022. Speaking on this occasion International Food Expert Dr. Khader Vali had said that Millets farming is going to increase in the coming days. He said that Millets will gain prominence in the coming days due to its nutrition value and health benefits. He was grandly felicitated by the college management. Mr. Millet Rambabu, Organic Farming Heart Trust Founder MS. Subramanyam Raju, Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dr. BHVN Lakshmi took part in this occasion.', 'event_details.php?id=121', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-22 08:55:51'),
(122, 'Yuvajanotsav 2022', '2022-11-18', '2022-11-18', 'District Level \'Yuvajanotsav\' by AP Govt was being held in a gradient manner at SRKR Engg College. Chief Guest of this occasion RDO Sri. Dasi Raju had said that these events play a major role in bringing out the hidden talents of the students. These events act as a stress buster for the students who are busy in their academics. Through these events students can come to know about various cultures and traditions of the country. CEO of Youth Services Mr. Mohan raj had said that the winners in these events will attend the selections at Guntur and the winners there will participate in the National Youth Day Celebrations on January 12th, 2023. Tahsildar Mr. Ravikumar, SRKR Vice President Mr. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. Jagapathi Raju, Vice-Principal Dr. K. Brahma Raju graced this event.\r\n', 'event_details.php?id=122', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-22 08:57:25'),
(123, 'Karthika Deeparadhana', '2022-11-14', '2022-11-14', 'On the eve of \'Karthika Somavaram\' the management, staff and students of SRKR Engg College had conducted \'Karthika Deeparadhana\' in the college premises in a devotional manner. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College, Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Vice-President Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju along with staff and students had participated in this event in large numbers. Speaking on this occasion Sri. Nishanth Varma had said that it is the tradition at SRKR to celebrate this event from the last 16 years. He wished the staff and students that their lives should be bright and success should fulfill their lives.', 'event_details.php?id=123', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-22 08:58:26'),
(124, 'Women Development Post Independence Exhibition', '2022-11-22', '2022-11-22', 'The NSS Unit at SRKR Engineering College on the occasion of Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav had held an exhibition on the above topic in which students from all the branches have participated enthusiastically. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Women have shown their impact in all the sectors post-independence and stood as a role model for others. He quoted the examples of former PM Indira Gandhi, present Finance Minister Smt. Nirmala Seetha Raman, Sania Mirza, Mithali Raj and many industrialists in the pharmacy sector as well. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju had praised the women community for their growth in the male dominated society. In charge CSE HOD Dr. Mahesh. Dr. Sirisha, NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya and other faculty members participated in this exhibition. ', 'event_details.php?id=124', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-24 05:47:35'),
(125, 'Workshop on Women Harassment - Preventive Measures', '2022-11-25', '2022-11-25', 'The Women Empowerment Cell at SRKR Engg College had conducted a Workshop on Women\r\nHarassment-Preventive Measures. Speaking on this occasion Senior Advocate Mrs. N. Satyavignana\r\nDevi had said that strict laws and punishments should be awarded to the people involved in women\r\nharassment. Inspite of having many stringent laws the attacks on women are still on a raise. She said\r\nthat it√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s the duty of the parents to raise their children with utmost discipline and then only we can\r\nput an end to these incidents. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should\r\nnot divert their interest towards unwanted incidents and should focus only on their high goals and\r\ndreams. The guest was being felicitated by the management very grandly. Vice President of SRKR Sri.\r\nSV Ranga Raju, Women Empowerment Cell In-Charge Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. Lakshmi, Dr. Aparna,\r\nMrs. Sasikala took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=125', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-26 08:18:56'),
(126, 'Constitution Day', '2022-11-26', '2022-11-26', 'The Constitution Day Celebrations were held in a grand manner at SRKR Engineering College. Speaking on this occasion, Political Science Retired Lecturer Mr. SNV Satyanarayana had said that Indian Constitution is the role model for the whole world, however it should be revised at regular intervals in order to derive maximum benefits. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Indian Constitution is a holy book for the whole Indians. HOD of Mathematics&Humanities Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju, Civil In-Charge HOD Dr. Lavkumar, NSS Coordinators Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, KNV Satyanarayana took part in this occasion. ', 'event_details.php?id=126', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-28 14:31:53'),
(127, 'Workshop on Prevention of Violence Aganist Women ', '2022-11-28', '2022-11-28', 'The Women Empowerment Cell at SRKR Engg College had organized a Workshop on the above topic. Speaking on this occasion Telugu Language Moment President G. Sridevi had said that the violence against women is due to non-following of our traditions and culture by the present generation people. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. BHVN Lakshmi, Dr. Hyma Lakshmi, Dr. Aparna took part in this event. ', 'event_details.php?id=127', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-30 13:47:09'),
(128, 'Student Project  Expo  Anusandhan', '2022-11-29', '2022-11-29', 'The Dept of Chemistry at SRKR Engg College had organised a student expo on integrating science and Technology named as \'ANUSANDHAN\'. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students can hone their creative skills by such exhibitions. He said that it is really good to know that students have displayed models on AI within 2 to 3 days by developing on their own. HOD of Chemistry Dr. P. Bhavani had said that students have displayed over 100 models. Best models were recognised and honoured with certificates. HOD of Physics, Dr. Ramana Murthy, Dr. Diwakar, Mr. Chandrasekhar, Mr. Kishore, Mr. Nagababu took part in this event. ', 'event_details.php?id=128', NULL, '', '', '2022-11-30 13:51:26'),
(129, 'Awareness Session On Traffic Rules', '2022-12-05', '2022-12-05', 'Traffic Police of Bhimavaram Town had conducted an awareness session to the students of SRKR\r\nEngg College on Traffic Rules. Speaking on this occasion, Chief Guest and DSP of Bhimavaram\r\nDivision Mr. Srinadh had said that the bike riders should compulsorily have driving licences. The\r\ntraffic Dept had been organising such sessions at various colleges to create awareness and provide\r\nLLR to the students who doesn√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t have driving licences until now. The bike riders should remember\r\ntheir family when they are driving the vehicles and should act responsibly. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M.\r\nJagapathi Raju had said that students should not drive vehicles without proper licences and\r\napplauded the efforts of the traffic department. Traffic CI Mr. G. Das, faculty Dr. Krishna Chaitanya,\r\nMr. Satyanarayana took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=129', NULL, '', '', '2022-12-06 12:55:18'),
(130, 'Save Soil Celebrations', '2022-12-05', '2022-12-05', 'SRKR Engineering College in collaboration with Bhimavaram Hospitals and Eesha Foundation had conducted an awareness rally on \'Save Soil\'. Speaking on this occasion MD of Bhimavaram Hospitals and Prominent Doctor Dr. Gopala Raju had said that because of the increasing pollution the nutrients in earth are degrading day by day. Everyone should collectively take up the responsibility of the protecting the earth. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the college is making every Saturday as green day and vehicles are prohibited inside the campus. Measures are being taken to eliminate the usage of plastic too inside the campus. Doctor Vijaya, and senior faculty took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=130', NULL, '', '', '2022-12-06 13:07:37'),
(131, 'Induction  Session To Students Of I B. Tech On Joy Of Engineering ', '2022-12-08', '2022-12-08', '\r\nAn induction session to students of I B. Tech was being conducted at SRKR College titled \'Joy of Engineering\' by prominent personality development trainer and Director Academic Planning at JNTUK, Dr. Murali Krishna. Speaking on this occasion he said that students should implement what they learn with good values and then they can shine in their lives. He said that students should not face any tensions and should carry on their studies with fresh and calm mind. He appreciated the students who had participated with great enthusiasm in the programme. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had presided over this session. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of Mathematics & Humanities, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, HOD of Chemistry Dr. Bhavani and other faculty took part in this session. \r\n', 'event_details.php?id=131', NULL, '', '', '2022-12-09 04:33:08'),
(132, 'Felicitation To The President Of SRKR', '2022-12-17', '2022-12-17', 'The Non-Teaching Staff Union at SRKR had felicitated the President of SRKR Sri. S. Prasada Raju in the campus. Speaking on this occasion, he said that SRKR gained fame in the International arena due to the support and cooperation of the teaching and non-teaching staff. He said that even in times of pandemic, students of SRKR succeeded in getting good placements and had won many accolades in the national level. Governing Body Members, Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and the Non-Teaching Staff union representatives took part in this occasion. \r\n', 'event_details.php?id=132', NULL, '', '', '2022-12-19 13:03:10'),
(133, 'SRKR GETS NAAC A+', '2022-12-26', '2022-12-26', 'SRKR Engineering College is accredited by NAAC with A+ Grade, Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had told the reporters at a meeting organised in the college on 26th Dec, 2022. The management celebrated this commendable achievement by cutting the cake and thanking all the stakeholders. SRKR had been awarded 3.42 CGPA and stood among the top colleges in the state of Andhra Pradesh. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that NAAC Committee members had visited the college on Dec 15th and 16th and examined the facilities and infrastructure of the college. HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s and Deans took part in this success celebrations.', 'event_details.php?id=133', NULL, '', '', '2022-12-27 12:33:18'),
(134, 'Savitribhai  Phule  Services Remebered', '2023-01-03', '2023-01-03', 'The services of Savitribhai Phule and National Women Faculty Day was celebrated in a grand manner\r\nat SRKR Engg College by the Women Empowerment Cell. Andhra University Computer Science Dept\r\nSenior Professor Dr. Valli Kumari attended the session as chief guest and addressed the faculty. She\r\nsaid that Phule had rendered the services when there are no infrastructure and this generation\r\nfaculty should treat her as a role model. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had appreciated the\r\nwomen empowerment cell for conducting this session and had remembered the services rendered\r\nby Phule. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Women Empowerment Cell Coordinators and\r\nother faculty took part in this session.', 'event_details.php?id=134', NULL, '', '', '2023-01-04 12:48:38'),
(135, 'National Level Hackathon And Bootcamp', '2023-02-06', '2023-02-12', 'IT Dept of SRKR Engg College is conducting National Level Boot Camp and 24 Hours Hackathon starting from Feb 6 th , Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus by Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Programme Coordinator and HOD of IT Dept Dr. BHVS Ramakrishnam Raju had said that this programme is organized in technical collaboration with Brain O Vision of Hyderabad. Dr. Hemalatha, Dr. Kishore Raju, B. Teja Sri, Saibaba, Satya Varma took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=135', NULL, '', 'IT', '2023-01-09 08:40:49'),
(136, 'Awareness Programme on Road Safety', '2023-01-24', '2023-01-24', '34 th Road Safety Week Valedictory programme was held at SRKR auditorium on 24 th January, 2023.\r\nDistrict Collector Smt. P. Prasanthi attended the same as the chief guest. Speaking on this occasion\r\nshe said that everyone should abide by the traffic rules and have a safe journey. ASP Sri. Subbaraju\r\nand District Transport Officer Sri. Umamaheswara Rao had said that many programmes were being\r\norganised in order to bring awareness on road safety. Eye tests were being conducted for the drivers\r\nand spectacles were being distributed to them by the collector. SRKR Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Governing Body Member Sri. Pratik Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju took  part in this programme.', 'event_details.php?id=136', NULL, '', '', '2023-01-25 07:31:32'),
(137, 'PRAJWALAN  2K23', '2023-03-23', '2023-04-24', '\"Calling all trailblazers! Join us for a one-of-a-kind innovation marathon Prajwalan, where ideas meet action and problems meet solutions.  Come and unleash your creativity, network with like-minded individuals, and make a difference ! Whether you\'re an experienced coder or a beginner with a passion for problem-solving, our hackathon will challenge you to push your boundaries, think outside the box & develop unique solutions to real-world problems.\" \r\n\r\nA team of 3-6 members are allowed.\r\nRound 1: Idea Submission- Closes by March 5\r\nRound 2 : Idea presentation - March 11 & March 12\r\nRound 3 : Grand Finale- 24hr Hackathon - March 23 to March 24\r\n\r\nRegistration fee for Idea submission: 100/- per team\r\nIf you are shortlisted, Registration fee for Grand Finale : 700/- per candidate\r\n\r\n√∞≈∏¬è‚Ä¶ Prize money : 30,000/- pool\r\n\r\nScan the QR code in the poster to get registered or click this : https://unstop.com/o/uji4pEa?lb=6yge2wf', 'event_details.php?id=137', NULL, ' https://sites.google.com/view/prajwalan2023/home', 'CS', '2023-02-24 15:47:17'),
(138, 'Workshop On \'Development Of Application\'', '2023-03-18', '2023-03-20', 'The Dept of CSE is going to conduct a workshop on √¢‚Ç¨ÀúDevelopment of Applications√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ for 3 days starting\r\nfrom 18 th of March, 2023 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same\r\nwas inaugurated by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Overview of new\r\ntechnologies and development of applications will take place in this workshop. A 24 hackathon will\r\nalso be conducted on 23 rd march and students from various Engg colleges across the country had\r\nregistered for the same. HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar, Dr. Mahesh, Dr. Sirisha took part in this\r\nevent.', 'event_details.php?id=138', NULL, '', 'CS', '2023-03-03 10:11:15'),
(139, 'NIPUNA 23', '2023-03-17', '2023-03-18', 'The ISTE Student Chapter at SRKR is conducting National Level Student Symposium NIPUNA-23 on\r\nthis month 17th and 18th , Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of the same was\r\ninaugurated by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Speaking on this occasion\r\nNipuna Faculty Coordinator Dr. Subbarao had said that 17 events are being conducted in this\r\nprogramme. The student Chapter of ISTE at SRKR had stood as No.1 in AP at all India level for 2\r\ntimes. Student representatives of ISTE took part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=139', NULL, '', '', '2023-03-06 05:21:20'),
(140, 'SPURTHI-23', '2023-03-25', '2023-03-25', 'The Dept of CSE is going to conduct a National Level Symposium named as SPURTHI-23 on 25 th of\r\nMarch 2023, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was\r\ninaugurated in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. HOD of CSE Dr.\r\nChandrasekhar had said that students across the country are going to participate in this event. A\r\nworkshop on Applications Development and 24hours hackathon is also going to be part of this event.\r\nGoverning Body Member Mr. Satya Pratik Varma, Faculty Mrs. Priyadarshini, Mr. Bharat Siva Varma\r\ntook part in this event.', 'event_details.php?id=140', NULL, '', 'CS', '2023-03-15 12:11:13'),
(141, 'FREEDOM FEST', '2023-04-19', '2023-04-20', 'The Dept of CSE and Technology Centre are conducting FREEDOM FEST under the aegis of SEWCHA FOUNDATION on 19 th and 20 th of this month, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus. CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar and CSD HOD Dr. Suresh Babu had said that students participating in this fest will have the chance to participate in 4 workshops on emerging technologies like AI, Web Programming, Electronics etc.', 'event_details.php?id=141', NULL, '', '', '2023-04-17 06:19:06');
