(35, '2018-11-04', NULL, NULL, 'Two teams from SRKR Engineering College, Bhimavaram won the first and third prizes in the college connect Startup Challenge competitions at the recently concluded Fintech festival at Visakhapatnam, according to college principal Dr G Partha Sarathi Varma.\n         In a statement on Saturday,he said the two teams received cash awards of Rs 75,000 and Rs 25,000 respectively from Cheif Minister N Chandra Babu Naidu.', NULL, 'CL', '2018-11-08 09:41:14'),
(36, '2018-11-13', NULL, NULL, 'Two projects of the Mechanical Engineering department of SRKR Engineering College here secured two gold medals in the national-level design competitions organised by the Institution of Engineers India (IEI) under the aegis of National Design Research Forum, according to principal Dr G Partha Sarathy Varma.\r\n    The project guide Dr V Durgaprasad said on Monday that Solar-powered walking bike, designed by the final year mechanical engineering students, bagged the gold medal in the environment section. Students team comprising Tumu Kedareswara Aditya, Yadla Ramesh, Yenumala Sivasurya, Palavalasa Srikrishnaveni received the gold medal in the national council.\r\n    In the Mechanical engineering division, Solar-powered multipurpose cultivation system, designed by the team of students comprising Kottada Tarun Kumar, MS Nikhil, KL Prasanna Kumar, I Chaitanya Varma, VLS VIkas and J Ritesh Varma under the guidance mechanical engineer department head Dr Kalidindi Brahma Raju secured the gold medal.\r\n   The college correspondent and secretary, Sagi Vithal Ranga Raju and CEO Sagi Ramakrishna Nishant Varma congratulated the students and the faculty for their achievement. \r\n', NULL, 'ME', '2018-11-13 06:03:46'),
(37, '2018-09-10', NULL, NULL, 'The IT Advisor to the Cheif Minister of Andhra Pradesh,Dr J A Chowdary addressed the audience at College Connect Programme organised at SRKR Engineering College,Bhimavaram recently.\r\n\r\nHe insisted that engineering students,after completion of their degree,can help build the soceity as an entrepreneur or product developer.The experts interact with students and select a few of them after which the concerned company will provide a mentor to the college.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe college principal Dr G Parhasaradhi Varma presided over the programme.Eminent experts from the corporate industry like P Raghavendra,P Srinivas,Dr Ramkumar R,Anirudda S Das,Zakkir Hussen and the college technology centre head Dr N Gopalakrishna Murthy also participated in the programme.', NULL, 'CL', '2018-11-13 10:55:20'),
(38, '2018-11-06', NULL, NULL, 'Four students of SRKR Engineering College were selected for University Fellowship Programme at Stanford University (USA), said the college principal Dr G Parthasaradhi Varma  here on Monday. He said that A Sai Chandana,studying in the third year ECE,Bhupathiraju Surya Subbaraju of second year Mechanical,N Roshini of Third year IT and N Lavanya of third year IT were selected for the fellowship programme.\r\n\r\nHe said that 358 students would participate in the fellowship programme from 16 various countries from across the world. He said that Google and Microsoft would support the fellowship programme.\r\n', NULL, 'TC', '2018-11-13 11:11:00'),
(39, '2018-11-17', NULL, NULL, 'The AICTE,ECI and ISTE will be jointly organising Chhatra Vishwakarma Awards-2018 at SRKR Engineering College,Bhimavaram on November 19.College Principal Dr G Pardhasaradhi Varma Said. On Friday,He released the poster for the event which he said,would encourage young bright students to become more innovtive. Programme coordinator Dr N Gopak Krishnamurthy said arround 816 projects would be displayed at the event.', NULL, 'CL', '2018-11-22 05:40:46'),
(40, '2018-11-20', NULL, NULL, 'All India Council For Technical Education (AICTE), Research and Faculty Development Counselor, Professor Dileep Malakhade said that the Engineering Students should come up with ideas and product Designs of Rural development, and Agriculture related areas. For these the AICTE is going to help them financially. On Monday at SRKR Engg College Bhimavaram, at AICTE, ECI & ISTE Chhatra Vishwakarma Awards - 2018 , he addressed this to the students in the meeting before the project Expo. And he also told that, the winners of Chhatra Vishwakarma awards will be taken to the International Expo and would fund about 10 Lakhs for each project financially. He told that students should think Innovatively and develop the projects useful for the society and bring them to the International Expo and claim the 1st places. As a part he told that all the world is using Technology for spraying of pesticides in the fields, but in India there is no such technology and 1300 workers had died during pesticide sprinkling, which is a bad situation.\n        He addressed students that, in the Godavari District for the Economy growth, the project in areas like Agriculture and Aqua fields are useful. AICTE regional director Dr.Ramesh Unnikrishnan told that, as the whole India Consists of 70% of the villages he addressed students that, it is encourageable to the students to design their innovative products in the areas of Agriculture. He told that about 60 projects from Twin Telugu states have appeared in the Expo and the best in these projects are selected and would be sent for state level  competition. \n         The principal of Srkr Engiuneering College, Dr.G. Pardhasaradhi Varma, addressed students that, the problems related to Rural areas should be studied and some best solutions would be brought by the students. In this program College Secretary and Correspondent Sagi vital RangaRaju, state Information Technology Academy  Program manager Gangadhar, P.Vasanth, College Technology Centre head Dr.N Gopala Krishnamurthy, and Vice- Principal Dr.K.V.S.N Raju had participated.', NULL, '', '2018-11-22 05:54:53'),
(41, '2019-07-18', NULL, NULL, 'In the field of Medical Image Processing,there is a need for more research for better treatment and speedy identification of the patients illness,said the eminent experts from various prestigious institutions like NIT and other research centres at the conducting season of the two week Faculty Development Programme held at SRKR Engineering College,Bhimavaram.', NULL, 'IT', '2019-10-30 06:20:08'),
(42, '2019-10-27', NULL, NULL, '<b>Seminar on Emerging Challenges in Grid Integrated Renewable Energy systems Conducted</b><br>An Assistant Professor from the IIT School of Electrical Engineering in Bhubaneswar, Dr.P.Chandrasekhar, stated that solar and wind energy will play a vital role in future in generating power  and its supply on overcoming any technical hurdles.Participating as a chief guest at a faculty training programme on Emerging challenges in grid integrated renewable energy systems at the SRKR Engineering College of Bhimavaram.\n         The college Secretary and Correspondent Sagi Vithal Raju and Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju said that Faculty Development Programmes were being held with high qualities in all engineering departments in the college and update advance technology among the teachers and the students.The teachers who participating in the programme were given participation certificates by Dr Chandrasekhar and Sri S V Rangaraju', NULL, 'EE', '2019-10-30 07:02:47'),
(43, '2019-10-17', NULL, NULL, '<b>UAV Varma Selected for National Cricket Tournament</b><br>A Final year CSE Student of SRKR Engineering College Bhimavaram, UAV Varma was selected for the Under-23 national cricket tournament to be held at Jiyapur from October 28, said college principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju on Wednesday.He added that the Andhra Pradesh Cricket Association(ACS) selected Varma in the State teams as an all-rounder.The principal spoke on his brilliant record, as last year under his captaincy,AP cricket team won the south Zone inter-university competition,with him bagging the man of the match award.The college secretary and correspondent S V Rangaraju congratulated him and wished him bright future in cricket.Physical director Dr Ch Harimohan and CSE department head Dr M Sivarambadriraju congratulated Varma.', NULL, '', '2019-10-30 09:55:24'),
(44, '2019-07-07', NULL, NULL, 'Mechanical Department of SRKR Engineering College is going to organise a one week Faculty Development Programme on Research Methodlogy from  \n8th to 12 July 2019 Broture has been released by In-charge principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju and Secretary Cum Correspondent Sri S V Rangaraju \n,On this occasion Dr K Brahmaraju Head ,Mechanical Engineering Department said that young researchers can utilize this oppurtunity to know new methodologies in doing research.', NULL, 'ME', '2019-10-30 10:08:55'),
(45, '2019-10-12', NULL, 'Mech Student Team Wins 3 Awards', 'In SRKR Engineering College Mechanical students were Designed a vehicle named as Allterain Vehicle(ATV) and got best Design Award in national level.Total 30 members of Mechanical students are formed as a group and designed a car named as Agraganya .This Agraganya was participated in national level Car challenging competitions and they are secured three national awards and also got Dronacharya award to Faculty those who are involved in designing of vehicle. This competition was conducted in biknur village near  by Rajasthan Thar Desert,it is near by Pakistan boarder.This competition was organized by some international Automobile companies from October 2nd to 4th at Biknur village. Dr. K. Brahma Raju,Head of Mechanical Engineering Department,he always gives motivation and ideas to students for doing new innovations. Assistant Professors K.Sitarama Raju,Sudheer Kumar Varma and Rajendra Prasad Varma always supports students and gives the technical ideas and innovation ideas.In this Competition girl Student Prajna secured best lady driver award and she was acted as co-driver, B.Pavan acted as Vehicle Driver,Ganesh Reddy acted as Captain and T.Ramasahith acted as vice captain.\n', NULL, 'ME', '2019-10-30 10:12:28'),
(46, '2019-09-24', NULL, 'SRKR Orator Championship 2019   Organized Successfully', 'SRKR Engineering College organized the grand finale of SOC popularily known among students as SRKR Orator Championship. It is an annual event aimed at identifying and Systematically assesing over 300 students in public speaking.In the grand finale 10 students performed on stage before a huge gathering involving students,Faculties,Principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju and Secretary Cum Correspondent Sri S V Rangaraju.The event ended after 3 students were announced winners and given awrds by the principal and the secretary.At the event  Dr N G K Murthy,Head Technology Centre was present along with the convenor of the event Mr Venkata Durga Kiran V and Cheif Judge of the event Mr M Sankar', NULL, 'TC', '2019-10-30 10:28:59'),
(47, '2019-09-27', NULL, 'Students selected for national level sports', 'Few Students of SRKR Engineering College Bhimavaram, was selected for the south zone inter university volleyball \ntournament from October, another student G Bahnusankar was selected for the Chess Tournment to be held at Andhra University and another student S N V Sai Ganesh was selected for the Chess Tournment to be held at Gandhigram Rural Institute-Deemed university said by the college principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju on Thursday.\nThe college secretary and correspondent S V Rangaraju congratulated him and Physical Director P Satyanarayana Raju and Volleybal coach Ramaraju congratulates.', NULL, '', '2019-10-30 11:35:27'),
(48, '2019-10-19', NULL, 'PhD Awarded by Mech Dept. of SRKREC', 'Mr Vempati Srinivasa Reddy  Assistant Professor in QIS College of Engineering and Technology, Ongole awarded PhD Degree from Mechanical Department of\nSRKR Engineering College,Bhimavaram in October 19 Under the Guidance of Dr K Brahmaraju, Head,Mechanical Department \nand Dr K Venkata Subbaih, Professor Andhra University as a co-guide. S.R.K.R. Engineering College Principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju appreciated Mr.Srinivasa Reddy on this ocassion. Dr.V Srinivasareddy said that his research is focused on defects on welding structural problems on that are used in Aerospace ,Ships and overcome that problem and proposed solution.', NULL, '', '2019-10-31 04:52:50'),
(49, '2019-10-15', NULL, 'Pragna Outreach Programme by Mech Department', 'Pragna Programme started at  ZPH School,Palakoderu under guidance of Dr K Brahmaraju Head,Mechanical Engineering of SRKR Engineering College, Few students of SRKR Engineering College\nexhibited  some projects developed and explained to students , On this ocassion Dr K Brahmaraju said that every student must have knowledge in \nlatest technologies . G.Sudharani Head Master of ZPH School,Palakoderu said that from childhood if students know more about  science and technology projects it will be very helpful to our society.', NULL, '', '2019-10-31 05:15:10'),
(50, '2019-11-01', NULL, 'PhD Awarded by SRKREC Research Centre', '3rd PhD Degree awarded from SRKR Engineering College for V. Bindu Niharika from Mechanical Engineering department under the supervision of Dr. V. Durga Prasad.', NULL, '', '2019-11-01 05:15:10'),
(51, '2019-11-03', NULL, '2 Weeks FDP on Deep Learning and Big Data Analytics Inaugurated', 'To address the changing trends in technology in the engineering colleges, AICTE is taking necessary steps\" says Srinivasa Rao assistant professor in NIT Warangal.\nOn the occasion of the opening of 2 Weeks workshop on Deep Learning and Big Data Analytics he added that the teachers should undergo training to introduce the changes in the technology to the students and help them bridge the gap between the industry and educational institutions, and for this initiative AICTE will be reaching out to the colleges with the financial help they need.\nDr M Jagapathi Raju, Principal added that SRKR engineering college has been organising Faculty development programs over the years particular to each department.Faculty and Educational instructors in and around the AP are drawn towards the training and are receiving it.\nThe ceremony was followed by the felicitation of Mr Srinivasa Rao by the college correspondent Sagi Vittal Rangaraju.\nAmong the other dignitaries who attended the program are IT head N.K.Kameswarao(Convenor of the workshop) and Asst Professor K. Kishore Raju(coordinator of the program).', NULL, 'IT', '2019-11-04 08:41:39'),
(52, '2019-11-03', NULL, '1 Day Training Camp on Human Values Organised', 'It is true that educational institutions guide the society in a moral and ethical way and the reason that is happening is because of the teachers who are a part of such esteemed educational institutions\" says the personality development expert , head of IIIT Earthquake Engineering Research Centre Dr Ramacharla Pradeep Kumar.\nOn Saturday in a training camp organised by SRKR Engineering College he spoke on the topic Role of a teacher in developing societal and humanitarian values and he quoted, For students to achieve completeness ethically and morally the responsibility is bestowed in the hands of the teacher and universities should take necessary steps to include Human Relations and values in the curriculum and design syllabus accordingly.\nAmong the other dignitaries who took part in the program are college Secretary and Correspondent Sagi Vittal Rangaraju and Principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju', NULL, '', '2019-11-04 08:45:06'),
(53, '2019-11-04', NULL, 'Poster Launch of SANKALP 2K19 - EEE Tech Fest', 'Dr M Jagapathi Raju, Principal of Bhimavaram SRKR Engineering College, said that educators and young people go to the villages and motivate the farmers to cultivate organic farming.\nAnnual Sankalp 2K19 National Level Student Symposium held annually in the college\'s EEE department,As part of this, students are moving to their hometowns to motivate each farmer this year to work on the direction of the farmers in their village to explain the organic farming results.\nCollege Secretary and Correspondent S V Rangaraju unveiled the poster in this regard.In this programme Dr P Kanthara Rao,Head of EEE, Program Coordinators K Kiran Kumar, B Motiram and Students are participated.', NULL, 'EE', '2019-11-04 13:13:57'),
(54, '2019-10-15', NULL, 'CISCO Women Rock IT Conducted Successfully', 'Cisco Women Rock IT Seminar held on Thursday under the aegis of Bhimavaram SRKR Engineering College,The conference was chaired by Dr. N Gopala Krishna Murthy,Head of the Technology Center.GDP growth will increase by 18% in the next six years if female social entrepreneurs rise, says Sahiti Divi, Hyderabad Impact Scientist Incorporated.\nHarshita Lalchand, Director of Toastmasters International, Visakhapatnam Division, said that young people who are not in the least able to participate in cellphone use, therefore intelligent young people need to create new technology.\nCollege Secretary and Correspondent S V Rangaraju and Principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju said today\'s women should be ideal for successful entrepreneurs like Sudha Narayana Murthy.', NULL, 'TC', '2019-11-05 04:46:54'),
(55, '2019-10-19', NULL, 'Narasapuram DSP Visits Campus', 'Narasapuram DSP K Nageswararao advised students to support the police to curb the injustices that happen in the society with the social responsibility \nof every student and youth, He addressed the students at Bhimavaram SRKR Engineering College on Saturday.\nBhimavaram Town CI Vijayakumar, SI Ramachandra Rao, V Rambabu, ASI Ajay Kumar and others participated in the event.\nDSP Nageshwara Rao hands over gifts to student\'s student who spoke well on public relations.\n', NULL, '', '2019-11-05 05:25:57'),
(56, '2019-10-08', NULL, 'EEE Student Selected for National Level Rifle Shooting', 'Dr M Jagapathiraju, Principal of SRKR Engineering College,Bhimavaram  said that P Kamalaswamy, their college student,\nhas been selected for the national level rifle shooting competitions.', NULL, '', '2019-11-05 05:32:53'),
(57, '2019-11-14', NULL, 'FDP on Deep Learning & Big Data Concludes\n', 'Faculty training on Deep Learning and Big Data Analytics conducted by IT Department from 2nd to 14th November 2019 at SRKR Engineering College Bhimavaram, Dr. M Jagapathi Raju, Principal congratulated the IT department for conducting 2 FDP programs in just 3 months.\nServiceNow applications manager Sri V Rakeshreddy said that faculty needs to get updated with new technologies from time to time.Sri Sagi Ramakrishna Nishant Varma,CEO SRKR Engineering College presented certificates,  K Kishore Raju,FDP co-ordinator and others were present.', NULL, 'IT', '2019-11-15 09:24:29'),
(58, '2019-11-21', NULL, 'Research Centre Started at SRKR Engineering College by Professor Rajanish Kaur Kale', 'Newly Established Research Centre Started in SRKR Engineering College by Professor Rajanish Kaur Calay from Norway.on this occasion said that,Experiments can be innovative that is useful to the society.In this event Dr M Jagapathi Raju , Principal,S V Ranga Raju,Secretary Cum Correspondent,Dr P Ramakrishnam Raju and others participated.', NULL, '', '2019-11-21 04:34:31'),
(59, '2019-11-26', NULL, '87 Students Gets Certified in Applied Robot Control Course', '87 Students of SRKREC have successfully completed 12 month online course on Applied Robot Control (ARC 1.0) Course conducted by Indo-European Centre for Mechatronics and Industrial Robotics in association with APSSDC. This certification will enable the students to join courses in Germany universities with out any entrance exams. ', NULL, '', '2019-11-26 02:32:00'),
(60, '2019-11-30', NULL, 'Divisional Youth Festival Conducted @ SRKREC', 'Divisional Youth Festival 2019 by Department of Youth Services, Government of Andhra Pradesh has been conducted @ SRKR Engineering College on 29th November 2019. More than 200 students from 8 surrounding colleges have participated in the events. ', NULL, '', '2019-12-01 00:39:54'),
(61, '2019-12-06', NULL, 'CSE & IT National Conference Poster Launched', 'Poster of the upcoming National Conference on Productivity, Quality, Reliability, Optimization and Computational Modeling (NCPQROCM-2019) has been launched yesterday by college management. The departments of CSE & IT is jointly organizing the conference during 18 to 20th December 2019. ', NULL, '', '2019-12-06 00:39:54'),
(62, '2019-12-07', NULL, 'SRKREC bags Leadership Excellence Award 2019', 'SRKREC has been awarded with Higher Education Award-2019 in the Category of Outstanding Contributor to Leadership Development for achieving excellence in providing Skill-based education programmes to foster academic and career success for students by Brainfeed Higher Education Awards. General Body Member Sri Sagi Satya Pratik Varma and Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopi Nukala received the award from Dr.B.Janardhan Reddy IAS , Secretary , Department of Education , Govt., of Telangana  and Dr.N.Raja Sekhar Reddy Secretary & CEO A.P. Higher Education Regulatory and Monitoring Commission, Govt., of A.P. at HITEX, Hyderabad on 7th December 2019.', NULL, '', '2019-12-07 12:00:15'),
(64, '2019-12-18', NULL, 'National Conference NCPQROCM 2019 Inaugurated', 'National Conference on Productivity, Quality, Reliability, Optimization and Computational Modeling (NCPQROCM-2019) has been inaugurated on 18th December 2019. The conference has been organized jointly by departments of CSE & IT and co-ordinated by Dr. R.N.V.Jagan Mohan. Experts from JNTUK and Industry graced the occasion.', NULL, 'CS', '2019-12-19 04:00:15'),
(63, '2019-12-13', NULL, 'SRKREC Students Excel in Sports', 'Students of SRKREC have excelled in inter-college sports events and got selected for tournaments at national and international level.\r\n\r\n<br><br>Y.G. Srinivas, 3/4 CSE student bags Gold medal in JNTUK Inter College Karate competitions.\r\n<br>J. Samhitha of 2/4 ECE selected for National level Judo Competitions to be held in Kanpur.\r\n<br>Sai Krishna of 2/4 EEE is going to represent JNTUK team in the upcoming South Zone Handball competitions in Bengaluru.\r\n<br>Mech Student Sai Tarun bags Silver medal in 4 X 100 mtrs running.\r\n<br>P. Kamalswamy of 2/4 Civil selected for International level Rifle Shooting Competitions for qualifying rounds.\r\n<br> Sandesh got selected for senior level Hockey Tournament. ', NULL, 'SP', '2019-12-13 08:00:15'),
(65, '2019-12-21', NULL, 'Artificial Intelligence (AI) Club Inaugurated', 'Keeping in view the importance of Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning and Deep Learning, a new student & faculty club named AI Club has been inaugurated by Shri. S.V.Rangaraju garu, Secretary and Correspondent of SRKREC on 21st December 2019 during the annual day celebrations of Technology Centre. ', '', 'TC', '2019-12-22 13:35:15'),
(66, '2020-01-04', NULL, 'Meeting Held on Funding Opportunities in R & D', 'Dr.D.R. Prasada Raju Garu , Ph.D, FNAE,R&D Adviser for IIT Madras, Advisory Council Member, SRKR Engineering College addressed the Staff of SRKREC on  \"FUNDING OPPORTUNITIES FOR RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT\" on JANUARY 4th 10:00 am to 11:00 am at E-class room of WET CENTER.  HOD\'s of all the Departments, Deans, R&D Coordinators and Senior Faculty members attended the meeting.', '', 'WC', '2020-01-04 08:35:15'),
(68, '2020-01-25', NULL, 'Facutly Cricket Team Wins Chandu Trophy for 3rd Time', 'SRKREC Faculty Cricket Team wins 25th Chandu Cricket Tournament - AP State Level Cricket Tournament for College Teachers held at Guntur. The team has outperformed all the teams in the tournament and stood as winner by beating Vignan Degree College in Finals, held at JKC Cricket Stadium, Guntur.<br><br>\n\nAround 30 teams from various degree and engineering colleges of AP participated in the tournament this year and incidentally, SRKREC team has scored a hat-trick by winning the trophy for 3 consecutive winners. <br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/27_jan_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'><img src=\'img/news/27_jan_2020_2.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'><br><br>\n\nScores and Matches details can be found at the below website link.', 'https://cricheroes.in/tournament/101632/TWENTY-FIVETH-CHANDU-S-CUP-CRICKET-TOURNMENT-FOR-COLLEGE-TEACHERS#Matches', '', '2020-01-25 07:44:15'),
(67, '2020-01-24', NULL, 'National Girl Child Day Celebrated on Campus', 'National Girl Child Day celebrated by NSS Unit & Women Empowerment Cell in S.R.K.R Engineering College on January 24. The objective of celebrating National Girl Child Day are as follows.\n<br><br>\n* Highlight the inequalities faced by girls in the country<br>\n* Promote awareness about the rights of a girl child<br>\n* Create awareness on importance of girl education,health and nutrition.<br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/24_jan_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'><img src=\'img/news/24_jan_2020_2.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'>', NULL, '', '2020-01-24 10:44:15'),
(69, '2020-01-28', NULL, 'TechFleet2020 - IT Tech Fest Poster Unveiled', 'Poster of IT department\'s upcoming National Tech Fest - TechFleet 2020 has been launched by Secretary & Correspondent Shri. S.V.Rangaraju garu and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu here on 28th Jan 2020. IT HOD Dr. Bh.V. S. Ramakrishnam Raju, Mr. Kishore Raju and Students were present.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<img src=\'img/news/28_jan_2020.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'>', NULL, 'IT', '2020-01-28 06:44:15'),
(71, '2020-01-30', NULL, 'NIPUNA 2020 - ISTE Tech Fest Poster Unveiled', 'Poster of ISTE\'s upcoming National Techo Management Fest - NIPUNA 2020 has been launched by Secretary & Correspondent Shri. S.V.Rangaraju garu and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu here on 29th Jan 2020. NIPUNA Convenor Prof. P. Subba Rao and Students were present.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', NULL, '', '2020-01-30 03:44:15'),
(70, '2020-01-29', NULL, 'SRKREC Signs MOU with 10 Engineering Colleges', 'As part of AICTE\'s Margadarshan Project, SRKREC has signed MOUs with 10 engineering colleges from East and West Godavari in the presence of Management and Principal here on 29th January 2020.<br><br>\r\nAs part of the initiative, SRKREC will impart Faculty Training & Technology Development to surrounding engineering colleges and enable them to get accredation by NBA in near future. Principals from Eluru Engineering College, Rama Chandra Engineering College, BVC Engineering College, DNR Engineering College, BIET, GVVIT, and other colleges have exchanged MOU documents during the occasion. ', NULL, '', '2020-01-29 12:44:15'),
(72, '2020-01-31', NULL, 'PhD in Mechanical Engg. produced by SRKREC', 'The research centre of SRKREC has produced a new PhD from Mechanical Engineering department. The research scholar Dr. K. Balaji, currently working as Associate Professor in Swarnandhra College of Engineering & Technology, has been guided by Dr. K. Brahmaraju, MECH HOD and Prof. K. Venkata Subbaiah, Senior Professor of Andhra University.      ', NULL, 'ME', '2020-01-31 03:26:15'),
(73, '2020-02-03', NULL, 'SRKR Go-Kart Club Wins Innovation Award', 'SRKR Mechanical Engineering Students have excelled in the recent National Level SAE Mahindra E-BAJA Mega Sporting Event (BAJA SAE INDIA -2020) at Indore by bagging FIRST PRIZE in the Innovation Category. A cash award of Rs. 40,000/- has been awarded to the SRKREC Team of 22 students who developed the Electric ATV Fabricated Vehicle.<br><br>\n\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, MECH HOD Dr. K. Brahmaraju garu congratulated the team and the mentors for this success. Faculty Team Mentors Dr. K. Sitaramaraju, N. Sudher Kumar Varma, V.V. Murali Krishnam Raju, U. Rajendra Prasad Varma, and Student team members SVV Sai Krishna (Captain), K. Pavan (Driver), N. Harsha (Driver), A. Bharadvaj (Vice Captain), Sheik Aslam,  S. Raja Narendra, N. Satyanandini, J. Varshita, P.J. Manjusha, P.L. Supriya were present.<br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/4_feb_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'><img src=\'img/news/4_feb_2020_2.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'>   ', NULL, 'ME', '2020-02-04 02:26:15'),
(74, '2020-02-04', NULL, 'CISCO Outstanding Performance Award for SRKREC ', 'SRKREC received Outstanding Performance Award for the year 2019 for getting more number of certifications for Women Rock IT course. Technology Centre staff Mr. KDV Pavan Kumar Varma and Ch Swaroop received the award during the CISCO Academy Conference 2020 at Bengaluru last week.<br><br>\n\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Technology Centre HOD Dr. N.G.K Murthy garu congratulated the team for the award.<br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/3_feb_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\'>', NULL, 'TC', '2020-02-04 04:26:15'),
(75, '2020-02-11', NULL, 'IT Tech Fest TECHFLEET-2K20 Conducted', 'National Level Tech. Fest of IT Department TECHFLEET-2K20 has been conducted during 10th and 11th February 2020. Former Vice-Chancellor of Adikavi Nannaya University Dr.P. Suresh Varma was the chief guest for the Inaugural Function. Incharge Principal Dr. K. Brahmaraju, Praveen Malla from IT Industry and IT HOD Dr. Bh.V. Rama Krishnam Raju were present during the inaugural session. The Smart City Project demonstrated by IT department students during this occasion has been appreciated by guests and faculty.', NULL, 'IT', '2020-02-11 14:26:15'),
(76, '2020-02-12', NULL, 'Awareness Talk on Corona Virus Conducted', 'NSS Unit of SRKREC has organized an awareness talk on Corona Virus and its impact by Dr. D. Sandeep Varma, MD (General Medicine) of Bhimavaram Hospitals on 12th February 2020 at ECE Seminar Hall.', NULL, '', '2020-02-13 07:26:15'),
(77, '2020-02-20', NULL, 'MECH Tech Fest SANKETA-2K20 Organized Successfully', 'The National Level Technical Fest of Mechanical Engineering Department has been organized on 19th and 20th February 2020. Principal of Sri Vasavi Engineering College, Tadepalligudem Dr. G.V.N.S.R Ratnakar garu was the chief guest for the inaugural function.Secretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapati Raju garu,   Mechanical department HOD Dr. K. Brahmaraju garu,Program convenor Dr. K. Sitaramaraju garu and MECH Association Chairman Dr. S. Rajesh were present.   ', NULL, 'ME', '2020-02-20 12:26:15'),
(84, '2020-06-03', NULL, 'NBA Accreditation Granted for All Branches', 'Based on the recommendation of the expert committee that conducted on-site evaluataion of the UG programs at SRKREC during 28th February and 1st March 2020, \r\nthe competent authority in National Board of Accreditation (NBA) has approved the accreditation status of the following UG programs for 3 years (2020 to 2023):<br><br>\r\n\r\n1. Civil Engineering<br>\r\n2. Computer Science & Engineering<br>\r\n3. Electronics & Communication Engineering<br>\r\n4. Information Technology<br>\r\n5. Mechnical Engineering<br>\r\n6. Electrical and Electronics Engineering<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe management congratulated the principal, HODs, Teaching and Non-Teaching Staff for their efforts in getting the accreditation for all branches.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_8.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_jun_2020_8.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n ', NULL, '', '2020-06-03 11:30:15'),
(79, '2020-03-05', NULL, '2 Students Teams Selected for Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2020 Grand Finale', '2 teams of SRKREC have been selected for the Grand Finale of Smart India Hackathon 2020. The teams have been selected for the problem sets given by  the Ministry of Textiles and Tripura Institute of Technology. The final will be held during 4th and 5th April 2020 at NIT Jamshedpur and KL University. The management and Principal congratulated the team and the mentors.', '', 'TC', '2020-03-05 12:26:15'),
(80, '2020-03-08', NULL, 'International Women\'s Day Celebrated @ SRKREC', 'International Women\'s Day has been celebrated by SRKREC Faculty and Students on 7th March 2020 at I-Block. High Court Judge Shri.AV. Sesha Sai and his wife Smt. Durgamba garu were the chief guests of the occasion. Cultural Programs have been conducted in the evening.<br><br>\n\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Vice-President Shri. G. Rama Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Women Empowerment Cell Convenor Smt. Shanti, Dr. P. Bhavani, and other women faculty were present.<br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/7_mar_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\' class=\'responsive\'>', NULL, '', '2020-02-08 04:26:15'),
(81, '2020-03-15', NULL, 'Students Exhibited Hardware & IOT Projects in CRUX 2020', 'CRUX 2020 - The annual hardware contest has been organized by ECE department during 14th and 15th March 2020. Students have exhibited various projects related to IOT and Hardware. The event has been organized under the direction of Professor D.V.R. Mohan garu who has been doing this since 25 years.', NULL, 'EC', '2020-02-17 04:26:15'),
(82, '2020-03-19', NULL, '2/4 & 3/4 B.Tech Mid - II Examinations Postponed', 'In view of Corona Virus Pandemic, the 2nd Mid Examinations of 2/4 B.Tech and 3/4 B.Tech originally scheduled from 22nd March 2020 have been postponed until further notice.<br><br>\n\nDates and Schedules of the postponed examinations will be intimated later.\n ', NULL, '', '2020-02-19 05:26:15'),
(83, '2020-03-19', NULL, '4/4 B.Tech (R16) Regular & Supply Examinations Postponed', 'In view of Corona Virus Pandemic, the IV B.Tech-II Sem (R16) - Regular Examinations & IV B.Tech-I-Sem (R16) Advanced Supply Examinations have been Postponed. The Revised Time Table will be displayed later.<br><br>\n\nCheck <a href=\'http://www.srkrexams.in\' target=\'_new\'>http://www.srkrexams.in</a> for examination updates.', 'http://www.srkrexams.in ', '', '2020-02-19 05:30:15'),
(85, '2020-06-09', NULL, '2 New Courses Sanctioned by AICTE', 'AICTE has sanctioned two new branches in SRKREC from the academic year 2020-21 with an intake of 60 each.<br><br>\n\n1. B.Tech in Artificial Intelligence & Data Science<br>\n2. B.Tech in Computer Science & Business Systems (Powered by TCS)<br>\n<br><br>\nKeeping in view the importance of Artificial Intelligence, Data Science and Industry 4.0 technologies, AICTE has recommended these new advanced branches / courses in reputed engineering colleges throughout the country.<br>\n\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>\n\n', NULL, '', '2020-06-09 11:30:15'),
(86, '2020-06-13', NULL, 'EU-INDIA HORIZON 2020 Project Sanctioned by DBT, India', 'The Horizon 2020 (European Union Framework Programme for Research and Innovation) programme and the Department of Biotechnology, Government of India have jointly approved <b>SPRING</b> (Strategic Planning for Water Resources and Implementation of Novel Biotechnical Treatment Solutions and Good Practices) under the Horizon 2020 Call: H2020-SC5-2018-2019-2020. With the release of funding to Indian partners on 14th May 2020, the project has officially taken off. (There are 8 Indian partners and 6 European partners from Norway, Finland, Hungary and Portugal in the SPRING consortium.)<br><br>\r\nTotal project worth Rs.31 Crores has been sanctioned - India (Rs.6.11 Crores) and SRKREC (Rs.1.4 Crores) ', NULL, 'WC', '2020-06-13 11:30:15'),
(87, '2020-06-22', NULL, 'International Yoga Day Celebrated @ SRKREC', 'International Yoga Day has been celebrated by SRKREC Faculty and Staff on 21st June 2020 at Basketball Court, maintaining social distance.<br><br>\n\nIn this connection, a special online Yoga Workshop has been conducted during 17th and 21st June 2020.<br><br>\n\n<img src=\'img/news/22_jun_2020_2.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\' class=\'responsive\'><img src=\'img/news/22_jun_2020_1.jpg\' style=\'padding-bottom:10px\' class=\'responsive\'>', NULL, '', '2020-06-22 14:26:15'),
(88, '2020-07-19', NULL, 'Founder\'s Birthday Celebrated', '87th Birthday of SRKREC Founder Shri Sagi Rama Krishnam Raju garu has been celebrated here on 19th July 2020 on campus. Secretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, HODs and Staff were present during the occasion.', NULL, '', '2020-07-20 14:26:15'),
(89, '2020-08-05', '', 'SRKREC Wins 1st Prize in Smart India Hackathon 2020', 'SRKREC team has won First Prize in the prestigious National Level 36 Hours AICTE Smart India Hackathon (SIH) 2020 conducted online from August 1st to August 3rd, 2020. The team named TeamHunters comprising of 2nd Year IT and EEE students have successfully developed a web-portal for income assessment of jute farmers and jute mill workers as per the problem statement (AR253) of Jute Board, Ministry of Textiles. The team has won One Lakh Rupees prize money.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Team:</b><br>\r\n\r\n1. Yakkala Bala Naga Venkata Siva Gopal (Team Leader) - 18B91A12H7 - B.Tech 2nd year - IT <br>\r\n2. Jagadeesh Reddy Medapati - 18B91A02C5 - B.Tech 2nd year - EEE<br>\r\n3. Vetsa Harish Kumar - 18B91A12H4 - B.Tech 2nd year - IT<br>\r\n4. Veeragani Uday Sandeep - 18B91A12G1 - B.Tech 2nd year - IT<br>\r\n5. Gogineni Vasantha Sai Lakshmi - 18B91A1230 - B.Tech 2nd year - IT<br>\r\n6. Ghanta Charishma - 18B91A1229 - B.Tech 2nd year - IT<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Mentors:</b><br>\r\n1. Dr. Suresh Babu Mudunuri<br>\r\n2. Mr. A. Krishna Kanth (3/4 IT)<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe team, mentors, and Tech Centre HOD Dr. NGK Murthy have been appreciated by  \r\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, CEO Shri Nishant Varma garu, Management Member Shri Manoj garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, HODs and Staff.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_aug_2020_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2020-08-05 14:26:15'),
(90, '2020-08-17', '', 'SRKREC Selected for Unnat Bharat Abhiyan (UBA) Award ', 'The Ministry of Education (previously called MHRD)\'s flagship programme UBA (Unnat Bharat Abhiyan) has selected about 2160 Higher Educational Institutions including Engineering Colleges to reach out the fruits of technology to the 6 lakh villages of India. SRKREC was amongst the first phase of institutions selected to carryout outreach activities. SRKREC has adopted Kalla, Kallakuru, Jakkaram, Peda Amiram and Gollalakoderu villages where the students of all departments and coordinating faculty have conducted many programmes.<br><br>In recognition of the impact of our work, the UBA Chairman has selected us and 77 other institutions in the country for an award that bestows a perennial fund of Rs.1,75,000 for carrying out UBA activities in the selected villages. This is a a great achievement as only 2 other institutions have been selected in the state.', '', 'WC', '2020-08-17 14:26:15'),
(91, '2020-09-05', '', 'SRKREC Stands 2nd in TIMES Ranking 2020', 'SRKREC secured <b>2nd place</b> in the top 10 colleges in the state  in the ranking survey 2020 conducted by <b>Times Engineering Institute</b>. At national level, the college stood at <b>62nd place</b>, stood 2nd in the research category in the state and 4th in the state in the infrastructure category.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_sep_2020_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2020-09-04 14:26:15');
