(92, '2020-12-11', '', 'PhD Awarded for Faculty of Physics Department', 'Moganti Venkata Someswara Rao, Assistant Professor of Physics Department, SRKREC has been awarded with PhD from Andhra University for his thesis titled \"Fabrication and Characterisation of Optimised Electro-spun Titanium Dioxide and Composite Nano Fibres for Energy Applications\" under the guideship of Dr. PSV Subba Rao, Research Director, Andhra University.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent SV Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HODs and Staff congratulated for his achievement.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_dec_2020_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'HS', '2020-12-11 14:26:15'),
(93, '2020-12-25', '', 'HPLC Equipment Installed at WET Research Centre', 'High Pressure Liquid Chromatography (HPLC) equipment has been set up at the Water, Environment and Technology (WET) Centre on campus on 24th December 2020. The equipment can be used to identify the mnutest of pesticides and chemical residues in water. The HPLC equipment worth 25 Lakh has been procured as part of Europen Union (EU) - India Project sponsored by Ministry of Science & Technology, Govt. of India.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri. S V. Ranga Raju garu inaugurated the equipment. SRKREC Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Dean (R&D) and EU-India Project Investigator Dr. PARK Raju garu presided over the event. Civil Dept HOD Dr. A. Subrahmanyam Raju, Dr. Sita RamiReddy, Dr. KM Ganesh, Dr. T Rambabu, Dr. Raghuram, Dr. Suribabu, N Siva Kishan, Jeevan and other faculty were present at the event.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/25_dec_2020_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'WT', '2020-12-25 05:26:15'),
(94, '2021-01-10', '', 'Civil Faculty P.Raju gets International Engineering Educator Degree', 'Faculty of Civil Engineering Department Mr. Penupothula Raju has been awarded with \"International Engineering Educator\" Degree from IGIP Austria (Consultative Status with UNESCO). The degree has been presented by Vice President Dr.Axel Zafoschnig on 10-01-2021 at 6 pm.<br><br>\r\nMr. P. Raju is one among the 19 faculty from different institutes in India who is conferred with this degree. The degree has been awarded due to the two year long journey with IUCEE (Indo Universal Collaboration for Engineering Education) and after the completion of a 3 phase certification process.<br>\r\n\r\nManagement, PrincipalIUCEE Co-ordinator Dr.NGK Murthy, HODs and faculty appreciated Mr. P Raju for his achievement.<br>\r\n  <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_jan_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CV', '2021-01-10 05:26:15'),
(95, '2021-02-11', '', 'Young Geo-Technical Engineer Award for Civil Faculty', 'T. Vamsi Nagaraju, Assistant Professor of Civil Engineering Department bagged the prestigious National Level Young Geo-Technical Engineer Award during the Geo-Technical Society\'s National Level Virtual Conference organized by Andhra University (18th & 19th December 2020). Indian Geo-Technical Society confers this award to young engineers every two years in recognition of their research in Geotechnology field.<br>\r\n\r\nManagement, Principal, HODs and faculty appreciated Mr. Vamsi Nagaraju for his achievement.<br>\r\n  <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_feb_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CV', '2021-02-11 05:26:15'),
(96, '2021-02-18', '', 'Industry Institute Partnership Cell (IIPC) Inaugurated in College', 'An \'Industry Institute Partnership Cell\' has been inaugurated by the Management and Administration of SRKR Engineering College on 18th February 2021 at 1130 hrs. The formal inauguration ceremony was graced by the Secretary and Correspondent Sri.S.V.Ranga Raju garu. The CEO of the College Sri.S.R.K.Nishant Varma garu and Director Sri K.Jeeva Sagar garu joined the meeting online. <br><br>\r\n13 companies across all Departments have come forward to sign MoU\'s with SRKR Engineering college to help students get practical training and exposure to industry. The Management has interacted with the representatives of the Industry and noted the expectations from the students graduating out of SRKREC. The Principal and Heads of the Department have explained what the college could offer to Industry through the partnership.<br><br>\r\nThe meeting was presided over by the Dean R&D, Dr.PARK Raju and organised by the IIPC committee coordinated by Sri.N.Siva Kishan of Civil Engineering Department. Close contacts with Industry will help students to be better prepared for work upon their graduation from SRKREC.<br><br>\r\n  <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_feb_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_feb_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2021-02-19 05:26:15'),
(97, '2021-02-25', '', 'Dr. N. Udaya Kumar of ECE Receives NPTEL Appreciation Certificate  ', 'Dr. Udaya Kumar Nadakuduru of ECE Department has been recognized as NPTEL Discipline Star by NPTEL for certification in courses of Electrical Engineering of 50+ weeks of learning and  getting a final score of 55+ in each subject.<br>\r\n\r\nManagement, Principal, HODs and faculty appreciated Dr. Udaya Kumar garu for his achievement.<br><br>\r\n  <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/25_feb_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/25_feb_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'EC', '2021-02-25 05:26:15'),
(98, '2021-02-26', '', 'SRKREC inks MOU with Byrraju Foundation', 'SRKREC has signed an Memorandum of Understanding with Hyderabad based Byrraju Foundation to provide infrastructural facilities to rural areas and mechanisation of agriculture. College principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and representative of the foundation V Pullamraju signed the MOU here on the college premises.<br><br>\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Shri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, CEO SRK Nishant Varma, R&D Dean Dr. PARK Raju garu, Mechanical Department HOD Dr.K. Brahmaraju garu, IIPC Co-ordinator Shri N Siva Kishan, HODs, Dean and other staff were present on the occasion. \r\n<br><br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_feb_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul> \r\n', '', 'MC', '2021-02-27 05:26:15'),
(99, '2021-03-05', '', 'Susmitha and Anjani Devi bagged Oruganti Sundari Merit Scholarship of Rs.25K/- each.', 'Smt Oruganti Sundari annual scholarship award sponsored by Mr Oruganti Bharat (1995 ECE Alumnus), Senior Vice President of operations at Q2 Inc. USA) has been presented to 2 best students of SRKREC. CHAVAKULA SUSMITHA (9.29 CGPA) from 4/4 ECE department and NADIMPALLI ANJANI DEVI (9.29 CGPA) of 4/4 CSE has been adjudged as winners of this award. A cash award of Rs.25,000/- has been presented to each of them.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe awards have been handedover by Sri S V Rangaraju garu, Secretary & correspondent on Friday 5-3-2021 @ 4pm  at Placements hall. Director of the college Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, CEO SRK Nishant Varma, R&D Dean Dr. PARK Raju garu, HODs, Deans and other staff were present on the occasion.<br>\r\n\r\n<H6><B>PRESS COVERAGE:</B></H6>\r\n\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_mar_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-03-05 05:26:15'),
(100, '2021-03-08', '', 'PhD Awarded for Faculty of CSE Department', 'P Bharat Siva Varma, Assistant Professor of CSE Department, SRKREC has been awarded with PhD from KL University for his thesis titled \"Functional Annotation of A Hypothetical Protein to Identify Druggable Components\" under the guidance Dr. K. Subrahmanyam, KLU and Dr. Yesubabu, CRR Engineering College.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, CSE HOD Dr. V Chandra Sekhar garu, other HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CS', '2021-03-08 14:26:15'),
(101, '2021-03-09', '', 'Faculty PhD Awarded from Acharya Nagarjuna University', 'Mathena Sri Hari Varma, Assistant Professor of CSE Department, SRKREC has been awarded with PhD from Acharya Nagarjuna University for his thesis titled \"Efficient Mining Framework to Analyse and Secure Outsourced Transactional Databases\" under the guidance Dr. C V P R Prasad.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, CSE HOD Dr. V Chandra Sekhar garu, other HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"img/news/9_mar_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_mar_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CS', '2021-03-09 14:26:15'),
(102, '2021-03-19', '', 'CR Rao Mathematics Research Centre Inaugurated on campus', 'Mathematics Research Centre of SRKREC, in the name of noted mathematician and centenarian Dr. CR. Rao, has been inaugurated on campus on 19th March 2021. The CR Rao Mathematics Research Centre would help researchers from all departments in their mathematical and statistical analysis of their research problems.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, JNTUK Professor Dr. GVR Deekshitulu garu, Mathematics Dept HOD Dr. R. Subbarao, Dr. CNB Rao, Dr. K. Brahmaraju, Dr. Vasudeva Murthy, Dr. MN Varma, Prof. G. Santhi, Dr. Kishore, Mr. Sobhan Babu, other HODs and staff were present on the occasion.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'HS', '2021-03-20 14:26:15'),
(103, '2021-03-21', '', 'Purohit Cricket League 2021 Hosted by SRKREC', 'SRKREC is hosting a state level cricket tournament exclusively for purohits at SRKREC Cricket ground from 21st to 27th March 2021. As many as 16 teams of purohits from different places of the state are going to participate in the contest. The event is inaugurated by MLA of Bhimavaram Sri Grandhi Srinivas garu & Undi MLA Sri Mantena Ramaraju garu. AP High Court Justice Sri B. Krishna Mohan garu will be the chief guest for the valedictory & final day of the tournament on 27th March 2021.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Physical Directors, HODs and staff were present on the occasion.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2021_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-03-21 14:26:15'),
(104, '2021-03-24', '', '50 Best Ranks in GATE 2021 for SRKREC Students', 'Around 50 students of SRKREC have secured best ranks in GATE 2021. CSE Student C Chaitanya secured All India 33rd Rank in Computer Science category. Around 50 students have scored ranks below 500 and about 30 more students have got ranks below 1000. SRKREC Faculty and Technology Centre Head Dr. NGK Murthy\'s elder son N Viswa Teja has got All India 3rd Rank in Mechanical Division.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HODs and staff were present on the occasion.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-03-24 14:26:15'),
(105, '2021-03-24', '', 'PhD Awarded from SRKREC Mathematics Research Centre', 'Mamidi Pushpalatha, Assistant Professor in Mathematics at Vishnu Institute of Technology has been awarded by Acharya Nagarjuna University for her research undertaken under the guidance of Dr. R Subba Rao, HOD Maths dept, SRKREC <br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'HS', '2021-03-24 14:26:15'),
(106, '2021-07-04', '', 'SRKREC gets AP 2nd Rank and All India 57th Rank by Times Engineering Rankings 2021', 'SRKR Engineering College has bagged 2nd Rank in AP and 57th in India by the recently announced Times Ranking 2021. Principal Dr M Jagapathi Raju garu and Secretary & Correspondent Shri S V Rangaraju garu appreciated the staff and students for this success during the press meeting. \r\n', '', '', '2021-07-04 14:26:15'),
(107, '2021-07-14', '', 'PhD Awarded for Faculty of CSE Department', 'UMN SSVKR Gupta, Assistant Professor of CSE Department has been awarded with PhD from KL University for his research work related to Brain Cancer Treatment under the guidance Dr. Ch. V. Phani Krishna, KLU and Dr. Yesubabu, CRR Engineering College.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, In-charge Principal Dr K. Brahmaraju garu, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, CSE HOD Dr. V Chandra Sekhar garu, other HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/14_jul_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/14_jul_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/14_jul_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/14_jul_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CS', '2021-07-14 14:26:15'),
(108, '2021-07-15', '', 'PhD Awarded for IT Faculty', 'Kalidindi Kishore Raju, Assistant Professor of IT Department has been awarded with PhD from JNTU Kakinada for his thesis titled \"Unsupervised Band Selection Approaches for the classification of remotely sensed hyperspectral images\" <br><br>\n\nSecretary and correspondent Shri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Shri Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, In-charge Principal Dr K. Brahmaraju garu, Dean (R&D) Dr.PARK Raju garu, IT HOD Dr. Bh.V.S.K. Raju, other HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_jul_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_jul_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_jul_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_jul_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>', '', 'IT', '2021-07-15 14:26:15'),
(109, '2021-07-20', '', '88th Birth Anniversary of Founder Celebrated', '88th Birth Anniversary Celebrations of SRKREC founder Sri. Sagi Rama Krishnam Raju garu has been celebrated on 19th July 2021 in the campus. Secretary & Correspondent Sri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Incharge Principal Dr. K. Brahmaraju garu paid homage by offering flowers to the statue of Sri. Sagi Rama Krishnam Raju garu. Heads of the departments, faculty and staff were present on the occasion.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_jul_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_jul_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_jul_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_jul_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-07-20 14:26:15'),
(110, '2021-07-28', '', 'New B.Tech Courses in SRKREC from Year 2021', 'AICTE has sanctioned two new courses in SRKREC from the academic year 2021-22 along with the 2 additional branches sanctioned last year.<br><br>\r\n\r\n1. B.Tech in Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning<br>\r\n2. B.Tech in Computer Science & Design<br>\r\n<br><br>\r\nKeeping in view the importance of Artificial Intelligence, Data Science and Industry 4.0 technologies, AICTE has recommended these new advanced branches / courses in reputed engineering colleges throughout the country. Last year, 2 new courses in B.Tech - Artificial Intelligence & Data Science (AI & DS) and Computer Science & Business Systems (CSBS) has been introduced in SRKREC.<br>\r\n\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_july_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_july_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_july_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_july_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_july_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_july_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_july_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_july_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2021-07-28 14:26:15'),
(111, '2021-08-08', '', 'PhD Awarded for ECE Faculty', 'G Nagaraju, Assistant Professor of ECE Department has been awarded with PhD from KL University for his thesis titled \"An optimised secure hybrid watermarking in medical imaging\" under the supervision of Dr. P Pardhasaradhi, Professor in ECE, KL University.<br><br>\n\nSecretary and correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, ECE HOD Dr. B.V.S.S.N. Raju, other HODs and Staff congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_aug_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>', '', 'EC', '2021-08-08 14:26:15'),
(112, '2021-08-17', '', 'GiTA Scholarships Awarded to Students', 'SRKREC alumni students introduced a special GiTA (Girls in Technology Advancement) scholarship with an inital fund of 10 lakh rupees. A group of 17 girl students who completed engineering in SRKREC from 1984 to 1987 batches has raised this fund in the memory of late beloved women faculty Gita Raj. As part of this scholarship, every year, two girl students - one from Civil Engineering and one from ECE branch would get scholarship worth Rs.25,000/-. For the year 2021, 2/4 Civil student Aregela Jyothirmayee and ECE student Ivvala Kiramnayee received the scholarships.<br><br>\r\n\r\nCollege secretary and correspondent Sri SV Ranga Raju garu, Alumni Association CFO Dr. VK Viswanadharaju garu, HODs of ECE and Civil Deparments and other faculty were present during the occasion.<br><br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_aug_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-08-17 14:26:15'),
(113, '2021-08-26', '', 'Campus Magazine Unveiled by Management!\r\n', 'The campus magazine of SRKREC named Campus Chronicle has been launched officially by the college management here on campus. The Campus Chronicle magazine will publish all the achievements, activities and happenings of the campus every 4 months. The college committee President Sri Sagi Prasada Raju garu, Vice Presidents Sri P Krishnam Raju garu, Sri Gokaraju Ramaraju garu, Secretary & Correspondent Sri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Governing Body Member Dr. K.S. Vijaya Narasimha Raju garu, CEO Sri S.R.K. Nishant garu, Principal Dr. Jagapathi Raju garu, and others were present on this occasion.<br><br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_aug_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>  ', '', '', '2021-08-25 23:26:15'),
(114, '2021-09-10', '', 'Felicitation for CVK Award Mentor & Team', 'The Civil Engineering students of SRKREC secured first place at national level AICTE Chattra Vishwa Karma Award 2020 by designing the shramik web portal. The final year students V Tridesh, K Bhargavi, Shyam Kiran, K Chandrika, S Kranti, K Suryakamal, K Puneeth designed Shramik.in website with the help of mentor Assistant Professor of Civil Department Mr. Raju Penupothula.\n<br><br>\nOut of the 1400 entries from all over India, SRKREC team secured first prize and received a cash award of Rs.51,000/- from union minister of education Dharmendra Pradhan and AICTE chairman Sahasrabuddhe on 5th September 2020 at New Delhi. The Civil Department has felicitated the mentor and his team for their achievement on 9th September on campus. The mentor P Raju said that the details of skilled labour could be found in the portal and in the case of natural disasters, they could be traced and helped. The portal is also useful for the construction industry.<br><br>\nThe Secretary & Correspondent Sri S.V. Rangaraju garu, Principal Dr. Jagapathi Raju garu, Dean (R&D) Dr. PARK Raju garu, Civil HOD Dr. ACSV Prasad, Technology Centre Head Dr. NGK. Murthy and others were present on this occasion.<br><br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_sep_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_sep_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_sep_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_sep_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>  ', '', 'CV', '2021-09-09 23:26:15'),
(115, '2021-09-16', '', 'Felicitations on Engineer\'s Day', 'Civil Engineering Department of SRKREC, in association with IEI, Bhimavaram Local Chapter has celebrated the Engineer\'s Day on campus this Wednesday by felicitating prominent engineering of the locality. Retired SE Sri Rangarao garu, Principal SRKREC Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Sri G Ravi Kiran Shastri (NIT AP), Deputy EE R&B Sri P.V. Ramaraju were felicitated and honored on this occasion. Dr. PARK Raju WET Centre Head, Senior Professors Dr. Subrahmanyam Raju, Dr. Phani Kumar, Siva Rama Raju, Dr. K. Brahma Raju, Dr. K. Suresh Babu, Dr. Viswanadha Raju, Dr. Prasad and other staff were present on this occasion.<br><br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_sep_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>  ', '', 'CV', '2021-09-15 23:26:15'),
(116, '2021-10-02', '', 'Appreciation for Best Performance', '3 Faculty from SRKREC have been given appreciation letters in a function held for their performance and contribution to the college during the recent years. Senior Professor D.V.R Mohan garu, Dr. NGK Murthy and Dr. Suresh Mudunuri of Technology Centre have been presented with Appreciation Certificates from CEO Nishant Varma garu, Secretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu here on 30th September 2021.<br><br>\r\n\r\nProf. DVR Mohan has bagged Best Project Award during the Faculty Workshop conducted for IDEA Lab Mentors at Pune.<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_oct_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_oct_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_oct_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_oct_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n\r\n </ul>', '', '', '2021-10-01 14:26:15'),
(117, '2021-10-06', '', 'PhD Awarded for Physics Faculty', 'V.S. Lakshmi Parana Pathoju, Assistant Professor of Physics Department has been awarded with PhD from Andhra University for her thesis titled \"Study of Molecular Interactions with Thermocostic and Spectroscopic Investigation in certain binary and ternary liquid mixtures\" under the supervision of Prof. K. Samatha, Professor of Andhra University.<br><br>\n\nSecretary and correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Physics HOD Dr. K.V. Raman Murthy, other HODs and Staff congratulated Dr. Aparna.<br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_oct_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_oct_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_oct_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_oct_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>', '', 'HS', '2021-10-06 14:26:15'),
(118, '2021-11-17', '', 'Centre for Foreign Languages Opened at SRKREC', 'A new Centre for Foreign Languages has been started in SRKR Engineerin College to train students in foriegn languages and provide opportunities. Dr. Katharina Gorgen, Director of Goethe Institute at Max Mueller Bhavan, Chennai inaugurated the Centre for Foreign Languages at SRKREC campus. Mr. Prabhakar Narayanan (Head of Language Dept), Mr. Balaji Venkataraman (Co-ordinator of Educational Services) from the Goethe Institute were the guests of honor. As part of the centre activities, 2 batches of students will get trained in Spanish and German Languages on campus. Secretary and Correspondent Sri. S.V. Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Co-ordinator of Centre for Foreign Languages Dr.Bh.V.N. Lakshmi, HODs, Deans and other faculty have been present. \r\n\r\n<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_nov_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'TP', '2021-11-17 14:26:15'),
(119, '2021-11-28', '', '2 SRKR Students bag 44 Lakh jobs at Amazon', '2 Students Dulam Sri Siva Gayatri Devi (4/4 ECE) and Sireesha Burgala (4/4 CSE) secured a six month internship in Amazon with Rs.80,000/- per month as stipend which will be further converted into a full time job with Rs.44 Lakhs Per Annum. The college management congratulated both the students and the placement team for this success.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M.Jagapathi Raju garu, CSE Dept HOD Dr. V Chandra Sekhar garu, ECE HOD Dr. N. Uday Kumar garu, Dean Placements Sri K. R. Satyanarayana garu, other HODS & Deans and placement team were present in the felicitation meeting.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_nov_2021_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', 'TP', '2021-11-28 14:26:15'),
(120, '2021-11-27', '', 'SRKREC inks MOU with Blackbuck Engg Co.\r\n', 'SRKREC signed Memorandum of Understanding with software firm Blackbuck Engineering Company on 27th November 2021. College principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu and CEO of Blackbuck T Anuradha signed the MoU and exchanged them. The MoU is aimed at providing triaing on latest technologies - Artificial Intelligence, Data Science, Machine Learning for students and faculty of SRKREC. <br><br>\r\n\r\nPrincipal Dr. M.Jagapathi Raju garu, Blackbuck CEO Ms. T Anuradha garu, R&D Dean Dr. PARK Raju garu, CSE Dept HOD Dr. V Chandra Sekhar, Technology Centre Head Dr. N Gopala Krishna Murthy, other HODS & Deans were present in the event.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_nov_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_nov_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_nov_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_nov_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'CS', '2021-11-27 14:26:15'),
(121, '2021-12-01', '', 'Mech Dept HOD Elected as IEI Council Member', 'Dr. K. Brahmaraju, Professor and Head of Mechanical Engineering department of SRKREC has been elected as a member of the National Council of Institution of Engineers (IEI), India. A total of 32 members contested in the Mechanical Engineering Division and Dr. Brahmaraju garu won the elections and secured  a second consecutive term. <br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju garu felicitated Dr. Brahmaraju garu on this occasion.<br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_dec_2021_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', 'ME', '2021-12-01 14:26:15'),
(122, '2021-12-04', '', 'PhD Awarded for ECE Faculty', 'K Bala Sindhuri, Assistant Professor of ECE Department has been awarded with PhD from JNTU Kakinada University for her thesis titled \"VLSI Architecture for Reconfigural SIR Filters\" under the supervision of Dr. K Padma Vasavi, HOD of ECE, Shri Vishnu Engineering College for Women, Bhimavaram and Ex-rector of JNTUK Dr Shanti Prabha.<br><br>\n\nSecretary and correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, CEO Nishant Varma garu, Director Shri K. Jeeva Sagar garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, ECE HOD Dr. N. Udaya Kumar garu, other HODs and Staff congratulated her for her achievement.<br>\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_dec_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n </ul>', '', 'EC', '2021-12-04 14:26:15'),
(123, '2021-12-07', '', 'Stakeholder Workshop on Water Quality Aspects of Godavari Western Delta\r\n', 'WET Centre of SRKREC has conducted an extensive survey of Canal water in Godavari Western Delta covering 806 villages and 5 cities of 2450 Sq Kms. The survey results have been presented by Dr. PARK Raju garu, Project PI, in the stake holder workshop conudcted on 6th December 2021 as part of the EU-India H2020 funded project \"Strategic Planning of Water Resources and Implementation of Novel Biotechnical Treatment Solutions and Good Practices (SPRING)\". The survey resulted in shocking results and stated that the water contamination is already at alarming levels and immediate action is recommended by the committee.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, BJP State Discipline Committee Chairman Paka Venkata Satyanarayana, Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju garu and other faculty were present at the meeting.<br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_dec_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'WC', '2021-12-07 14:26:15'),
(124, '2022-03-18', '', '4 SRKR Students Went to Silicon Valley USA', '4 SRKREC students S Vinaya Kumar, Y Sai Teja Sri, K Harsha, and Md Sabiha have been selected as University Innovation Fellows (UIF) and attended Stanford University Silicon Meet Up to be held on Silicon Valley USA from March 2o to 23 2021. The programee is being conducted in partnership with Google.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K. Jeeva Sagara garu, Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju garu, UIF Faculty Coordinator Dr. NGK Murthy and other faculty congratulated and appreciated the team.<br><br><br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_6.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_6.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_mar_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>', '', 'TC', '2022-03-18 14:26:15'),
(125, '2022-03-18', '', 'Holi Celebrated by IT Department', 'Holi festival has been celebrated in the campus by IT department in the name of Varna. Students have celebrated the festival on 18th March 2022 by hand printing and signing on banners.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary & Correspondent Sri SV Rangaraju garu, CEO Sri Sagi Nishant Varma garu, Director Sri K. Jeeva Sagara garu, Principal Dr.M.Jagapathi Raju garu, IT HOD Dr. Bh.RK Raju and other faculty appreciated the team.<br><br><br>\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n ', '', 'IT', '2022-03-18 09:26:15'),
(126, '2022-03-20', '', 'SRKR NSS Camp at Kallakuru\r\n', 'NSS camp was being organized at Kallakuru Village by SRKR students from 21-03-22. The poster relating to this was inaugurated at the campus by the Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College Sri. S. Vital Rangaraju garu. Speaking on this occasion the Principal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said that the NSS unit at SRKR was recognized by the State Govt of AP. NSS Coordinator KNV Satyanarayana had said that this programme was being conducted with the slogan of \'FIT INDIA-HEALTH INDIA\'. As a part of this camp various activities are being planned as below:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>21st March: A Survey on needs of the villagers</li>\r\n<li>22nd March: Awareness session on Plastic</li> \r\n<li>23rd March: Awareness Session On Swach Bharat</li>\r\n<li>24th March: Dental camp</li>\r\n<li>25th March: Planting of saplings in the Village</li>\r\n<li>26th March: Career Guidance and Science Expo to the school students</li>\r\n<li>27th March: General Health Camp.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n <ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n ', '', '', '2022-03-20 09:26:15'),
(127, '2022-03-19', '', 'ECE FDP on Exposure on Fundamentals & Tools Usage for Project Implementation\r\n', 'The Dept of ECE at SRKR Engineering College was conducting a one week Online Student Development Programme on \"EXPOSURE ON FUNDAMENTALS AND TOOLS USAGE FOR PROJECT IMPLEMENTATION\" from 21st March to 25th March, 2022. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by the Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College, Sri. S. Vital Ranga Raju garu. This programme was aimed at enlightening the students on various tools that can be used during their project evaluation.  The alumni of the college who are in prominent positions in the industry will enlighten the students everyday from 7PM to 8PM as a part of this programme. The Principal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and the HOD of ECE Dept Dr. N. Uday Kumar urged the students to make use of this enriching sessions which will provide a platform for the students to equip the latest skills and knowledge through which they can enhance their knowledge.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_mar_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n ', '', 'EC', '2022-03-19 09:26:15'),
(128, '2022-03-21', '', 'IT Dept Workshop AI & ML Based on IOT', 'The Dept of Information Technology at SRKR Engg College was conducting a one week Workshop on \'Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning Based on IOT\' from 21st of March, 2022. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by the Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College Sri. S. Vital Ranga Raju Garu.Speaking on this occasion the Principal of SRKR Engg College, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu and HOD of IT Dept Dr. BHVS Ramakrishnam Raju garu had said that this programme was basically designed with the objective of disseminating the latest technologies to the students by the industry experts. Dr. K. Hemalatha and Dr. K. Kishore Raju will act as faculty coordinators for this workshop.\r\n<br>\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'IT', '2022-03-21 09:26:15'),
(129, '2022-03-20', '', 'PhD Awarded for Mathematics Faculty', 'Yandamuri Sobhan Babu, Assistant Professor of Mathematics Department of SRKREC has been awarded with PhD in Applied Mathematics from Andhra University under the supervision of Dr. M. Vijaya Shanti, Senior Profesor, Andhra University Visakhapatnam.<br><br>\r\n\r\nSecretary and correspondent Shri S.V. Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, Mathematics & Humanities HOD Dr.D. Venkatapathi Raju  garu, other HODs and Staff feliciated and congratulated him for his achievement.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_6.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_6.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20_mar_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'HS', '2022-03-20 10:26:15'),
(130, '2022-03-22', '', 'EEE Tech Symposium on 26th & 27th March\r\n', 'The Dept of EEE at SRKR Engg College is conducting a Technical Symposium named as \'APOORVA\' on 26th & 27th of March, 2022. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by the Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College Sri. S. Vital Ranga Raju garu. This Programme is being conducted with the collaboration and support of the alumni who are in the prominent positions in the industry. The alumni in various foreign countries would connect to the students in virtual mode and some of the alumni will visit the campus physically and interact with the students. Industry experts are also going to be a part of this symposium. Principal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu and Head of EEE Dept Dr. BHRK Varma urged the students to make use of this opportunity and enhance their knowledge. Mr. Kiran Kumar and Mr. Rajasekhar Reddy  are acting as coordinators for this symposium. <br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'EE', '2022-03-22 10:26:15'),
(131, '2022-03-22', '', 'SRKR Student Bags GATE 14th Rank\r\n', 'Mr. Ankireddy Sai Praveen, the student of SRKR Engg College had achieved 14th Rank in the GATE examination and got accolades to the institution. The Secretaty and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College Mr. S. Vital Ranga Raju garu and Principal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu felicitated Mr. Praveen and wished him all the best for his future endeavors. They suggested the students to get inspired from Mr. Praveen and dream high and achieve great results.  Speaking on this occasion Mr. Praveen had said that though he got a very good job opportunity in campus placements, he had always dreamt of doing research in atomic sector. He aspires to become a scientist at Baba Atomic Research Center and do service to the country. HOD of ECE dept Dr. N. Uday Kumar and other faculty conveyed their warm wishes to Mr. Praveen on his achievement. <br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'EC', '2022-03-22 11:26:15'),
(132, '2022-03-23', '', 'Swach Barath Campaign by SRKR Students\r\n', 'The students of SRKR Engineering College had held a SWACHBHARAT campaign at Kallakuru village as a part of the NSS camp and created awareness to the villagers on this noble initiative. This campaign was held with the aim of \'FIT INDIA-HEALTH INDIA\' from ZP High School to Lord Venkateswara Swamy temple. NSS Faculty Coordinators along with the Sarpanch and Vice-Sarpanch of the village had participated in this programme.\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-03-24 04:26:15');
