(133, '2022-03-24', '', 'PhD Awarded to Dean of Placements', 'The Dean Placements of SRKR Engg College Mr. KR Satyanarayana had received the Doctorate from GITAM University in the stream of Mechanical Engineering. He had done his research on the topic of \'Fabrication and Characterization and Micro structural Studies of 6063 Alumini Alloy Nano Composites\'. His research would be adding value to the sectors of Automobiles and Industry. The Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College Sri. S. Vital Ranga Raju garu, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahma Raju garu and other faculty members felicitated Dr. Satyanarayana and wished him all the best for his future endeavors. <br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-03-25 04:26:15'),
(134, '2022-03-24', '', 'Health Camp at Kallakuru', 'The students of NSS Unit at SRKR Engineering College had conducted a health camp at Kallakuru Village. The doctors from prominent hospitals had diagnosed the villagers for various health issues and had given free medicines. This programme was held with the backdrop of \'FIT INDIA-HEALTHY INDIA\'. Dr. Neeladri Raju, college NSS Coordinators Mr. KNV Satyanarayana, Mr. JNS Suryanarayana, E. Suresh and the village administration along with the students of SRKR had rendered their services in this noble initiative.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_mar_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-03-25 04:26:15'),
(135, '2022-03-25', '', 'Planting of Saplings by NSS Students\r\n', 'As a part of the NSS Unit, the students of SRKR Engineering College had planted the saplings in the villages of Kallakuru, Jakkaram, Kalla and Doddanapudi with the backdrop of \'FIT INDIA:HELATH INDIA\'. Free mega health camp was also organized where the villagers are treated for various health related issues and free medicines are delivered to them by Dr. Neeladri Raju and team. Students had conducted a door to door survey in the village regarding the various health issues of the villagers. Coordinators of SRKR NSS Unit Mr. KNV Satyanarayana, P. Uday Raju and VNV Harsha coordinated this noble initiative.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-03-27 04:26:15'),
(136, '2022-03-28', '', 'EEE Women Empowerment Cell Awareness Session to Teen Girls', 'Women Empowerment Cell wing of Dept of EEE at SRKR Engg College had come up with a novel idea and conducted awareness program on physical, psychological and emotional changes in puberty to the teen girls named as \'A DAY WITH TEEN GIRLS\'. The aim of this session is to bring awareness to the young girls of the local community about physical fitness, health & hygiene, psychological and emotional changes in puberty and also about misconceptions and taboos associated with menstruation. Dr. D. Vijaya, Gynecologist of Bhimavaram Hospitals enlightened the target audience. Principal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Head of EEE Dept Dr. BHRK Varma also took part in this programme. This programme was coordinated by Ms. I. Swetha\r\nMounica of EEE Dept.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'EE', '2022-03-28 04:26:15'),
(137, '2022-03-28', '', 'Science Expo & Health Camp by NSS Unit', 'The NSS Unit at SRKR Engineering College had conducted free Mega Health Camp at Kallakuru Village with the collaboration of Neeladri Hospitals. Cancer Patients have been given free treatment and medicines. The students had also conducted Technical Expo and Career Guidance Sessions at the Upper Primary School in the village. The students had conducted door to door survey and created awareness to the villagers on various health issues. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College Mr. SV Ranga Raju, Dr. Neeladri Raju of Neeladri\r\nHospitals, MLA of Undi Constituency Mr. M. Ramaraju, DCCB Chairman Mr.PVL Narasimha Raju, Kshatriya Corporation Chairman Mr. P. Sarraju, Ex TTD Board Member Mr. G. Ramaraju, EX-MP Mr. K. Bapiraju, Tahsildar Mr. Krishna Rao, Coordinators of SRKR NSS Unit Mr. KSV Prasada Raju and Mr. KNV Satyanarayana had participated in this noble initiative.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_mar_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-03-28 04:26:15'),
(138, '2022-03-29', '', 'SRKR Students Selected for Inter University South Zone Chess Competitions\r\n', 'SRKR students B. Dharmika and KSS Harsha had been selected for the Interuniversity Southzone Chess Competitions to be held at SRM University, Chennai from 1 st April, 2022. B. Dharmika had secured 2 nd Place at the Chess Competitions held at Visakhapatnam where she had competed with the students from 200 Colleges under JNTUK. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College, Mr. SV Rangaraju and Principal of SRKR Engineering College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had felicitated both the students and wished them all the best for the upcoming competitions. Physical Director of SRKR Engineering College, P. Satyanarayana Raju and Assistant Physical Directors Dr. Ch. Harimohan and G. Sarika also wished the students and hoped that they would\r\nbe bringing accolades to the institution.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>  \r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_mar_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-03-29 04:26:15'),
(139, '2022-03-30', '', 'Students Grab IBM Placement with 11.5 LPA', 'The students of SRKR Engineering College Ms. Kayala Reshma of IT, Ms. Bhuvaneshwari of CSE and Mr. Veerabhadra Rao of ECE got selected into IBM Company at a lucrative package of Rs. 11.50L Per Annum. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College Mr. SV Ranga Raju garu, Principal of SRKR Engineering Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu, HODs of CSE, IT and ECE and the Placement team congratulated the students and wished that they should excel in their carriers.<br>\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_mar_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_mar_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-03-30 04:26:15'),
(140, '2022-04-04', '', 'SRKR CSE Student Bags Dream Offer @ 47 LPA\r\n', 'Ms. Edida Satya Surya Ramalakshmi, a final year student of CSE at SRKR Engineering\r\nCollege had bagged a dream offer from Bangalore based prominent Cyber Security Company\r\nPAL ALTO NETWORKS with a lucrative package of Rs. 47L Per Annum. She will be under\r\ninternship from April to July with a stipend of Rs.80K per month. Secretary and Correspondent\r\nof SRKR Engineering College Sri SV Ranga Raju and Principal of SRKR Engineering College\r\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Pal Alto Networks had selected 7 students across India from\r\nvarious premier institutions and it was really a matter of great pride and privilege for SRKR to\r\nhave our student as one among them. They said that there are many prominent companies that\r\nare going to visit the campus for placements very shortly. President of SRKR Engineering\r\nCollege Sri. S. Prasada Raju, CEO Sri. S. Nishanth Varma, Director Sri. K. Jeevasagar, HOD of\r\nCSE Dr. Chandrasekhar, Dean Placements Dr. KR Satyanarayana wished the student all the best\r\nfor her bright and illuminating career.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>  \r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/03_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'CS', '2022-04-04 04:26:15'),
(141, '2022-04-08', '', 'Seminar Organized by Women Empowerment Cell of SRKREC\r\n', 'The Women Empowerment Cell at SRKR Engineering College had conducted a seminar on \'Codes of Conduct: Ethics and Indian Culture\' on 8 th April, 2022. Prominent Advocate N. Satyavignana Devi has been the chief guest of this seminar. Speaking on this occasion she said that students of this generation should lead a life style which should be the role model for the upcoming generations. She emphasized that students should respect the Indian traditions and culture which are very prominent from the early ages and they should not get distracted towards the foreign culture which will create a negative impact. She said that students should control their emotions and committing suicides in the heat of the moment should be avoided. Incharge Principal of the College Dr. Brahma Raju had said that it is the moral obligation of the student community to protect the rich traditions and heritage of the India for the upcoming generations. Mrs. Devi was felicitated by the college authorities on this occasion. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari has presided over this event along with Dr. P. Bhavani, the Head of the Chemistry Dept.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-04-08 04:26:15'),
(142, '2022-04-15', '', 'Sports Camp by NSS Unit and Women Empowerment Cell\r\n', 'The Physical Education Department at SRKR Engg College in collaboration with NSS Unit and Women Empowerment Cell is conducting Sports Camp in Shuttle and Volley Ball for one month. This camp was being inaugurated by the Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engineering College Sri. SV Ranga Raju garu on 13th April at the indoor stadium of the college. Speaking on this occasion Sri SV Ranga Raju garu urged the students to give prime importance to sports too along with the academics which will play a vital role in the all round development of the students. Principal of SRKR Engineering College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said that the students in this camp will be trained by the Volleyball Coach Mr. Ramaraju and Shuttle coach Dr. KKK Varma for a period of one month at morning and evening times. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. P. Bhuvaneshwari, NSS Unit Coordinator Prasadraju, Physical Education Dept staff members Dr. P. Satyanarayana Raju, Dr. Harimohan and Dr. G. Sarika took part in this occasion. <br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_apr_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-04-15 04:26:15'),
(143, '2022-04-16', '', 'ISTE NIPUNA 22 Poster Inaugurated', 'ISTE (Indian Society for Technical Education) student chapter is conducting two day national level student symposium NIPUNA-22 at SRKR Engineering College on 29 th and 30 th of this month. A poster of this event is being inaugurated at the college by CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma Garu, Secretary & Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju garu and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu. Speaking on this occasion ISTE Faculty Advisor and Senior Professor P. Subbarao has said that this event would be inaugurated on 29 th April by prominent alumni of the college, D. Somsekhar, Principal ML Scientist at Wadhwani Institute of AI, Bangalore. There was a huge response from student community around the state to participate in this event. ISTE Student Division Chairperson Ganesh, Secretary Harshavardhan, Akash Srinivas had participated in this programme.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-04-16 04:26:15'),
(144, '2022-04-17', '', 'Installation of Lord Abhaya Anjaneya Swamy and Lord Vinayaka Idols at the Campus', 'The idol of Lord Abhaya Anjaneya Swamy had been installed at the SRKR Campus by CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma garu along with his wife and Lord Vinayaka idol had been reinstalled by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju garu along with his wife in a traditional and spiritual environment on 16 th and 17 th of April, 2022 under the supervision of the priests Sri. Ch. Kameswara Sharma and his team. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said that it was a great gesture from the management to install the idols at the campus and urged the students to develop a sense of spirituality which will lead them towards success with confidence. He said that with the blessings of the almighty the pandemic should end shortly and wished that students should march ahead in the path of success. College Vice President Sri. P. Krishnam Raju garu, Governing Body Member Sagi Achutaramaraju Garu along with the HODs, Teaching, Non-Teaching staff and students participated in these rituals. <br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_apr_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n', '', '', '2022-04-17 04:26:15'),
(145, '2022-04-19', '', 'Annual Day Poster Unveiled', 'SRKR Engineering College is going to celebrate its 42nd Annual Day on 23rd April, 2022. The poster relating to this was inaugurated in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju garu, CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma garu and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu. Speaking on this occasion CEO and Secretary had said that this function would be commencing at 9:30AM on 23rd April, 2022 and the Guests for this function were Dr. GV Prasada Raju, Vice Chancellor of JNTU, Kakinada and Dr. KV Lakshmipathi Raju, Principal of MVGR College of Engineering, Vijayanagaram who were the prominent alumni of the SRKR Engg College. They said that it was a matter of great pride that the distinguished alumni of the college are attending the annual day function as the guests. Prizes for the students who have excelled in academics and sports would be given on this occasion. \n\nPrincipal of SRKR Engg College Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said that the Sports Day celebrations would be held at the college on 23rd April, 2022 at 5:30 PM for which Sri. Ravi prakash, Superintendent of Police of West Godavari Dist and ASP Sri. AV Subbaraju would be attending as the guests and give away the prizes to the students who had excelled in Sports. He invited all the students, parents, teaching and non teaching fraternity to attend all the programmes and make it a grand success.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', '', '2022-04-19 04:26:15'),
(146, '2022-04-22', '', 'SRKR Hostel Students Noble Gesture\r\n', 'The hostel students of SRKR Engg College had displayed their noble heart and empathy by donating 1.25L valued furniture to Arunodaya Manovikasa Kendra of Bhimavaram through SRKR CEO Sri. Nishanth Varma Garu on 21st April, 2022. They invited the specially privileged students of the Kendra to the hostel and served the food and instilled a sense of confidence in them. Speaking on this occasion Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma garu had said that he was proud of the noble gesture of the students and appreciated them for their kind heart. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu and Hostel warden Prof C. Ramakrishnam Raju Garu had said that it‚Äôs really an inspirational act from the students and lauded them for their good deed. Vice President of SRKR Sri. G. Ramaraju, Secretary & Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Deputy warden G. Chatrapathi raju and hostel staff took part in this benevolent activity.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', '', '2022-04-22 04:26:15'),
(147, '2022-04-23', '', '42nd Annual Day Celebrated in Grand Manner', 'SRKR Engineering College had celebrated its 42nd Annual day Celebrations on 23rd April, 2022 in a splendid manner. Alumni of SRKR Engg College Dr. Prasada Raju Garu, VC of JNTUK and Dr. Lakshmipathi Raju Garu, Principal of MVGR College of Engineering-Vijayanagaram had graced the occasion as Chief Guest and Guest of Honor. Speaking on this occasion Dr. Prasada Raju garu had said that students should takes the lives of the great people as inspiration and go ahead in their lives. Dr. Lakshmipathi Raju garu had updated the students on the latest trends in the economy and suggested them to be dynamic. President Sri Sagi Prasada Raju garu had suggested the students to update their skills and emerge as victorious in their respective fields. CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma Garu had briefed about the latest changes in the educational sphere and the changes that are going to take place in the college infrastructure in the coming days. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had presented the annual report. Awards were being distributed to the students who excelled in academics, sports and placements. Secretary & Correspondent Sri SV Ranga Raju garu, Director Sri. Jeeva Sagar Garu, Vice-Presidents Sri. P. Krishnam Raju garu, Sri. G. Ranga Raju Garu, Governing Body Member Sri. Vijaya Narasimha Raju Garu, Ex-MLA of Bhimavaram Sri. P. Ramanjenyulu garu had graced the occasion. The cultural activities of the students had been the highlight of the occasion where the  inherent talents of the students were exhibited.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_apr_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<br><br><b>ANNUAL DAY PICTURE GALLERY LINK:</b> <a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/SRKRECOFFICIAL\' target=\'_new\'> https://www.facebook.com/SRKRECOFFICIAL</a>', '', '', '2022-04-23 04:26:15'),
(148, '2022-04-23', '', '42nd Annual Sports Day Celebrated', 'The Annual Sports Day celebrations of SRKR Engg College are being held on 23 rd April, 2022\r\nevening in the college premises. Chairman of AP Legislative Council Sri. K. Moshen Raju, MLA\r\nof Undi Constituency Sri. M. Ramaraju and ASP of West Godavari District Sri. Subbaraju\r\nattended the same as the prominent guests along with President of Management Committee Sri.\r\nS. Prasada Raju, Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju, CEO Sri SRK Nishanth\r\nVarma, Director Sri. Jeeva Sagar and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. The guests emphasized\r\nthe importance of sports in human life and suggested the students to take part in sports actively\r\nthrough which they will have a sound body and mind. Awards were being presented to the staff\r\nand students who excelled in sports events conducted at college level. Physical Director Dr. P.\r\nSatyanarayana Raju along with his team had coordinated this event. HOD‚Äôs, Deans and Faculty\r\nMembers along with large number of students attended this event.<br>\r\n\r\n<br><br><b>SPORTS DAY PICTURE GALLERY:</b> <br>\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/post.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FSRKRECOFFICIAL%2Fposts%2F1918108338377691&show_text=true&width=500\" width=\"500\" height=\"690\" style=\"border:none;overflow:hidden\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allow=\"autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture; web-share\"></iframe>', '', '', '2022-04-23 04:26:15'),
(149, '2022-04-27', '', '15 Days Workshop by CSE Department', 'A Workshop of 15 days by CSE Department has started on 27th April, 2022. Chief Guest of inaugural function of this workshop was Mr. Anand Datla, who was from Natural Solutions Language Home NGO from Hyderabad. He urged the students to do collaborative projects with various IT companies right from the engineering stage so that they would have a fair understanding of the latest trends of the industry. CEO of SRKR Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that many software companies are coming forward to give free internships to the students and many of the students at SRKR are now undergoing internships at prominent companies on latest technologies. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that it is mandatory under National Education Policy for every student to gain expertise in various areas. IT Dept HOD Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju and CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar had said that the students who had excelled in this workshop will be provided with free internship. Selected students from CSE and IT branches will be participating in this workshop.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_apr_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'CS', '2022-04-27 04:26:15'),
(150, '2022-04-28', '', 'IT Dept Conducts Techthon & TechFleet\n', 'IT Dept of SRKR Engg College is conducting 12 hours hackathon named TECHTHON on 5th May, 2022, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju garu had said. IT Dept HOD Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju had said that interested students should send their concepts by 30th of April, 2022. After scrutinizing the ideas, the shortlisted students would only be allowed to participate in this event. Students from any engineering stream can participate in this event. SRKR CEO Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had inaugurated the poster of TECHATHON. Departments of IT, CSBS and AIDS in collaboration with Computer Society of India Student Chapter are going to organize Two Day National Level Symposium TECHFLEET 2K22 on May 7th and 8th. IT HOD Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju is the Coordinator of this event and Dr. I. Hemalatha and Dr. K. Kishore Raju would act as Co-Coordinators and S. Jeswanth Sai and K. Bindu Maduri will act as Student Coordinators. <br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_apr_2022_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'IT', '2022-04-28 04:26:15'),
(151, '2022-04-29', '', 'NIPUNA Tech Fest Inaugurated\r\n', 'NIPUNA a two day event on recent changes in the industry by ISTE Student Chapter  is being inaugurated on 22nd April, 2022 at SRKR Engg College by D. Somsekhar, Principal ML Scientist at Wadhwani Institute of AI, Bangalore. Speaking on this occasion he said that Engineering students should have grip on the group subjects in order to have a competitive edge in the today‚Äôs society. He emphasized that students should have command over the language and they should participate in various National and International events in order to have a bright future. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that it was really a matter of great pride and inspiration that the prominent alumni of the college are rendering their services for the growth of the institution. ISTE Faculty advisor Prof. P. Subbarao had presided over the meeting. ISTE Student Chapter Chairperson SSV Giridhar and Secretary Harshavardhan took care of the various arrangements of this event. The management had felicitated Mr. D. Somsekhar in a grand manner.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/29_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-04-29 04:26:15'),
(152, '2022-04-30', '', 'EEE SANKALP Poster Unveiled', 'EEE Dept of SRKR was going to organize SANKALP 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th and 8th of May, 2022 Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of the same was being inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Program convener and EEE HOD Dr. Varma had said that Students would be given training on various technical issues and various competitions would be conducted on these two days. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had urged the students to make use of this symposium as a way for their bright future. Prof K. Swetha and I. Swetha Mounica will act as faculty coordinators and Mr. A. Harsha, Mr. P. Vamsi, Mr. A. Aditya and Ms. P. Jhansi will act as student coordinators for this symposium.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_apr_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'EE', '2022-04-30 04:26:15'),
(153, '2022-05-01', '', 'PhD Awarded to ECE Faculty', 'SRKR Engg College Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that PhD had been awarded by AU to ECE Dept Faculty R. Krishna Chaitanya. CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Secretary & Correspondent Sri. SV Ranga Raju had felicitated Dr. Krishna Chaitanya. Dr. Krishna Chaitanya had said that he has done his research under the guidance of Dr. P. Mallikarjuna Rao and former Prof of SRKR Dr. KVSN Raju. He told that his research would be significant in reducing the radiation in the Radar Communications. ECE HOD Dr. Udaykumar and other HODs have congratulated him on this occasion.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_may_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_may_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'EC', '2022-05-01 04:26:15'),
(154, '2022-05-02', '', 'SANKETA 2K22 Poster Unveiled', 'The Dept of Mechanical Engg is going to organize SANKETA 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th of May, 2022 Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. SANKETA 2K22 Chairman and HOD of Mechanical Engg Dr. Brahma Raju had said that students would undergo various workshops during this symposium like 3D Printing. Secretary  & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had recommended the students to participate in this symposium actively. Dr. P. Ramamurthy Raju will act as Faculty Coordinator and Mr. Krishna, Mr. Purna Aditya will act as student representatives.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'ME', '2022-05-02 04:26:15'),
(155, '2022-05-02', '', 'TRANCE 2K22 Poster Unveiled', 'The Dept of ECE is going to conduct TRANCE 2K22 a National Level Student Symposium on 7th Of May, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by CEO of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Secretary & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju had wished that this event would be successful. Programme Convener and HOD of ECE Dr. Uday Kumar had said that students would undergo training on latest technologies and participate in various competitions as a part of this event. Prof GVS Padma Rao would act as Co-Convener and Ms. Prathima, Mr. Sanjay and Mrs. Bharathi would act as Faculty coordinators.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_6.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_6.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/2_may_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/2_may_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'EC', '2022-05-02 04:26:15'),
(156, '2022-05-03', '', 'SRKREC Inks MoU With Blood Banks', 'SRKR Engg College had entered an MOU with prominent Blood Banks in Bhimavaram which will facilitate the staff and students to avail blood during the case of emergencies. CEO of SRKR Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that this MOU with Ananda Blood Bank, ASN Raju Charitable Trust and Dharani Voluntary Blood Bank will benefit the students and staff during the unforeseen circumstances. He also said that it is customary to conduct voluntary blood donation camps in the college every year by the students. Secretary & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, NSS Coordinator KSN Prasada Raju and Blood Banks representatives Dr. Jogi Anand Varma, Mr. ASN Raju and Mr. V. Sirish took part in this noble activity.<br>\r\n	\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_may_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_may_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_may_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_may_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-05-03 04:26:15'),
(157, '2022-05-04', '', 'Spurthi 2K22 Poster Unveiled\r\n', 'The Dept of CSE at SRKR is going to conduct National Level Student Symposium SPURTHI22 on May 7th, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated by Secretary  & Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Program convener an HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar had said that students would undergo various workshops and technical competitions as a part of this event. Dr. M. Srihari Varma and K. Aruna Kumari will act as Faculty Coordinators and S. Yasin and G. Supraja will act as student coordinators.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'CS', '2022-05-04 04:26:15'),
(158, '2022-05-05', '', 'Supernova 2K22 Poster Unveiled', 'SRKR Engineering College is conducting 6 National Level Student Symposiums under various departments on 7th May, 2022 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of SUPERNOVA 2022 the National Level Student Symposium by Civil Department has been inaugurated by Secretary& Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Principal had said that because of the Covid Pandemic the symposiums were not being conducted during the last 2 years which had an adverse effect on the research and analytical skills of the students. Keeping in view the upcoming academic examinations, in order to infuse enthusiasm and passion in the students, these symposiums were being planned. Civil dept HOD Dr. Prasad will act as convener, Mr. M. Venkat Rao will act as Faculty Coordinator, K. Jagadeep, Pavan Kumar, P. Raju, JNS Raju will act as Faculty Co-Coordinators and M. Saiprakash and K. Bhaskar will act as Student representatives for this SUPERNOVA2022.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_may_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_may_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_may_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_may_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/5_may_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/5_may_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', '', '2022-05-05 04:26:15'),
(159, '2022-05-07', '', 'Experts Speak at National Level Tech Fests', 'National Level Student Symposiums were being conducted by various departments at SRKR Engg College on 7th May, 2022. Divisional Electrical Executive Engineer (Operations) of Bhimavaram Mr. Peer Ahmed Khan who was the chief guest at Symposium of EEE Dept had said that students are going to have a bright future in core branches. Chief Guest of CSE Dept Symposium Mr. PC Varma, a prominent Alumni of SRKR and Director of  a Software Company had suggested the students to learn the applications of software in various fields through which they will have a good chances of getting prominent jobs. Chief Guest of Civil Dept Symposium Mr. V. Appalaraju, Director of Prominent Construction Company SLV had said that it was indeed a matter of great pride that alumni of SRKR are in prominent positions across the globe. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that alumni of SRKR are the symbols of development and their frequent visits to the institution are of great help in guiding the present students. Secretary&Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SV Rangaraju had said that Symposiums will provide a platform for the students to showcase their skills and talents. HODs of various departments had participated in these symposiums and the chief guests were felicitated by the management in a grand manner.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_may_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_may_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/7_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/7_may_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/new