(166, '2022-05-18', '', 'Blood Donation Camp for Thalassemia Patients Organized', 'The students of SRKR had donated the blood for the Thalassemia patients at the blood donation camp organized in the college on 18th May, 2022. This camp was organized by the NSS Unit of the college in collaboration with Indian Red Cross Society, Eluru. Speaking on this occasion Incharge Principal and HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahmaraju had said that it was really a matter of great pride and inspiration that the students are participating voluntarily in this noble event. He lauded the services of the NSS and Indian Red Cross Society. He called the students to donate blood at frequent intervals which is good for health and also of great help to others who are in need of it. NSS Coordinator Prasadraju, Programme Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, Head‚Äôs of various departments Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju, Dr. P. Bhavani, Dean-Academics Dr. K. Suresh Babu, Assistant Physical Director Dr. Ch. Harimohan, College Engineer Satyanarayana Raju and other staff members participated in this programme.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_may_2022_8.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_may_2022_8.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-05-18 04:26:15'),
(167, '2022-05-17', '', 'Guest Lecture by ECE Department', 'The Department of ECE had conducted a guest lecture on the theme Digital Technologies for Older Persons and Healthy Ageing on 17-05-2022. The guest lecture was delivered by Sri.T.N.V.Mani Kumar, Sub Divisional Engineer (Enterprise Business), Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited, Tanuku. In Charge Principal and HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahmaraju had outlined the theme to the students. HOD of ECE Dept Dr. Udaykumar had emphasized the relevance of the theme. Smt.Prathima Gamini, Assistant Professor of ECE Department acted as event coordinator. The Resource person Sri. T.N.V.Mani Kumar has taken session on technical aspects, recent trends and Global insights of Telecommunication. Students of Ist Year ECE and Faculty members participated in this programme.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_may_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_may_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', 'EC', '2022-05-17 04:26:15'),
(168, '2022-05-21', '', 'NEET Entrance Examination Centre @ SRKR', 'Medical PG Entrance examination NEET was conducted in a peaceful manner at SRKR on 21st May, 2022. This was the first time that SRKR was allotted as the examination center for NEET after Bhimavaram was announced as the district headquarters for the new West Godavari District. SRKR Secretary&Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishant Varma said that it was really a matter of pride for the SRKR to be allotted as the test center and he said that SRKR is ready to host as center for any national level examinations. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that all the arrangements were made for the candidates appearing for NEET keeping in view the temperature and climatic conditions. Total of 152 students were allotted and 137 were present and 15 were absent for the examination. Dr. N. Gopalakrishna Murthy acted as the Chief Superintendent for this examination.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_may_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_may_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_may_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_may_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/21_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/21_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'TC', '2022-05-21 04:26:15'),
(169, '2022-05-23', '', 'EEE Department Organizes Project Expo', 'The Dept of EEE had conducted Project Expo on 23rd May, 2022. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should convert these projects into startups and then only it would be beneficial to the society. He said that students should do projects with minimum investment and maximum results. He emphasized that if students come forward with good projects, college is ready to invest in them and mould them into startups. Special attraction of this expo was the project which will not allow the vehicle to go forward if the driver is drunk and the ECG machine that was developed by the students. EEE Dept HOD Dr. Varma and faculty DVR Mohan also took part in this expo.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_may_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_may_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_may_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_may_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/23_may_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/23_may_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', 'EE', '2022-05-23 04:26:15'),
(170, '2022-05-24', '', 'Valedictory Function of Volley Ball Coaching Camp', 'The volleyball coaching camp at SRKR which is being conducted for the last one month has ended on 24th May, 2022. Speaking on this occasion former national volleyball player and trainer Dantuluri Prabhakar Raju had said that students will excel in the field of sports only through continuous commitment and hard work. Former National Volleyball Player Shivaji Raju had said that studies can land in good jobs at state and central level by excelling in the field of sports and students should give importance to sports too along with academics. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the college management is willing to support the students in the area of sports and that is the reason for many SRKR students being placed in University team for many national events. Sports kits were being handed over to students who took part in this camp. Physical Director of SRKR Dr. P. Satyanarayana Raju had presided over this meeting. Assistant Physical Directors Dr. Harimohan and G. Sarika also took part in this meeting.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_may_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_may_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_may_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_may_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_may_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_may_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_may_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_may_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/24_may_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/24_may_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n', '', '', '2022-05-24 04:26:15'),
(171, '2022-06-03', '', 'Valedictory Function of Shuttle Coaching Camp', 'The shuttle coaching camp at SRKR which was being conducted for the last 45 days has ended on 31st May, 2022. This was organized in collaboration with Women Empowerment Cell, NSS Unit and Physical Education Dept. Speaking on this occasion, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students can reduce their mental tensions and emerge victorious by taking part in various sports. He said that the management is planning to provide better sports infrastructure to the students and je urged the students to keep up the name of the college in sports arena too along with the academic arena. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari and NSS Coordinator Mr. Prasada Raju had said that there was huge response from the students towards this camp. Head of English Dept Dr. Lakshmi, Coach Dr. Kirankumar Varma, Vidyasagar and Physical Directors G. Harimohan and Ms. Sarika also took part in this programme.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '2022-06-03 04:26:15'),
(172, '2022-06-03', '', 'SRKREC Wins FIT INDIA Challenge', 'SRKR Engineering College emerged as the winners in the \'FIT INDIA\' Challenge conducted by AICTE last year. AICTE has issued a letter in this regard and the same was handed over to Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju by Dr. Bhavani Head of Chemistry Dept and organizer of Fit India Challenge. Speaking on this occasion, Dr. Bhavani had said that as per the vision of our PM Sri. Narendra Modi, AICTE had requested the educational institutes across the country to conduct this challenge in order to increase the physical and mental strength of the students. SRKR had conducted this challenge with 1500 students in collaboration with PAIE (People Association for Inner Engineering) Cell, NSS Unit and Physical Education Dept. AICTE after scrutinizing the videos of hundreds of colleges across the country, SRKR was declared as the winner in Category III. College President Sri. Prasada Raju, Secretary & Correspondent Sri. Nishanth Varma had congratulated the staff and the students for bringing laurels to the institute. Dr. Satyanarayana Raju, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, Prasada Raju and Ramesh Raju also participated in this occasion. <br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/3_jun_2022_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-03 04:26:15'),
(173, '2022-06-06', '', 'World Environment Day Celebrated', '\r\nThe World Environment Day Celebrations were conducted in a grand manner at SRKR in collaboration with the Women Empowerment Cell. Sri. Sivaramakrishna, Commissioner of Bhimavaram Municipality attended this event as a chief guest. Speaking on this occasion he called the students to plant saplings in large numbers in order to protect the mother earth. The guest of Honor for this vent was Dr. Vijaya, Gynaecologist at Bhimavaram Hospitals. She said that earth had lost up to 60% fertility until now, and if we don‚Äôt step in to preserve the environment, then we will be facing food crisis in the future. Principal of SRKREC Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the students of SRKR will play a vital role in the restoration of the Yanamadurru drain.  HOD of English Dept Dr. Lakshmi and Coordinator of Women Empowerment Cell Dr. Bhuvaneshwari had said that many competitions were conducted to the students on the eve of World Environment Day and the prizes were distributed to the winners. Exhibition of organic plants by Mr. Seetharamaraju stood as the special attraction in this programme. Dr. P. Bhavani, Roopajhansi etc. had took part in this occasion.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_6.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_6.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n   <li><a href=\"img/news/6_june_2022_8.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/6_june_2022_8.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-06 04:26:15'),
(174, '2022-06-08', '', 'Placement Day Celebrated', 'Placement Day Celebrations were held in a grand manner at SRKR Engg College on 08-06-22. Speaking on this occasion Secretary cum Correspondent of SRKREC Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that in this academic year 1157 students had got 2642 offers from various prominent companies across the globe. The college had achieved a novel position in the entire state of AP in terms of placements. The management had celebrated this achievement in the presence of placed students and their parents. Sri. Nishanth Varma had said that students had got highest package worth Rs. 47.2 LPA and some of the companies are also providing internships to the students with a stipend of Rs. 80000 per month. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that in spite of Covid, the students had excelled in placements with their hard work, passion and support from the management. Placement Dean Dr. Satyanarayana had said that the management had taken all the necessary measures to provide the students with the latest training, which had played a key role in achieving large number of placements. President Sri. Prasada Raju, Secretary cum Correspondent Sri. Nishanth Varma and Director Sri. Jeevasagar had congratulated the placement team and principal for this novel achievement.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_june_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_june_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_june_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_june_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_june_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_june_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_june_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_june_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_june_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_june_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', 'TP', '2022-06-08 04:26:15'),
(175, '2022-06-11', '', 'Chemistry Department conferred as Research Centre by JNTUK', 'The Department of Engineering Chemistry at SRKR Engg College has been conferred with the \'Research Centre\' status by the JNTUK. The official proceedings of the same were released by the college management yesterday. Speaking on this occasion, Principal of SRKREC Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that under the National Educational Policy, multidisciplinary studies are given more importance and research centres play a vital role in the promotion of the same. HOD of Engg Chemistry Department Dr. P. Bhavani had said that the faculty in the department are having rich academic and research experience and had published 179 research papers in various reputed journals and conferences. Until now, 8 research projects are also completed by the department. Majority of the faculty in the department had completed their PhD and all the facilities are being provided in the department for the scholars to pursue their research.  She urged the scholars to make use of the same and promote research. College President Sri. S. Prasada Raju, Secretary cum Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had congratulated the team of Chemistry Department for achieving this novel status. Faculty of the Chemistry Dept Dr. Chandrasekhar, Dr. Diwakar, Dr. Nagababu, Dr. Kishore, J. Suresh Kumar, Ms. Balageetha, Ms. KT Bhavani also took part in this programme.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_june_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_june_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n', '', 'HS', '2022-06-11 04:26:15'),
(176, '2022-06-13', '', 'SRKR Emerges as Winner in AICTE FIT INDIA Challenge - Category II', '	SRKR Engineering College which has already secured top place AICTE Fit India Challenge Category-III has now secured yet again a top place in Category-II too. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that III Year B. Tech Students Geddam Kumarbabu and P. Noris Swamikiran in the Individual Category had completed the desired yoga postures in 6 minutes and created a record. As per AICTE these postures can be completed in 7 minutes. The results were released by the AICTE yesterday. The students were being felicitated by the Member of the Governing Body Mr. S. Satya Pratik Varma in the college yesterday. President of SRKR Sri. S. Prasada Raju, Secretary cum Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had congratulated the students, physical education department for this noble achievement.<br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/13_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/13_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/13_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/13_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/13_june_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/13_june_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/13_june_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/13_june_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-13 04:26:15'),
(177, '2022-06-22', '', 'International Yoga Day Celebrated On Campus', 'The International Yoga Day Celebrations were held in a grand manner at SRKR Engineering College on 21st June, 2022. The yoga postures by the students who are the winners in AICTE Fit India Challenge stood as the special attraction in these celebrations. Chief Guest of this occasion ASP Sri. Subbaraju had said that students should practice yoga through which they will attain mental peace and can emerge victorious in studies too. He congratulated the students who are the winners of the AICTE Fit India Challenge. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students of SRKR from the Ist Year itself will be trained in yoga through the S+ course which was yielding phenomenal results. Commissioner of Bhimavaram Municipality Mr. Sivaramakrishna, DEO Mr. Ramana, Governing Body Member of SRKR Mr. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of Engg Chemistry and Coordinator of PAIE (Peoples Association of Inner Engineering) Cell Dr. P. Bhavani, Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, P. Ramesh Raju, Students of PAIE Cell and NSS had participated in this event.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_june_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_june_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_june_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_june_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/22_june_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/22_june_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-22 04:26:15'),
(178, '2022-06-26', '', 'Inauguration of Sagi Rama Krishnam Raju Marg', '	The prominent road in Bhimavaram which is called as Juvvalapalem Road until now has been officially named as \'Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju Marg\' on 26th June, 2022 by MLA of Bhimavaram Mr. Grandhi Srinivas, Collector and District Magistrate of West Godavari District Mrs. P. Prashanthi IAS, Muncipal Commissioner of Bhimavaram Mr. S. Sivarama Krishna, President of SRKR Mr. S. Prasad Raju, Secretary & Correspondent of SRKR Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma, GB Members of SRKR in the presence of many prominent people of the city, Staff Members of SRKR and Students. Celebrating this occasion, the Leadership of SRKR along with the staff and students had conducted a rally in the SRKR Marg. Speaking on this occasion Mr. Grandhi Srinivas had said that Bhimavaram had become an educational hub based on the foundation of Mr. Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju. President of SRKR Mr. Prasad Raju had congratulated the govt for its noble gesture. Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that all the steps would be taken to carry forward the legacy of Mr. Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had emphasized the prominence of SRKR in the country. Many Prominent Leaders, Police Officials and large number of people attended this occasion.<br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n		  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_8.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_8.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n\r\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/26_june_2022_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/26_june_2022_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-26 04:26:15'),
(179, '2022-06-27', '', 'Student Placed in Wells Fargo with 20 LPA Package', 'Final Year IT student Ms. Yojitha Dandamudi was selected for prominent IT Company WELLS FARGO with a package of 20 LPA. The management had felicitated her on this occasion. Speaking on this occasion Dean Placements Dr. Satyanarayana had said that Yojitha was selected as a Process Associate at Wells Fargo. President of SRKR Dr. Prasad Raju had expressed his happiness that all the eligible Final Year students had been placed with a record placement of 1186 offers. The students as well as their parents are very happy about these rare feet.  Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Governing Body Member Mr. Pratik Varma had suggested the placement team to start the training for the upcoming batches on war front and make sure that the placements increase year by year. HOD of IT Dept Dr. BHV Ramakrishnam Raju had also participated in this occasion.<br>\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n <li><a href=\"img/news/27_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	 </ul>\n', '', 'IT', '2022-06-27 04:26:15'),
(180, '2022-06-27', '', 'Celebration Begun at SRKR on Alluri Sitarama Raju 125th Anniversary', 'The 125th Anniversary Celebrations of Prominent Freedom Fighter Sri. Alluri Sitarama Raju had begun at SRKR Engg College on 27th June, 2022. These celebrations had gained major importance in view of the visit of the Honourable Prime Minister of India Mr. Narendra Modi to Bhimavaram on 4th of July, 2022. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that these celebrations should inspire everyone regarding the life and passion of Alluri Sitarama Raju. He said that Alluri had inspired many people in his tender age and made them revolt against the British empire. The youth of this generation should learn about him and imbibe his leadership qualities. He inspired the students to welcome the Honourable PM of India in a very grand manner. Dr. Lakshmi, Dr. Bhavani. Mr. Seetharamaraju, Mr. Prasad and a large number of students took part in this occasion.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_june_2022_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_june_2022_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_june_2022_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_june_2022_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/27_june_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/27_june_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-27 04:26:15'),
(181, '2022-06-28', '', 'Azadi ka Amruth Mahotsav - Patriotic Songs Competition Conducted', 'The students of SRKR as a part of the Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav and 125th Anniversary Celebrations of prominent freedom fighter Alluri Sitarama Raju had conducted patriotic songs competition in the campus where the audience where instilled with pride and devotion towards the country. The performances of the students stole the show. Program Coordinators Dr. P. Bhavani and Mr. E. Sitarama Raju had urged the students to enlighten the society with the passion of Alluri Sitarama Raju. <br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/28_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/28_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-28 04:26:15'),
(182, '2022-06-30', '', 'Grandson of Alluri Sitarama Raju Felicitated at SRKR', 'The Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had felicitated Sri. Alluri Ramaraju, the grandson of the prominent freedom fighter Sri. Alluri Sitarama Raju on the occasion of \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\' and 125th Birth Anniversary Celebrations of Sri. Alluri Sitarama Raju. Speaking on this occasion he said that the patriotism of Sri. Alluri Sitarama Raju should be imbibed by everyone. Coordinator of this event Sri. E. Sitarama Raju had said that Alluri Sitarama Raju has not only fought for the freedom, but he had also served the tribal in their each and very need. HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahma Raju, HOD of Chemistry Dr. P. Bhavani and HOD of English Dr. Lakshmi took part in this occasion.<br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_june_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_june_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/30_june_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/30_june_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-06-30 04:26:15'),
(183, '2022-07-01', '', 'Badminton District Selections to be Held at SRKREC', 'Badminton district selections are going to be conducted at SRKR Engg College on 8th, 9th and 10th of July by the name \'Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju Memorial\'. The brochure relating to the same was inaugurated by the Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma on 1st July, 2022. The interested aspirants should send their nominations to Sri. Harimohan before 7th of July, 2022. Players shortlisted in this selections would be made eligible for the state level competitions. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, PD Dr. Satyanarayana Raju, Sri. Harimohan, HOD of Mechanical Dr. Brahma Raju took part in this event.<br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>', '', '', '2022-07-01 04:26:15'),
(184, '2022-07-01', '', 'Students Perform Rally on the occasion of 125th Birth Anniversary', 'The students and the staff of SRKR Engineering College had conducted a massive rally from the college premises to the \'Statue of Bravery\' which is going to inaugurated by the Honourable PM of India on 4th July, 2022. The rally was flagged off by the leadership of the college at the college premises. Speaking on this occasion Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had urged the students to imbibe the qualities of patriotism and leadership of prominent freedom fighter Sri. Alluri Sitarama Raju. He requested the students and the staff to make the visit of Indian PM a grand success. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Governing Body Member Sri. S. Pratik Varma, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahma Raju and the staff members along with the students took part in this rally in large number..<br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/1_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/1_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-01 04:26:15'),
(185, '2022-07-04', '', 'SRKR Steals The Show at PM Modi\'s Meet', 'The students of SRKR Engineering College had stolen the show at the PM Modi\'s meet at Bhimavaram on 4 th of July, 2022 on the occasion of \'Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav\' and \'125th Birth Anniversary Celebrations of Alluri Sitarama Raju\'. Around 3000 students and 1000 staff members from the college wearing the tricolour t-shirts depicting the national integrity attended the program\nand mesmerized the audiences with their stunning cultural programmes. They stood as the centre of attraction in the whole program. College President Sri. S. Prasad Raju, Secretary Cum Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Governing Body Member Sri. S. Satya Pratik Varma and Principal of SRKR\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had thanked all the students and staff members for making the programme successful and lifting the pride of the institution.. <br>\n\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/04_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/04_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/04_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/04_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	 </ul>\n', '', '', '2022-07-04 04:26:15'),
(186, '2022-07-05', '', 'EAPCET being Conducted at SRKREC', 'EAPCET 2022, the common entrance test for Engineering, Agriculture and Pharmacy Courses by the Govt of Andhra Pradesh was conducted smoothly on the second day (05-07-22) at SRKR Engineering College. Out of registered 440 students, 419 students attended the examination. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and team coordinated the examination process and made sure that it is done smoothly.<br>\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/4_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/4_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	 </ul>\n', '', '', '2022-07-05 04:26:15'),
(187, '2022-07-08', '', 'Badminton Selections at SRKREC', 'The Badminton selections of the old West Godavari District are going to be conducted at the SRKR Engineering College, Bhimavaram from 8th of July, 2022 said Secretary of the District Association Mr. Vamsi Krishna and Organising Secretary Dr. P. Satyanarayana Raju. Interested players are requested to submit the entries by the end of the day on 7th July, 2022. Winners of this selections will be playing at the State Level Championship.  Principal of SRKR and Tournament Convener Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had requested the interested players to avail this opportunity and he thanked the management or SRKR for their valuable support in conducting this event.<br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-08 04:26:15'),
(188, '2022-07-08', '', 'Badminton Selections Inaugurated by Srikanth Kidambi\r\n', 'The West Godavari District Level Badminton selections were inaugurated at the SRKR Engineering College on 8th July, 2022. Speaking on this occasion West Godavari Badminton Association President Smt. Chitturi Satya Usha Rani had said that its high time that the sports should be given prime importance right from the school level, then we can be able to produce some great players. Governing Body Member of SRKR Sri. S. Pratik Varma had said that at SRKR the management is committed to support sports too along with the studies. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should give importance to sports too along with the studies, so that they can grow in their respective careers. Thomas Cup winner and prominent badminton player of India Sri. Srikanth Kidambi inaugurated the event virtually and said that in the coming days more players should represent India at the National Level. He thanked the management of SRKR for giving prime importance to sports. Smt. Usharani was grandly felicitated by the management on this occasion. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Secretary of Badminton Association M. Vamsi Krishna, Co-Secretary Sri. VV Somaraju had graced this occasion. <br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/8_july_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/8_july_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-08 04:26:15'),
(189, '2022-07-10', '', 'Badminton Selections Ends at SRKREC\r\n', 'The district badminton selections that are being conducted at SRKR from the last 3 days had ended on 10th July, 2022 in a very grand manner. The prizes were distributed to the winners by Governing Body Member of SRKR Mr. Pratik Varma and Vice President of SRKR Mr. SV Ranga Raju. 400 Participants and 650+ matches were being conducted as a part of this event. In charge Principal of\nSRKR Dr. Brahma Raju and representatives of the District Badminton Association had participated in this closing celebrations.<br> 	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/10_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/10_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\n	 </ul>\n', '', '', '2022-07-10 04:26:15'),
(190, '2022-07-09', '', 'JNTUK Grants 6 Research Centres To SRKR\r\n\r\n', 'JNTUK has conferred \'Research Centre\' status to the departments of CSE, IT, ECE, EEE, Civil and Mechanical Engineering; Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The documents relating to the same were being handed over to Governing Body Member of SRKR, Mr. S. Satya Pratik Varma. Mathematics and Chemistry Departments are already having the research centre status and so it‚Äôs a huge opportunity for the young researchers to pursue their research in these 8 departments, principal had said. Mr. Pratik Varma had thanked the VC of JNTUK for grating the research centres and giving an opportunity to promote the research. Vice-President of SRKR Mr. SV Ranga Raju and the HOD‚Äôs of CSE, IT, ECE, EEE, Civil and Mechanical Departments participated in this meeting.<br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/9_july_2022_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/9_july_2022_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>', '', '', '2022-07-09 04:26:15'),
(191, '2022-07-11', '', 'Best Paper Award for Civil Faculty at China International Conference\r\n', 'Mr. Vamsi Nagaraju, Assistant Professor in the Civil Dept at SRKR Engineering college had got the Best Paper Presentation Award at the International Conference ACEER 2022 conducted in China from 4th to 7th of July said Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Mr. Vamsi had said that along with the award, he received a financial assistance of 800 USD. Best Paper Presentations were awarded to 5 faculties in the world and he is one among them.  Governing Body Member of SRKR Mr. Pratik Varma had felicitated Mr. Vamsi on this occasion and said that all the faculty in the college should take this as an inspiration. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Civil Engineering Dept Professor Dr. Padmanadha Raju took part in this occasion. <br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/11_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/11_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>', '', 'CV', '2022-07-11 04:26:15'),
(192, '2022-07-12', '', 'SRKR Students Get 26.5 Lakhs Funding from MSME', 'Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises (MSME) of Govt of India had funded Rs.26.5L to the students of SRKR, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Revealing the details, Head of the Technology Centre Dr. Gopi had said that Dept of ECE had got a funding of 8L for Drones which will be used during natural calamities. Dept of Mechanical Engineering got a funding of 3.5L for the drones which will be used to repair the pipes underground. Smart glasses for the partially blind and complete blind people got a funding of 15L. Governing Body Member Mr. Pratik Varma had expressed his happiness about this achievement and urged the students to bring out state of the art products. The entire team who got the funding were felicitated by the college vice president Sri. SV Ranga Raju along with the HODs of CSE, ECE, EEE and Mechanical Departments. <br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/12_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/12_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/12_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/12_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/12_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/12_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', 'TC', '2022-07-12 04:26:15'),
(196, '2022-07-17', '', 'Graduation Day Celebrated on Campus', 'The Graduation Day Celebrations at SRKR Engineering College were conducted in a jubilant manner on 17th July ,2022. The Chief Guest of this function was Mr. GSN Raju, Chairman-Appellate Committee of AICTE and VC of Centurion University, Visakhapatnam. He suggested the students to make use of the latest technologies and land in their dream jobs. He said that technology was developing very vastly from the last 10 years and students should make use of this technology. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had presented a brief report on the achievements of the college and placement statistics. Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR, Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had urged the students to make SRKR proud with their great work and bring laurels to the institution as well as their respective families. SRKR Vice President Dr. Krishnam Raju, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Dean Evaluation Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju and students along with their parents had participated in large numbers.<br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/17_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/17_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-17 04:26:15'),
(195, '2022-07-16', '', 'SRKR Student Placed in Amazon with 44LPA', 'The Final Student of CSE, Ms. CH. Mahima Bharathi was placed in Amazon as a software engineer with a package of 44LPA. Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had felicitated her and thanked her for bringing laurels to the college. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that it is a great achievement that many of the students of SRKR had landed in the jobs with high packages. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Placements Coordinator Dr. Lakshmi, HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar had participated in this occasion.<br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/16_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/16_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>', '', '', '2022-07-17 04:26:16'),
(193, '2022-07-15', '', 'SRKR Students Truimph at APSSC Examinations', 'The alumni of SRKR ECE Dept Mr. John Erwin and Ms. Premanvita had selected in APPSC Exams as Deputy Collector and MPDO respectively. They were felicitated in the college by Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and he expressed his happiness for their achievement and wished them all the best in their future endeavours. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, ECE HOD Dr. Uday Kumar participated in this occasion. <br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_july_2022_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_july_2022_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_july_2022_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_july_2022_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-15 04:26:16'),
(194, '2022-07-15', '', 'DST Funded Entrepreneurship Awareness Camp Organized', 'Entrepreneurship Awareness Camp was being conducted by the technology centre at SRKR Engineering College for three days. This was inaugurated by the Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. He addressed the students and asked them to choose the path of entrepreneurship which will create an impact on the society and on the lives of the people. He stated that the youth of the country should develop and mould as entrepreneurs. He reminded the students about the old student of the SRKR college is now earning crores of rupees through his start up at Gujarat. Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopala Krishna Murthy had said that this programme was arranged with the financial assistance of DST and NIMT. Dean R&D of SRKR, Dr. P. Ramakrishna Raju, Dean Academics Dr. Suresh Babu, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, Dr. M. Suresh Babu took part in this occasion. <br>\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_july_2022_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_july_2022_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/15_july_2022_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/15_july_2022_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', 'TC', '2022-07-15 04:26:16'),
(197, '2022-07-18', '', 'SRKREC Receives A Grade from NPTEL and stood in Top 100 Colleges in India ', 'SRKR Engineering College stood in the top 100 colleges in India in NPTEL and also received \'A\' Grade from NPTEL and IIT Chennai. The certificate relating to the same was handed over to Secretary Cum Correspondent of SRKR Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma by the Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopala Krishna Murthy had said that NPTEL was started in SRKR in 2017 and until now around 7000 students received the certificates from various prestigious universities across the country.  Mr. Nishanth Varma asked the faculty and the students to make use of the technology Centre and enhance their knowledge. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju also took part in this occasion.<br>\r\n\r\n	<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/18_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/18_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n', '', 'TC', '2022-07-18 04:26:15'),
(198, '2022-07-19', '', 'Founder\'s 89th Birth Anniversary Celebrated', 'The founder of SRKR and the \'METAL KING\' awardee by then PM Smt. Indira Gandhi Sri. Sagi Rama Krishnam Raju 89th Birth Anniversary Celebrations were celebrated in a grand manner on 19th July, 2022. The statues of SRKR in his native village Chinna Amiram and in the college were garlanded by the Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Around 100 members from the staff and students donated blood on this occasion through NSS. Speaking on this occasion, he praised the vision of SRKR and the name and fame that the college had today is all attributed to the vision of the founder and the present management. NSS In Charge Dr. Chaitanya, KSS Prasada Raju and HOD\'s of various departments along with the staff members participated in large numbers.<br>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\">\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_july_2022_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_july_2022_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_july_2022_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_july_2022_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n	  <li><a href=\"img/news/19_july_2022_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/19_july_2022_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '2022-07-19 04:26:15');
