(240, '2022-09-21', NULL, 'Inauguration of DST FDP on Integrative Research in Various Fields of Engineering', 'Inaugural Function of FDP on \'INTEGRATIVE RESEARCH IN VARIOUS FIELDS OF ENGINEERING\' had took place on Tuesday. Professor of GITAM University Dr. Srinivas Prasad had attended the same as a chief guest and addressed the participants. He said that Internships and Start-ups would play a key role in the development of technical students. SRKR and GITAM are playing a vital role in the areas of research in the states of AP and Telangana. Collaborative Research and Training programmes are being organised by both the institutes through which students and faculty may have expertise and develop in their careers. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HOD of Mechanical Dept Dr. Brahma Raju, Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy, Dr. P.A. Ramakrishnam Raju, Dr. B. Ravi Kumar Varma took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922103717_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922103717_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922103717_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922103717_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922103717_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922103717_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922103717_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922103717_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922103717_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922103717_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-09-22 05:07:17'),
(241, '2022-09-21', NULL, 'Prominent Alumni and IFS Officer Visits SRKR', 'Prominent Alumni of SRKR and Tamil Nadu Cadre IFS Officer Mr. Nagasatish, had visited the campus on Tuesday and addressed the students. He said that students should be mentally and physically strong and should be aware of all the latest happenings and then they can excel in their careers. They should not have inferiority complex. He said that SRKR played a vital role in moulding his career and making him what he is today. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, ECE HOD Dr. Udaykumar and team had felicitated the guest and wished him all the best for his future endeavours. \r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922104136_1.30.56 AM (5).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922104136_1.30.56 AM (5).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922104136_2.30.56 AM (4).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922104136_2.30.56 AM (4).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922104136_3.30.56 AM (3).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922104136_3.30.56 AM (3).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20220922104136_4.30.56 AM (2).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20220922104136_4.30.56 AM (2).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-09-22 05:11:36'),
(242, '2022-09-22', NULL, 'State Level U-13 Sub Juniors Badminton Championship at SRKR', 'SRKR Engineering College is hosting the prestigious Sri. Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju Memorial Badminton Championship (State Level U-13 Sub Juniors Badminton Championship) from Friday. The qualifying matches were inaugurated by Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. He said that students excel in sports as well as well as academics. The valedictory would be conducted on 25th and the winners would participate at National Level Championship at Lucknow. Physical Director Dr. Satyanarayana Raju and team took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"20221011135629_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221011135629_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"20221011135629_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221011135629_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"20221011135629_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221011135629_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"20221011135629_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221011135629_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"20221011135629_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221011135629_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2022-10-11 08:26:29'),
(243, '2022-09-22', NULL, 'State U-13 Badminton Championship Inaugurated at SRKR', 'The State Level U-13 Badminton Championship was inaugurated at SRKR by Superintendent of Police, West Godavari District Sri. Ravi Prakash. Speaking on this occasion he said that students should strive ahead in sports too along with academics and then only they can larch ahead with confidence. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the college is renowned at the National Level for its achievements. Badminton Association State Secretary Mr. Chowdary had said that the new state is marching ahead in the field of badminton. The SP had personally interacted with all the participants and wished them all the best. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Physical Education Department Team and other officials took part in this event. \r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112129_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112129_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2022-10-13 05:51:29'),
(244, '2022-09-23', NULL, 'SP Congratulates for Full Seat Allotment in 1st Phase of EAPCET 2022', 'SP Mr. Ravi Prakash had congratulated the management of SRKR for completing all the seats in the first phase allotment of EAPCET. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that SRKR is the only college with large number of seats under JNTUK. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. Nishanth Varma had congratulated all the students for selecting SRKR and he said that the management will strive hard top make their dreams come true. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju and administrative team members participated in this joyous moments. \r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112826_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112826_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112826_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112826_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013112826_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013112826_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-10-13 05:58:26'),
(245, '2022-09-24', NULL, 'State Level Badminton in Full Swing at SRKREC', 'The State Level U-13 Badminton Championship is going on in full swing at SRKR. The matches were very sportive and competitive. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. Nishanth Varma had seen the matches and said that the badminton training academies should play a key role in developing new players. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, the state Badminton association team and Physical education team of SRKR took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113018_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113018_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113018_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113018_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2022-10-13 06:00:18'),
(246, '2022-09-25', NULL, 'State Level U-13 Badminton Championship Valedictory at SRKR', 'The valedictory championship of State Level U-13 Badminton Championship had happened at SRKR and ASP Sri. Subbaraju attended the same as the Chief Guest. He distributed the prizes to the winners and said that it is only with sports that students can march ahead in life with confidence and values. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR, Sri. Nishanth Varma had said that SRKR is hosting this event every year. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, State Badminton Association Members, Physical Education Department Members and players took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113344_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113344_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>\r\n', '', 'PE', '2022-10-13 06:03:44'),
(247, '2022-09-26', NULL, 'EEE Department Faculty at SRKR Received PhD ', 'Assistant Professor of EEE Mr. Veeranna had received his Ph.D. from JNTUK Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju said. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR, Sri. Nishanth Varma had felicitated him on this occasion. Dr. Veeranna had thanked his guides, management of SRKR and EEE Dept faculty for their continuous support and motivation.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113529_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113529_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113529_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113529_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113529_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113529_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013113529_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013113529_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2022-10-13 06:05:29'),
(248, '2022-09-27', NULL, 'Valedictory of DST Workshop Held at SRKR', 'The Workshop which was being conducted for the last few days at SRKR in association with GITAM University had concluded and the recipients were awarded with their certificates. GITAM University Professor Dr. Srinivasa Prasad had said that research plays a key role on engineering education and all the faculty members should constantly pursue the same. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Technology Centre Head, Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy, HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Dr. Brahma Raju, Dr. Varma, Dr. Prasad, Dean Dr. PARK Raju and other dignitaries attended this function.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114037_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114037_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114037_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114037_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114037_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114037_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'TC', '2022-10-13 06:10:37'),
(249, '2022-10-11', NULL, 'Workshop on LED Lights by Women Empowerment Cell and ECE Department', 'Women Empowerment Cell in collaboration with ECE Department had conducted a workshop on \'LED Lightening\'. Plastic Omenium Lightening Technical Specialist and Alumni of SRKR Mr. Tejaswi Challa had attended the same as the chief Guest. Speaking on this occasion he said that, Research is under process on the problems that are arising when the temperature of the LED Lights is high. He shared his experiences with the electronics students. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. BHVN Lakshmi presided over this function. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that it is a matter of great pride that the prominent alumni of the college are visiting the campus and sharing their experiences with the students. The management had felicitated Mr. Tejaswi in a grand manner. HOD of ECE, Dr. Uday Kumar, Women Empowerment Cell Co-Coordinators Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. Hemalakshmi, Mrs. Phatima, Mrs. Bharathi took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114618_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114618_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114618_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114618_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114618_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114618_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221013114618_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221013114618_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EC', '2022-10-13 06:16:18'),
(250, '2022-10-15', NULL, 'Orientation Programme on Academic Project and Research Paper Writing', 'The Dept of CSE is conducting an Orientation Programme On Academic Project and Research Paper Writing for two days. The same has been inaugurated in the campus by Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Speaking on this occasion Principal had said that it is mandatory for the students to have training on academic projects and research paper writing under the new National Educational Policy. The students with this skill set will have more chances for their career upgrade. Faculty of CSE Dept and students took part in this occasion.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221015152839_1.37.44.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221015152839_1.37.44.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221015152839_2.37.44 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221015152839_2.37.44 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2022-10-15 09:58:39'),
(251, '2022-10-20', NULL, 'Blood Donation Camp at SRKR', 'The NSS Unit at SRKR Engg College had conducted a Blood Donation Camp where the Civil and Mechanical Engineering Students had donated the blood for a noble cause. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should inculcate the habit of donating the blood right from the childhood. Vice President of SRKR, Mr. SV Ranga Raju, College NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Dr. Brahma Raju, Dr. Varma, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, Dr. Prasad, Physical Education Department staff etc. took part in this programme. \r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111420_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111420_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111420_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111420_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111420_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111420_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111420_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111420_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111420_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111420_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-10-21 05:44:20'),
(252, '2022-10-19', NULL, 'Clean Challenge Drive by SRKR Students', 'The students of SRKR Engg College had conducted an Clean Challenge drive at Pedamiram Village under the college NSS Unit. Speaking on this occasion, Professor of Civil Engg Dr. Ganesh had said that students should voluntarily come forward to serve in the villages. The students took part in an awareness campaign in the village.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221021111608_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221021111608_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-10-21 05:46:08'),
(253, '2022-10-21', NULL, 'IIT Former Director Visits SRKREC', 'Former Director of IIT Delhi, Dr. VS Raju had visited SRKR and the Idea Lab that was constituted newly in collaboration with AICTE. Speaking on this occasion, he said that the faculty should develop good relation with the students and develop them intellectually. He said that India is slowly emerging as a champion in the fields of science and technology in the entire world. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had detailed the contributions of Dr. Raju to the eminent academic institutions across the country. The management of SRKR had felicitated Dr. Raju in a grand manner. Vice President of SRKR Dr. SV Ranga Raju and other faculty took part in this occasion. \r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221022102005_1.07.16.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221022102005_1.07.16.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-10-22 04:50:05'),
(254, '2022-11-14', NULL, 'Jyothirlingarchana at SRKR Engineering College', 'On the eve of \'Karthika Somavaram\' the management, staff and students of SRKR Engg College had conducted \'Karthika Deeparadhana\' in the college premises in a devotional manner. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Engg College, Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Vice-President Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju along with staff and students had participated in this event in large numbers. Speaking on this occasion Sri. Nishanth Varma had said that it is the tradition at SRKR to celebrate this event from the last 16 years. He wished the staff and students that their lives should be bright and success should fulfill their lives.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221115140139_1. 14th Nov Karteeka Deepostvam Ph2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221115140139_1. 14th Nov Karteeka Deepostvam Ph2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221115140139_2. 14th Nov Kartika Deepostvam Ph1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221115140139_2. 14th Nov Kartika Deepostvam Ph1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221115140139_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221115140139_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221115140139_4. 14th Nov Karteeka Deepostvam Ph3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221115140139_4. 14th Nov Karteeka Deepostvam Ph3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-15 08:31:39'),
(255, '2022-11-18', NULL, 'District Level Yuvajanotsav Conducted at SRKREC', 'District Level \'Yuvajanotsav\' by AP Govt was being held in a gradient manner at SRKR Engg College. Chief Guest of this occasion RDO Sri. Dasi Raju had said that these events play a major role in bringing out the hidden talents of the students. These events act as a stress buster for the students who are busy in their academics. Through these events students can come to know about various cultures and traditions of the country. CEO of Youth Services Mr. Mohan raj had said that the winners in these events will attend the selections at Guntur and the winners there will participate in the National Youth Day Celebrations on January 12th, 2023. Tahsildar Mr. Ravikumar, SRKR Vice President Mr. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. Jagapathi Raju, Vice-Principal Dr. K. Brahma Raju graced this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221119104541_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221119104541_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221119104541_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221119104541_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221119104541_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221119104541_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-19 05:15:41'),
(256, '2022-11-21', NULL, 'Awareness Session on Millets', 'An awareness session was organized on \'Millets Nutrition & Health\' at SRKR Engg College on 20th Nov, 2022. Speaking on this occasion International Food Expert Dr. Khader Vali had said that Millets farming is going to increase in the coming days. He said that Millets will gain prominence in the coming days due to its nutrition value and health benefits. He was grandly felicitated by the college management. Mr. Millet Rambabu, Organic Farming Heart Trust Founder MS. Subramanyam Raju, Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dr. BHVN Lakshmi took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122141824_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122141824_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122141824_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122141824_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122141824_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122141824_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122141824_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122141824_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122141824_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122141824_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-22 08:48:24'),
(257, '2022-11-21', NULL, 'Workshop on Strategic Planning for Water Resources and Implementation of Noble Bio Technical Treatment and Good Practice', 'The WET Centre at SRKR Engineering College is set to host a Workshop on the above topic on 23rd Nov, 2022 with the scientists from European Union and IIT\'s. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Principal Investigator Dr. PA Ramakrishnam Raju had said that SPRING Project was being used in SRKR in collaboration with prominent IITs in India and countries like Norway, Finland, Portugal and Hungary. They have disclosed the list of prominent scientists and professors attending the workshop.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122142313_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122142313_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122142313_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122142313_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122142313_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122142313_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221122142313_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221122142313_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-22 08:53:13'),
(258, '2022-11-22', NULL, 'Exhibition of Women Development Post Independence', 'The NSS Unit at SRKR Engineering College on the occasion of Azaadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav had held an exhibition on the above topic in which students from all the branches have participated enthusiastically. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Women have shown their impact in all the sectors post-independence and stood as a role model for others. He quoted the examples of former PM Indira Gandhi, present Finance Minister Smt. Nirmala Seetha Raman, Sania Mirza, Mithali Raj and many industrialists in the pharmacy sector as well. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju had praised the women community for their growth in the male dominated society. In charge CSE HOD Dr. Mahesh. Dr. Sirisha, NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya and other faculty members participated in this exhibition. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221124111816_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221124111816_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221124111816_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221124111816_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221124111816_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221124111816_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-24 05:48:16'),
(259, '2022-11-22', NULL, 'SRKR Students Shine in IBM Hack Challenge 2022', 'The students of SRKR have shined in the \'HACK Challenge 2022\' conducted by IBM at the National Level and brought glory to the institution. Revealing the details of the same, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that 1321 Institutions and 20500 students across the country participated in this event and 331 teams were shortlisted out of which 9 best teams were awarded by the Jury Members. One among the 9 teams was from SRKR in which 3rd Year IT students Sakshith, Varshini and Joharika have developed a Digital Payment Book for the convenience of the small and petty firms. The students were being congratulated by the management of the college. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, IT HOD Dr. Ramakrishnam Raju, Placements Dean Dr. Satyanarayana, Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopala Krishna Murthy were present in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126004809_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126004809_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126004809_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126004809_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126004809_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126004809_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126004809_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126004809_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'IT', '2022-11-25 19:18:09'),
(260, '2022-11-24', NULL, 'Spring Workshop at SRKR', 'The WET Center at SRKR had organized a workshop on \'Strategic Planning for Water Resources, Implementation of Biotechnological Practices (SPRING)\' with the eminent scientists from European Union and eminent IITs across the country. Speaking on this occasion, the scientists expressed that in order to provide pure water resources, village or town should be taken as a single unit. He said that it is the duty of everyone to make sure that the globe is pollution free. SPRING project is expected to be complete by coming year. The scientists were briefed about the water resources particulars by BJP Leader Mr. Paka Satyanarayana. Principal Investigator Dr. PA Ramakrishnam Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and other eminent academicians took part in this workshop. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126011322_1. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126011322_1. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126011322_2. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126011322_2. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126011322_3. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126011322_3. 23rd Nov SPRING Ph3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126011322_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126011322_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126011322_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126011322_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'TC', '2022-11-25 19:43:22'),
(261, '2022-11-25', NULL, 'Workshop on \'Women Harassment-Preventive Measures\'', 'The Women Empowerment Cell at SRKR Engg College had conducted a Workshop on \'Women Harassment-Preventive Measures\'. Speaking on this occasion Senior Advocate Mrs. N. Satyavignana Devi had said that strict laws and punishments should be awarded to the people involved in women harassment. Inspite of having many stringent laws the attacks on women are still on a raise. She said that it√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s the duty of the parents to raise their children with utmost discipline and then only we can put an end to these incidents. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should not divert their interest towards unwanted incidents and should focus only on their high goals and dreams. The guest was being felicitated by the management very grandly. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Women Empowerment Cell In-Charge Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. Lakshmi, Dr. Aparna, Mrs. Sasikala took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126135524_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126135524_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126135524_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126135524_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126135524_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126135524_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221126135524_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221126135524_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-26 08:25:24'),
(262, '2022-11-26', NULL, 'Constitution Day Celebrations', '\r\nThe Constitution Day Celebrations were held in a grand manner at SRKR Engineering College. Speaking on this occasion, Political Science Retired Lecturer Mr. SNV Satyanarayana had said that Indian Constitution is the role model for the whole world, however it should be revised at regular intervals in order to derive maximum benefits. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Indian Constitution is a holy book for the whole Indians. HOD of Mathematics&Humanities Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju, Civil In-Charge HOD Dr. Lavkumar, NSS Coordinators Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, KNV Satyanarayana took part in this occasion. \r\n\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221128183200_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221128183200_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221128183200_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221128183200_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-28 13:02:00'),
(263, '2022-11-28', NULL, 'Workshop on Prevention of Violence Against Women', 'The Women Empowerment Cell at SRKR Engg College had organized a Workshop on the above topic. Speaking on this occasion Telugu Language Moment President G. Sridevi had said that the violence against women is due to non-following of our traditions and culture by the present generation people. SRKR Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Dr. BHVN Lakshmi, Dr. Hyma Lakshmi, Dr. Aparna took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130175157_1.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130175157_1.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130175157_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130175157_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-30 12:21:57'),
(264, '2022-11-29', NULL, 'Student  Project Expo Anusandhan', 'The Dept of Chemistry at SRKR Engg College had organised a student expo on integrating science and Technology named as \'ANUSANDHAN\'. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students can hone their creative skills by such exhibitions. He said that it is really good to know that students have displayed models on AI within 2 to 3 days by developing on their own. HOD of Chemistry Dr. P. Bhavani had said that students have displayed over 100 models. Best models were recognised and honoured with certificates. HOD of Physics, Dr. Ramana Murthy, Dr. Diwakar, Mr. Chandrasekhar, Mr. Kishore, Mr. Nagababu took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130180136_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130180136_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130180136_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130180136_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130180136_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130180136_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221130180136_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221130180136_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-11-30 12:31:36'),
(265, '2022-12-03', NULL, 'Foreign Languages and Communication Skills Lab Inaugurated', 'Under the aegis of English Dept \'Foreign Languages and Communication Skills Lab\' was being inaugurated by the President of SRKR Sri. S. Prasada Raju. Speaking on this occasion, he said that English Language plays a very major role in moulding the students at the international levels. He said that SRKR always emphasizes on providing state of the art infrastructure for the development of its students. In order to develop ideas into reality, IDEA LAB is also being implemented at SRKR with major funding. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR, Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had said that students should try to acquire skills in sports and foreign languages too, other than the academics. This lab would be useful to students for acquiring foreign language skills. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Governing Body Member Mr. Satya Pratik Varma, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Foreign Language In charge Dr. BHVN Lakshmi took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221205113234_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221205113234_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221205113234_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221205113234_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221205113234_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221205113234_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221205113234_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221205113234_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-05 06:02:34'),
(266, '2022-12-05', NULL, 'Awareness Session On Traffic Rules', 'Traffic Police of Bhimavaram Town had conducted an awareness session to the students of SRKR\r\nEngg College on Traffic Rules. Speaking on this occasion, Chief Guest and DSP of Bhimavaram\r\nDivision Mr. Srinadh had said that the bike riders should compulsorily have driving licences. The\r\ntraffic Dept had been organising such sessions at various colleges to create awareness and provide\r\nLLR to the students who doesn√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t have driving licences until now. The bike riders should remember\r\ntheir family when they are driving the vehicles and should act responsibly. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M.\r\nJagapathi Raju had said that students should not drive vehicles without proper licences and\r\napplauded the efforts of the traffic department. Traffic CI Mr. G. Das, faculty Dr. Krishna Chaitanya,\r\nMr. Satyanarayana took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206182410_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206182410_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-06 12:54:10'),
(267, '2022-12-05', NULL, 'Save Soil Celebrations', 'SRKR Engineering College in collaboration with Bhimavaram Hospitals and Eesha Foundation had conducted an awareness rally on \'Save Soil\'. Speaking on this occasion MD of Bhimavaram Hospitals and Prominent Doctor Dr. Gopala Raju had said that because of the increasing pollution the nutrients in earth are degrading day by day. Everyone should collectively take up the responsibility of the protecting the earth. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the college is making every Saturday as green day and vehicles are prohibited inside the campus. Measures are being taken to eliminate the usage of plastic too inside the campus. Doctor Vijaya, and senior faculty took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221206183602_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221206183602_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-06 13:06:02'),
(268, '2022-12-06', NULL, 'SRKR Student Selected For Southzone Chess Championship', 'Two SRKR Students had been selected for South Zone Championship at Bangalore from 15 th\r\nDecember on behalf of JNTUK, Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Speaking on this\r\noccasion, Physical Director Dr. P. Satyanarayana Raju had said that CSE II Year Student\r\nMs. Y. Yamuna Kumari and IT Final Year Student Ms. K. Kamala were selected in the championship\r\nthat was conducted last week at Gayatri Vidya Parishad, Visakhapatnam. The students were being\r\ncongratulated by Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and the\r\nteam of Physical Department.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221207160338_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221207160338_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221207160338_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221207160338_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221207160338_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221207160338_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2022-12-07 10:33:38'),
(269, '2022-12-08', NULL, 'Induction Session To Students Of I B. Tech On Joy  Of Engineering ', '\r\nAn induction session to students of I B. Tech was being conducted at SRKR College titled \'Joy of Engineering\' by prominent personality development trainer and Director Academic Planning at JNTUK, Dr. Murali Krishna. Speaking on this occasion he said that students should implement what they learn with good values and then they can shine in their lives. He said that students should not face any tensions and should carry on their studies with fresh and calm mind. He appreciated the students who had participated with great enthusiasm in the programme. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had presided over this session. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of Mathematics & Humanities, Dr. Venkatapathi Raju, HOD of Chemistry Dr. Bhavani and other faculty took part in this session. \r\n\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221209095308_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221209095308_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221209095308_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221209095308_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221209095308_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221209095308_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-09 04:23:08'),
(270, '2022-12-17', NULL, 'Felicitation To The President Of SRKR', 'The Non-Teaching Staff Union at SRKR had felicitated the President of SRKR Sri. S. Prasada Raju in the campus. Speaking on this occasion, he said that SRKR gained fame in the International arena due to the support and cooperation of the teaching and non-teaching staff. He said that even in times of pandemic, students of SRKR succeeded in getting good placements and had won many accolades in the national level. Governing Body Members, Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and the Non-Teaching Staff union representatives took part in this occasion. \r\n\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221219182914_1.30.40.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221219182914_1.30.40.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221219182914_2.34.26.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221219182914_2.34.26.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221219182914_3.34.27.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221219182914_3.34.27.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221219182914_4.47.35.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221219182914_4.47.35.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-19 12:59:14'),
(271, '2022-12-27', NULL, 'SRKR GETS NAAC A+', 'SRKR Engineering College is accredited by NAAC with A+ Grade, Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma had told the reporters at a meeting organised in the college on 26th Dec, 2022. The management celebrated this commendable achievement by cutting the cake and thanking all the stakeholders. SRKR had been awarded 3.42 CGPA and stood among the top colleges in the state of Andhra Pradesh. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that NAAC Committee members had visited the college on Dec 15th and 16th and examined the facilities and infrastructure of the college. HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s and Deans took part in this success celebrations.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221227180021_1.00.48.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221227180021_1.00.48.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221227180021_2.00.49 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221227180021_2.00.49 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221227180021_3.00.49.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221227180021_3.00.49.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221227180021_4.00.53.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221227180021_4.00.53.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221227180021_5.14.53.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221227180021_5.14.53.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-27 12:30:21'),
(272, '2022-12-28', NULL, 'FELICITATION TO PRINCIPAL AND LEADERSHIP TEAM BY LIONS CLUB', '\r\nThe Lions Club of Bhimavaram had felicitated the Principal, HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s and Deans on 27th December 2022 for getting NAAC A+ accreditation. Speaking on this occasion President of Lions Club, Mr. K. Venkataraju had said that the entire Bhimavaram city and District of West Godavari is proud of SRKR and its achievements. Social Service activist, Mr. Rangasai had said that this achievement is only possible with the collective effort of all the departments and staff of the organisation. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the cooperation of the management is very vital in getting this accreditation and SRKR is marching ahead in the direction set by founder Dr. Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju, President Mr. S. Prasada Raju, Secretary&Correspondent Mr. SRK Nishanth Varma and other management members. Representatives of the Lions Club, HOD√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s and Deans took part in this occasion. \r\n\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228180015_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228180015_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228180015_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228180015_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228180015_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228180015_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228180015_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228180015_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228180015_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228180015_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-28 12:30:15'),
(273, '2022-12-28', NULL, 'TALENT EXAMINATION BY EENADU', 'Most Circulated Telugu Newspaper \'Eenadu\' had conducted talent examination to the students of SRKR on 27th December 2022, in order to bring out the inner potential of the students. Students of various branches took part in this examination and the students with highest marks were being awarded by Vice President of SRKR, Mr. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and HOD of CSE, Dr. Chandrasekhar. B. Tech final year students Ms. Sarvani, Mr. Saikrishna, Mr. Abhishek and Mr. P. Abhishek stood as the top four in these examinations. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20221228181434_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20221228181434_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2022-12-28 12:44:34'),
(274, '2023-01-01', NULL, 'Coaching Camp For Women University Basketball Team at SRKR', 'The coaching camp for University Women Basketball team is being conducted at SRKR. This team is going to represent JNTUK at South zone inter university Basketball Tournament from Jan 4 th to 8 th at Madras University, Chennai. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had visited the camp and wished the students all the best. He said that students should progress in sports as well as academics. In charge PD Dr. Harimohan had said that 12 students from institutions under the purview of JNTUK are being trained here at SRKR. The team is going to Chennai in the supervision of Assistant PD Ms. G. Sarika of SRKR.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230102134359_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230102134359_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230102134359_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230102134359_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230102134359_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230102134359_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-01-02 08:13:59'),
(275, '2023-01-02', NULL, 'SRKR PRINCIPAL WISHES ALL A VERY HAPPY NEW YEAR 2023', 'Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had wished all the staff and students of SRKR on the\r\noccasion of New Year. Various staff members had met him and wished him on this occasion. He said that Collaborative effort only brings good results and so everyone should work with unity in the path of progress. There were some extremely important achievements that the college had got last year and this year too they must be replicated with more efforts. He said that the management is ready to go to extra mile for the benefit of the institution, staff and students. The staff had met and wished the Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju garu too.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230102134841_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230102134841_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-02 08:18:41'),
(276, '2023-01-04', NULL, 'Savitribhai Phule Services Remebered', 'The services of Savitribhai Phule and National Women Faculty Day was celebrated in a grand manner\r\nat SRKR Engg College by the Women Empowerment Cell. Andhra University Computer Science Dept\r\nSenior Professor Dr. Valli Kumari attended the session as chief guest and addressed the faculty. She\r\nsaid that Phule had rendered the services when there are no infrastructure and this generation\r\nfaculty should treat her as a role model. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had appreciated the\r\nwomen empowerment cell for conducting this session and had remembered the services rendered\r\nby Phule. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Women Empowerment Cell Coordinators and\r\nother faculty took part in this session.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230104180029_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230104180029_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230104180029_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230104180029_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-04 12:30:29'),
(277, '2023-01-04', NULL, 'BasketBall Coaching Camp Concluded', 'The coaching camp of JNTUK Women Basketball team players was concluded in the SRKR college on\r\n3 rd Jan, 2023. Speaking on this occasion, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju wished the players\r\nall the best and hoped that they would win accolades in the competitions. Suits were distributed to\r\nthe players. PD Dr. Satyanarayana Raju, Assistant PDs Dr. Harimohan, Ms. Sarika and Mr. Avinash\r\ntook part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230104180610_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230104180610_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230104180610_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230104180610_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-01-04 12:36:10');
