(278, '2023-01-06', NULL, 'Awareness Session On \'Ayurveda\'', 'An awareness session on \'Ayurveda\' was being conducted at SRKR Engg College under the Ayushman\r\nBharat Scheme. Prominent ayurvedic scientist D. Subbaraju had visited the ayurvedic garden in the\r\ncampus and said that nearly 200 different varieties of species are available in the garden. He said\r\nthat the college management should explore the chances of setting up an ayurvedic institute too for\r\nthe benefit of the people. He said that Ayurveda is the gift of our ancestors for this generation.\r\nAyurvedic medicines will not have any side effects as compared to English medicines and so\r\neveryone should start using Ayurveda for the healthy life. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju\r\nhad said that he will deliberate with the management on starting the Ayurveda institute or course as\r\nsuggested by the guest. Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Dean R&amp; D Dr. PARK Raju, HOD of EM&amp; H Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju, NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya etc took part in this session.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230106180840_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230106180840_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230106180840_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230106180840_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230106180840_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230106180840_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-06 12:38:40'),
(279, '2023-01-09', NULL, 'National Level Hackathon And Bootcamp', 'IT Dept of SRKR Engg College is conducting National Level Boot Camp and 24 Hours Hackathon starting from Feb 6 th , Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus by Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Programme Coordinator and HOD of IT Dept Dr. BHVS Ramakrishnam Raju had said that this programme is organized in technical collaboration with Brain O Vision of Hyderabad. Dr. Hemalatha, Dr. Kishore Raju,  B.Teja Sri, Saibaba, Satya Varma took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230109140853_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230109140853_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230109140853_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230109140853_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230109140853_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230109140853_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'IT', '2023-01-09 08:38:54'),
(280, '2023-01-09', NULL, 'AICTE EDUSKILLS 33rd RANK TO SRKR ', 'SRKR gets 33 rd Rank at National Level in AICTE EDUSKILLS Virtual Internship program. The details regarding the same were disclosed by Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Dean Placements Dr. Satyanarayana. AICTE EDUSKILLS had created virtual internship opportunities to the students on latest technologies at PAN India Level. Under this programme students completed their internships and top 50 colleges were recognized at the national level. It is a matter of great pride that SRKR stood at 33 rd Rank in the national level. The certificate relating to the same was handed over to Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju by Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230109142017_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230109142017_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230109142017_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230109142017_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-09 08:50:17'),
(281, '2023-01-10', NULL, 'SRKR Shine In Toastmasters Club', 'The students of SRKR had brought accolades by participating in various competitions in Toastmasters Club at the National Level and improved their proficiency and expression of thoughts, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Third Year Mechanical student Mr. Dilip Rohit had got first prize in Humorous Speech and Third Year CSBS student Mr. Sravan Kumar had got third prize. The mementoes given by International Toastmasters Club for these students were being handed over to them by Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Coordinator of Toastmasters Club Dr. Lakshmi.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230111141327_1.43.01.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230111141327_1.43.01.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230111141327_2.44.03.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230111141327_2.44.03.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-11 08:43:27'),
(282, '2023-01-11', NULL, 'SRKR Placement Officer Recieves Innovative Leader Award', 'The Maharashtra Training and Placement Cell Officers Association had awarded Innovative Leader award to SRKR Placement Officer Dr. Satyanarayana, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was felicitated in the campus by Principal and Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Speaking on this occasion Dr. Satyanarayana had said that the top 20 placement officers across the country are awarded and SRKR was the only one to receive from the state of Andhra Pradesh. He thanked the efforts of the college management which had played a key role in securing the highest number of placements for the students of SRKR. Dr. Satyanarayana was congratulated by HODs, Deans and Faculty of the institution.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230111141849_1.24.44.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230111141849_1.24.44.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230111141849_2.37.55.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230111141849_2.37.55.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-11 08:48:49'),
(283, '2023-01-12', NULL, 'Young Research  Award to SRKR Professor', 'Civil Engineering Assistant Professor Mr. Vamsi Nagaraju had received Young Researcher Award from  the STEM Institute, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He congratulated Mr. Nagaraju for this achievement and wished him all the best for the future. He said that every year Himachal Pradesh University in association with STEM will select one as the young researcher across the country. Earlier Mr. Nagaraju had received Geo technical award too.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118173316_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118173316_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118173316_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118173316_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118173316_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118173316_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118173316_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118173316_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-18 12:03:16'),
(284, '2023-01-13', NULL, 'SRKR Receives  Awards From Atal Incubation Center', 'Atal Incubation Centre at Sri Krishnadevaraya University, Anantpur is going to present awards to SRKR Engineering College for its efforts in promoting the start-up ecosystem, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Technology Centre head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy is being felicitated by the Principal on this occasion. Dr. Murthy had said that these awards are being presented for encouraging the start-up ecosystem and starting more start-ups in the campus. These awards are going to be presented at the university on 21 st January, 2023.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118174547_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118174547_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118174547_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118174547_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118174547_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118174547_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230118174547_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230118174547_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'TC', '2023-01-18 12:15:47'),
(285, '2023-01-18', NULL, 'Mathematics Department  Assistant Professor Recives  Ph.D', 'Mrs. G. Santhi, Assistant Professor in the Department of Mathematics at SRKR Engineering College\r\nhad received her Ph.D. from Andhra University in the field of Applied Mathematics, Principal Dr. M.\r\nJagapathi Raju had said. She was felicitated in the college by the Vice President Mr. SV Ranga Raju,\r\nPrincipal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and HOD of Mathematics &amp; Humanities Dr. D. Venkatapathi Raju. She had completed her Ph.D. under the supervision of Dr. T. Lingaraju and Dr. CNB Rao. She was\r\ncongratulated by the staff of the college.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230120124001_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230120124001_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230120124001_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230120124001_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-20 07:10:01'),
(286, '2023-01-19', NULL, 'Conference  On ONDC', 'A conference on ONDC was being held at the technology centre of SRKR in collaboration with\r\nBangalore based E-Samuday and Bhimavaram Online. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR\r\nDr. Jagapathi Raju had said that even small business people can also enter into online phase and\r\nSRKR is ready to help them in growing their business in online mode. He said that Govt is giving more\r\nprominence to online businesses and ONDC (Open Network for Digital Commerce) is playing a very\r\nprominent role in this. E- Samuday network Head Mr. Raghavendra had said that their portal is\r\nlinked with ONDC and so, the businesses in online can be done with more ease. Bhimavaram Online\r\nDirector Dr. Suresh Babu had said that SRKR had started online services in the year 2018 and is\r\nmarching ahead. Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy and E-Samuday representative\r\nMr. Krishna took part in this conference.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230120124712_1.06.25.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230120124712_1.06.25.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230120124712_2.06.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230120124712_2.06.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230120124712_3.07.05.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230120124712_3.07.05.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-20 07:17:12'),
(287, '2023-01-20', NULL, 'EEE Department Assistant Professor Recived Ph.D', 'Mr. Gorla Pavan Kumar, Assistant Professor in the Department of EEE had received his PhD from\r\nAndhra University, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He had done his research on\r\nSolar Power and Wind Energy under the guidance of Dr. Srinu Nayak, Professor in EEE at Andhra\r\nUniversity. He was being felicitated by the Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju and Principal\r\nand wished him all the best for the future. The staff of the college had congratulated him on his\r\nachievement.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125123835_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125123835_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125123835_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125123835_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125123835_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125123835_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125123835_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125123835_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-01-25 07:08:35'),
(288, '2023-01-21', NULL, 'Assistant Professor Of Mathematics Department  Recevied Ph.D', 'Assistant Professor in the Department of Mathematics Mr. Kasibotla Satya Srinivasa Babu had\r\nreceived his doctorate from JNTU, Anantpur in the field of Applied Mathematics, Principal of SRKR\r\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was being felicitated in the campus by Vice President of SRKR Sri.\r\nSV Ranga Raju, Principal and HOD of Mathematics &amp; Humanities Dr. Venkatapathi Raju. He has\r\ncompleted his research under the guidance of Dr. A. Parandhama of Sri Vidyaniketan, Tirupati and\r\nProf. R. Bhuvanavijaya of JNTU, Anantpur. He was congratulated by the staff of the college.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124543_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124543_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124543_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124543_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124543_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124543_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-25 07:15:43'),
(289, '2023-01-23', NULL, 'EEE Department Assistant Professor Recieves Ph.D', 'Assistant Professor in the Dept of EEE, Mr. Gadiraju Harish Varma had received his Ph. D from NIT\r\nGoa, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was being felicitated in the campus by Vice\r\nPresident of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and HOD of EEE Dr. Varma. He\r\nhas done his research under the supervision of Dr. Venugopal Reddy from NIT Goa. He was being\r\ncongratulated by the staff of the college. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124931_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124931_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124931_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124931_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125124931_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125124931_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-01-25 07:19:31'),
(290, '2023-01-25', NULL, 'Awarness Programme On Road Safety', '34 th Road Safety Week Valedictory programme was held at SRKR auditorium on 24 th January, 2023.\r\nDistrict Collector Smt. P. Prasanthi attended the same as the chief guest. Speaking on this occasion\r\nshe said that everyone should abide by the traffic rules and have a safe journey. ASP Sri. Subbaraju\r\nand District Transport Officer Sri. Umamaheswara Rao had said that many programmes were being\r\norganised in order to bring awareness on road safety. Eye tests were being conducted for the drivers\r\nand spectacles were being distributed to them by the collector. SRKR Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Governing Body Member Sri. Pratik Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju took part in this programme.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125125752_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125125752_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125125752_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125125752_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125125752_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125125752_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125125752_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125125752_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125125752_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125125752_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-25 07:27:52'),
(291, '2023-01-25', NULL, 'Mega Health Camp By SRKR College', 'A mega health camp was being organised by the SRKR Engg College on 28 th January Morning in the\r\ncampus with the collaboration of Vijayawada based Akkineni Women√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Hospital. The brochure\r\nrelating to the same was inaugurated in the campus by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. He urged the women of SRKR Unnat Bharat Abhiyan adopted villages Pedda Amiram,\r\nKopalle, Kalla, Kallakuru and Jakkaram to make use of this health camp. CEO of Akkineni Women√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s\r\nHospital P. Srinivas had said that free medicines would be distributed to the needy in this health\r\ncamp. Governing Body Member Mr. Pratik Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dean R&amp;D Dr.\r\nPARK Raju etc. took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125130512_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125130512_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125130512_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125130512_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125130512_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125130512_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125130512_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125130512_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230125130512_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230125130512_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-01-25 07:35:12'),
(292, '2023-01-28', NULL, 'Mega Health Camp At SRKR', 'A mega health camp was being organised at SRKR Engg College by Women Empowerment Cell,\r\nUnnat Bharat Abhiyan and Akkineni Women√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Hospital of Vijayawada on 28 th Jan, 2023. Speaking on\r\nthis occasion, Founder of Akkineni Women√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Hospital Dr. Mani had said that their hospital is ready to\r\nextend any services for the wellbeing of the Women fraternity. She said that their hospital had\r\norganised several health camps across the state and treated thousands of patients. In this health\r\ncamp medical services are rendered to around 400 people and free medicines were distributed to\r\nthe needy. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, In-Charge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju, Dean R&amp;D\r\nDr. PARK Raju, Women Empowerment Cell InCharge Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Hospital CEO Mr. P.\r\nSrinivasa Rao etc. took part in this noble initiative.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207181630_1.58.23.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207181630_1.58.23.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207181630_2.58.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207181630_2.58.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207181630_3.11.09.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207181630_3.11.09.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-07 12:46:30'),
(293, '2023-02-01', NULL, 'Awareness Programme On General Medicine', 'An awareness programme on general medicine was being conducted in collaboration with the NSS\r\nUnit at SRKR Engg College on 31-01-23. Dr. Ganapathi Raju from Ingalls Memorial University of\r\nChicago Medical Centre Family Medicine MD from US has attended the same and addressed the\r\nstudents. He cautioned the students to avoid the habits of Smoking and Drinking through which the\r\nbody parts gets affected and the lives will be ruined. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said\r\nthat students should give equal importance to studies and health, through which they can make the\r\ndreams of their parents come true. Dr. Ganapathi Raju was being felicitated by the Vice President of\r\nSRKR, Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and NSS Co-Ordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya\r\nand NSS Co- Coordinator Mr. KNV Satyanarayana.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207182002_1.12.04.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207182002_1.12.04.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207182002_2.13.14.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207182002_2.13.14.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207182002_3.01.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207182002_3.01.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-07 12:50:02'),
(294, '2023-02-02', NULL, 'IIT Tirupathi Director Visits SRKR', 'IIT Tirupathi Director Dr. KN Satyanarayana had visited SRKR Engg College. He visited √¢‚Ç¨ÀúSRUJANA\r\nVATIKA√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ where he examined various food items that are made from millets and various items\r\nbelonging to the olden days and appreciated the initiative. He had then visited the IDEA Lab and\r\nexamined the resources. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had explained him about the various\r\ninitiatives that are taken up by the college. He had then interacted with the Deans and HODs of\r\nvarious departments and he suggested the team to make sure that holistic development of the\r\nstudents should take place. He was being felicitated grandly by the college administration.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207182229_1.02.58.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207182229_1.02.58.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-07 12:52:29'),
(295, '2023-02-02', NULL, 'Mechanical ', 'Mr. Akula Naresh who was working as the faculty in the research centre of Mechanical Department\r\nat SRKR Engg College had received doctorate from Andhra University, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju\r\nhad said. He had done his research on mixing Palmolein Oil with Diesel which will reduce the\r\npollution and increase the lifetime of the machine. He had done his research under the supervision\r\nof Mechanical HOD Dr. Brahma Raju and Andhra University Joint Research Director Dr. P. Srinivas\r\nKishore. He was being felicitated by the administration of the college.\r\n\r\nMechanical Dept HOD Dr. Brahma Raju was being felicitated by the Principal of the College for his\r\nnoble contribution as the Director of the Mechanical Research Centre. 12 students received their\r\ndoctorates from the research centre since 2014.\r\n\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230207182856_1.02.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230207182856_1.02.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'ME', '2023-02-07 12:58:56'),
(296, '2023-02-06', NULL, 'Inauguration of Bootcamp And  Hackthon', 'The Dept of IT is conducting Bootcamp and 24 Hours Hackathon and the same was inaugurated on 5 th Feb by CEO of Brain O Vision Mr. D. Ganesh Nag. Speaking on this occasion he said that through human brain and intellectual skills alone we can acquire knowledge. IT Dept HOD Dr. BHVS Ramakrishnam Raju and Incharge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju had said that Data Science relevance was there in all the fields and so students should focus more on it. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, Programme Coordinators Dr. Hemalatha, Dr. Kishore took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216141713_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216141713_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'IT', '2023-02-16 08:47:13'),
(297, '2023-02-10', NULL, 'Blood  Donation Camp On 40th Remembrance Day Of Sagi Ramakrishnam Raju', 'A blood donation camp was being organised at SRKR on the 40 th remembrance day of Sri.Sagi\r\nRamakrishnam Raju garu, chief donor of SRKR Engg College. Faculty of CSE Dept Dr. K. Aruna Kumari had donated blood 5 times until now and she was appreciated for her noble task. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and NSS Team took part in this activity.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_4.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_4.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216142451_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216142451_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-16 08:54:51'),
(298, '2023-02-12', NULL, 'Inauguration Of AICTE Idea Lab And 43rd Annual Day  Celebrations', 'AICTE IDEA LAB and 43 rd Annual Day Celebrations of SRKR Engg College were inaugurated by Former Vice President of India Sri. M. Venkiah Naidu Garu. Speaking on this occasion he said that research towards promoting new infrastructure in rural areas should be promoted. He visited and appreciated SRUJANA VATIKA a centre of our heritage and traditions. President of SRKR Sri. SD. Prasad Raju and Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma stressed the need of traditions and culture in student√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s life and urged the students to make use of the IDEA LAB. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had presented a brief report of various accomplishments of SRKR Engg College in the academic year. Sri. Venkiah Naidu Garu was felicitated grandly by the management and governing body members of the college. Members of the Management, Governing Body, Parents, Faculty and students were present at this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216143224_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216143224_8.jpg\" class=\"i