(301, '2023-02-15', NULL, 'EEE Dept  Faculty Received Ph.D.', 'Assistant Professor in the Dept of EEE Mr. Mujib Khan Pathan had received his doctorate from Anna University, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was felicitated by Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma Secretary &amp; Correspondent of the college. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of EEE Dr. Varma took part in this event. Mr. Khan was being congratulated by the faculty of the college.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145100_1.54.10 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145100_1.54.10 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145100_2.56.19 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145100_2.56.19 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145100_3.56.21.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145100_3.56.21.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-02-16 09:21:00'),
(302, '2023-02-15', NULL, 'Mathematics Faculty  Receives  Ph.D.', 'Assistant Professor in the Department of Mathematics &amp; Humanities Mr. Nalla Veeraju had received his doctorate from Krishna University, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was being felicitated by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Speaking on this occasion Principal had said that it was the teacher√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s duty to make sure that the students are responsible and are of human values. He suggested all the young faculty to complete their Ph. D. at the earliest. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of EM&amp;H Dept Dr. Venkatapathi Raju took part in this event. Mr. Veeraju was congratulated by all the staff members of the institution.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145857_1.05.51.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145857_1.05.51.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145857_2.05.51 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145857_2.05.51 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230216145857_3.05.52.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230216145857_3.05.52.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-16 09:28:57'),
(303, '2023-02-17', NULL, 'Student Develop E-Commerce APP', 'Students of SRKR had developed an online food delivery app named as √¢‚Ç¨ÀúBhimavaram Online√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. The\r\nstall of the same was being set up at the girl√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s hostel of SRKR and was inaugurated by the secretary\r\nand Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. He appreciated the student√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s efforts in\r\ndeveloping a novel app. Speaking on this occasion Stall Coordinator, CSD Students Ms. Saranya had\r\nsaid that food items, biryani, sweets and other items that are made by the home makers at their\r\nrespective homes will be delivered through this app to the customers without any service charges.\r\nThis option would be there for the customers who book online only. Even stationery items for the\r\nstudents are also available through this app. Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Dr. Gopalakrishna\r\nMurthy, Dr. Suresh, Dr. C Ramakrishnam Raju took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230220150547_1.54.15.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230220150547_1.54.15.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230220150547_2.54.16.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230220150547_2.54.16.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CD', '2023-02-20 09:35:47'),
(304, '2023-02-17', NULL, 'SRKR INKS MOU With  DRIVEDOCK', 'SRKR Engg College had entered into an MOU with DRIVEDOCK, a start-up that was initiated by the\r\nalumni of SRKR Mechanical Engg Dept Mr. Deepu Saladi. The documents relating to the same were\r\nexchanged by Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Company representative Mr. S. Sudhakara Raju.\r\nSpeaking on this occasion, HOD of ME Dr. Brahma Raju had said that Deepu used to be very active in\r\nAutomotive Club and though he was working in Germany, he started his start-up at Mallikipuram\r\nand now the second branch at SRKR. In this branch, repair of batteries, recycling of dry batteries and\r\nmanufacturing of Go-Karts will take place. Mechanical students will also be provided with\r\ninternships. Technology Centre Head Dr. N. Gopalakrishna Murthy, Drive Dock Sales Rep Ms. Lasya,\r\nMechanical Engg Dept Assistant Professor Mr. V. Muralikrishnam Raju took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230220151719_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230220151719_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230220151719_2.57.45 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230220151719_2.57.45 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230220151719_3.57.45.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230220151719_3.57.45.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'ME', '2023-02-20 09:47:19'),
(305, '2023-02-22', NULL, 'Workshop On \'AIMS & Objective Of UBA\'', 'A workshop was conducted on √¢‚Ç¨ÀúAims &amp; Objectives of UBA√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ at SRKR College for the districts of Eluru\r\nand West Godavari where around coordinators from 30 colleges had participated. UBA Coordinator\r\nof Andhra University B. Pavani had graced this occasion. She said that students should use their\r\nintellectual capabilities and make sure that rural places are developed on par with the urban places.\r\nEvery college should adopt 5 villages and make sure that water, cleanliness and elimination of plastic\r\ntakes place. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that SRKR had adopted 5 villages and is\r\nmaking sure that the developmental activities in that villages are happening well. Certificates had\r\nbeen distributed to the coordinators of various colleges. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju,\r\nUBA Coordinator Dr. PARK Raju, R. Subbarao, V. Ramaraju, T. Rambabu took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224160604_1.46.31.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224160604_1.46.31.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224160604_2.46.52.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224160604_2.46.52.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-24 10:36:04'),
(306, '2023-02-23', NULL, 'Workshop On Emerging Technologies', 'A workshop on emerging technologies was conducted at SRKR by Dr. Prabhakar Rao, Visiting\r\nScientist at IISC, Centre for Nano Science and Engineering. He said that because of the Ukraine war\r\nelectronics industry was facing lot of struggle as Ukraine was the chief supplier of microchips in the\r\nworld. Entire world was trying to make microchips and US is the forerunner in this race and India is\r\ngiving lots of incentives for the manufacturing of microchips. Hence he suggested that all the IITs\r\nshould encourage research on microchips. Principal Dr. Ma. Jagapathi Raju had said that in the new\r\neducation policy, students should not get limited to books and should always make sure that they\r\nare aware on the latest emerging technologies. Dr. Prabhakar Rao was grandly felicitated by the\r\nmanagement of the college. HOD of ECE Dr. Uday Kumar was present on this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224161227_1.23.37.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224161227_1.23.37.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-24 10:42:27'),
(307, '2023-02-24', NULL, 'Awareness Session By SEB', 'An awareness session was conducted by SEB at SRKR on the critical effects of usage of drugs.\r\nSpeaking on this occasion District ASP (SEB) Sri. ATV Ravi Kumar said that it was the duty of the\r\nyouth to make the state drug free and the role of the youth should be responsible. It is through\r\ndrugs that we spoil our own lives and hence youth should bring to the notice of the officials if any of\r\ntheir friends have the habit of drugs. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, HOD of CSE Dr.\r\nChandrasekhar took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224161606_1.23.35.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224161606_1.23.35.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224161606_2.23.36 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224161606_2.23.36 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230224161606_3.23.36.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230224161606_3.23.36.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-02-24 10:46:06'),
(308, '2023-02-26', NULL, 'Inauguration Of Apoorva-23', 'National Level Workshop of EEE Dept √¢‚Ç¨ÀúAPOORVA-23√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ was inaugurated at SRKR Engg College. This\r\nworkshop is being held in collaboration with the alumni of the dept. DRDO Scientist and Alumni of\r\nSRKR Dr. BV Ravikumar had inaugurated the same. Speaking on this occasion, he said that India had\r\ndeveloped massively in the areas of science and technology and started exporting defence\r\nequipment√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s to foreign countries. 80% of the India√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s defence equipment were manufactured in India\r\nand this was due to √¢‚Ç¨ÀúMake In India√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ and √¢‚Ç¨ÀúAtmanirbhar Bharat√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. At the time of Covid DRDO developed\r\nD2G Drug which had showed abnormal results and saved the lives of many people. He advised the\r\nstudents to give importance to core groups and do intensive research in those areas. He had\r\nreleased the souvenir of the EEE Dept. He was being felicitated by the Vice President of SRKR, Sri. SV\r\nRanga Raju, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. HOD of EEE Dr. Varma, Alumni Association Coordinator\r\nDr. VK. Viswanadha Raju, Dr. G. Harish Kumar Varma took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230227204610_7.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230227204610_7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-02-27 15:16:10'),
(309, '2023-02-28', NULL, 'PRAJNA-23 Exhibition At SRKR', 'The Dept of Mechanical Engg had conducted a science exhibition Prajna-23 on the occasion of\r\nscience day. This exhibition was inaugurated by Former Director of IIT Delhi Dr. VS Raju. Speaking on\r\nthis occasion he said that students can create wonders with not only Computers but also in the field\r\nof mechanical. Students these days are giving more importance to computers groups, but with the\r\nfields of Mechanical, Civil, EEE and ECE more accomplishments can be done. Mechanical students\r\nhad designed an motor cycle worth 25K and he appraised the students for the same. This exhibition\r\nwas being witnessed by the school students of Bhimavaram surrounding areas. Secretary and\r\nCorrespondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Vice President of\r\nSRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju and HOPD of Mechanical Dr. Brahma Raju took part in this event.\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302180807_1.16.31.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302180807_1.16.31.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302180807_2.16.34.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302180807_2.16.34.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302180807_3.17.57.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302180807_3.17.57.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302180807_4.17.58.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302180807_4.17.58.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302180807_5.17.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302180807_5.17.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'ME', '2023-03-02 12:38:07'),
(310, '2023-02-28', NULL, 'Panel Discussion On Reducing Traffic In Bhimavaram', 'A panel discussion was being held at SRKR Engg College with Principals of various colleges, police\r\nDept and other intellectuals of Bhimavaram on the ways to reduce the traffic in Bhimavaram.\r\nSpeaking on this occasion IIT Former Director Dr. VS Raju said that Educational Institutions, NSS, NCC\r\nshould play a major role in the reduction of traffic and stand as a role model for others. Sound and\r\nNoise pollution should be reduced and police posts should be erected at necessary places. ASP Sri.\r\nSubbaraju had said that they are creating awareness on usage of helmets and the usage rate is\r\nincreased by 15% than before. Traffic CI Das had said that No Horn Boards will be of more use at the\r\nplaces of importance. DST Scientist Dr. Prasad Raju had said that AICTE is giving prime importance to\r\ntraffic reduction and pollution free cities. Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth\r\nVarma, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Principal of SVECW Dr. G. Srinivasa Rao, Principal of\r\nDNR Dr. Anjan Kumar, Dean R&amp;D Dr. PARK Raju, experts of various fields took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_1.16.31 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_1.16.31 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_2.16.32 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_2.16.32 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_3.16.32.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_3.16.32.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_4.16.33.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_4.16.33.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_5.17.57 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_5.17.57 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302181518_6.17.58 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302181518_6.17.58 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-02 12:45:18'),
(311, '2023-03-02', NULL, 'New Startup By SRKR Students', 'The students of SRKR had started new start-ups. Students under the guidance of Dr. Suresh Babu\r\nhad started a start-up named as Caf√É¬© By SRKR and students under the guidance of Dr. Gopalakrishna\r\nMurthy and alumni of SRKR Mr. Rajsekhar had started a start-up for the blind people named as\r\n√¢‚Ç¨ÀúSmart Vision By SRKR√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. Both these start-ups were being awarded by NIT, Tadepalligudem recently.\r\nOn this occasion the students and mentors were felicitated by the Secretary and Correspondent of\r\nSRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. He said that students should not be job seekers and they should be\r\njob providers. Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the students of SRKR had proved\r\ntheir mettle in various hackathons held across the country. Technology Centre Head Dr.\r\nGopalakrishna Murthy and CSD HOD Dr. Suresh Babu took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302183037_1.45.06 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302183037_1.45.06 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302183037_2.45.06.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302183037_2.45.06.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302183037_3.17.56.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302183037_3.17.56.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CD', '2023-03-02 13:00:37'),
(312, '2023-03-01', NULL, 'SRKR Staff Wins Shuttle Tournament ', 'SRKR staff members Dr. Varma HOD of EEE and Dr. Kiran Kumar Varma Professor in Humanities Dept\r\nhad won first place in 45+ doubles at State Level College Teachers Shuttle Badminton Competitions\r\nheld at RVRJC Engg College, Guntur. The staff members were being felicitated by the Secretary and\r\nCorrespondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Dr. Kiran Kumar\r\nVarma had also won Best Player Award in this tournament.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302185104_1.45.07.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302185104_1.45.07.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230302185104_2.17.12.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230302185104_2.17.12.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-03-02 13:21:04'),
(313, '2023-03-03', NULL, 'Workshop On \'Development Of Application\'', 'The Dept of CSE is going to conduct a workshop on √¢‚Ç¨ÀúDevelopment of Applications√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ for 3 days starting\r\nfrom 18 th of March, 2023 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same\r\nwas inaugurated by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Overview of new\r\ntechnologies and development of applications will take place in this workshop. A 24 hackathon will\r\nalso be conducted on 23 rd march and students from various Engg colleges across the country had\r\nregistered for the same. HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar, Dr. Mahesh, Dr. Sirisha took part in this\r\nevent.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230303153342_1.53.47.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230303153342_1.53.47.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230303153342_2.53.48.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230303153342_2.53.48.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230303153342_3.53.50.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230303153342_3.53.50.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-03-03 10:03:42'),
(314, '2023-03-04', NULL, 'NIPUNA 23', 'The ISTE Student Chapter at SRKR is conducting National Level Student Symposium NIPUNA-23 on\r\nthis month 17 th and 18 th , Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster of the same was\r\ninaugurated by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Speaking on this occasion\r\nNipuna Faculty Coordinator Dr. Subbarao had said that 17 events are being conducted in this\r\nprogramme. The student Chapter of ISTE at SRKR had stood as No.1 in AP at all India level for 2\r\ntimes. Student representatives of ISTE took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306092003_1.52.52 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306092003_1.52.52 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306092003_2.52.52.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306092003_2.52.52.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-06 03:50:03'),
(315, '2023-03-03', NULL, 'Students Selected For South Zone Inter University Chess Competitions', 'SRKR students had been selected for south zone inter university chess competitions that re going to\r\nbe held at Chennai from 10th to 12th March, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He\r\nwished the students all the best. 6 students had been selected on behalf of JNTUK and 3 of them are\r\nfrom SRKR. PD Dr. Satyanarayana Raju had said that coaching camp was being organized at SRKR for\r\nJNTUK selected students from 4th to 8th of this month. Assistant PD G. Harimohan took part in this\r\nevent.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306092516_1.52.53.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306092516_1.52.53.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306092516_2.52.54.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306092516_2.52.54.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-03-06 03:55:16');
