(316, '2023-03-04', NULL, 'Atal Community Innovation Centre Sanctioned For SRKR', 'Atal Community Innovation Centre was sanctioned for SRKR Engg College through NITI Aayog and\r\nAtal Innovation Mission, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Through this Industries with\r\nresources can be encouraged in twin Godavari and Krishna Districts and new start-ups can be\r\nmentored. A dedicated lab is also being set up by the college management for this centre. New start-\r\nups in the fields of agriculture, aqua and other agro based areas can be explored. Prof. N. Siva Kishan\r\nwill act as the CEO for this centre. Dean R&amp;D Dr. PARK Raju, Technology Centre Head Dr.\r\nGopalakrishna Murthy, Dr. Suresh Babu took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230306095250_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230306095250_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-06 04:22:50'),
(317, '2023-03-15', NULL, 'SPURTHI-23', 'The Dept of CSE is going to conduct a National Level Symposium named as SPURTHI-23 on 25 th of\r\nMarch 2023, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was\r\ninaugurated in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. HOD of CSE Dr.\r\nChandrasekhar had said that students across the country are going to participate in this event. A\r\nworkshop on Applications Development and 24hours hackathon is also going to be part of this event.\r\nGoverning Body Member Mr. Satya Pratik Varma, Faculty Mrs. Priyadarshini, Mr. Bharat Siva Varma\r\ntook part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_1.31.50.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_1.31.50.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_2.31.51 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_2.31.51 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_3.31.51.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_3.31.51.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_4.31.52.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_4.31.52.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_5.29.57.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_5.29.57.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173205_6.59.24.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173205_6.59.24.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-03-15 12:02:05'),
(318, '2023-03-15', NULL, 'EEE Dept Faculty Recieves Ph.D', 'Assistant Professor in the Dept of EEE Mr. Mohammed Azhar Ahmed had received his doctorate\r\nfrom Anna University, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was felicitated in the campus by\r\nSecretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Mr. Mohammed had said that he had done\r\nhis research under the supervision of Dr. Kanda Swamy Raja of Anna University on the topic of\r\n√¢‚Ç¨ÀúIntelligent Controller Schemes for Power Generation√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. HOD of EEE Dr. Varma took part in this event.\r\nMr. Mohammed was congratulated by the faculty of SRKR.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173636_1.31.51 (2).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173636_1.31.51 (2).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230315173636_2.30.19.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230315173636_2.30.19.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-03-15 12:06:36'),
(319, '2023-03-17', NULL, 'TECH FLEET 2K23', 'The Dept of IT is going to conduct a National Level Symposium named as TECH FLEET 2K23 on 25 th of\r\nMarch, 2023 Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released\r\nin the campus by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Speaking on this occasion\r\nConvener of this event and HOD of IT Dr. BHVSRK Raju said that 12 different events are being\r\nplanned for the students in this mega event. Dr. Hemalatha and Dr. Kishore Raju will act as faculty\r\ncoordinators for this event. Governing Body Member Mr. Pratik Varma and Student coordinators of\r\nthis event took part in this poster release.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230317185803_1.27.49.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230317185803_1.27.49.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230317185803_2.27.51 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230317185803_2.27.51 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230317185803_3.27.51.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230317185803_3.27.51.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230317185803_4.14.58.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230317185803_4.14.58.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230317185803_5.23.10.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230317185803_5.23.10.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'IT', '2023-03-17 13:28:03'),
(320, '2023-03-18', NULL, 'Inauguration Of Nipuna-23', 'National Level Technical Symposium Nipuna-23 was inaugurated in the campus. GST Central Excise Commissioner Mrs. Grandhi Mounica and Income Tax Officer Mr. Grandhi Anjani Kumar who are the alumni of the college attended the same as the chief guests. The said that students should mould themselves at the college age only and then they can find more opportunities of growth. Being the alumni of the college and various professional bodies in the college, they had the scope to improve their communication skills, problem solving, command over the language and that√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s the reason for their success today. Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that the alumni of the college are the progress symbols of the college. It is very happy to see that the prominent alumni of the college across the country keeps on visiting the campus and illuminating the students. The chief guests were felicitated by the management. Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju, P. Subbarao, Ramgopal Reddy took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173415_1.06.29 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173415_1.06.29 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173415_2.06.29.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173415_2.06.29.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173415_3.06.30.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173415_3.06.30.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173415_4.06.31.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173415_4.06.31.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-18 12:04:15'),
(321, '2023-03-18', NULL, 'Sankalpa-2023', 'The Dept of EEE is going to conduct a National Level Workshop on Electric Vehicles SANKALPA-2K23 on 25th and 26th of March, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Governing Body Member Sri. Pratik Varma. HOD of EEE Dr. Varma had said that this workshop will enable the students to have awareness on the emerging field of electric vehicles and its spare parts. Faculty Coordinators and Student Coordinators of this programme took part in this event. \n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173619_1.08.58.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173619_1.08.58.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173619_2.09.00 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173619_2.09.00 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173619_3.09.00.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173619_3.09.00.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230318173619_4.09.01.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230318173619_4.09.01.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-03-18 12:06:19'),
(322, '2023-03-19', NULL, 'Inauguration Of \'Workshop On Software Development Applications\'', 'A workshop on √¢‚Ç¨ÀúSoftware Development Applications√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ was being inaugurated at SRKR Engg College\r\nunder the aegis of CSE Dept. Swecha Foundation AP General Secretary Mr. Sripathy Rai attended the\r\nsame as the chief guest. Speaking on this occasion he said that students should upgrade themselves\r\nas per the latest technologies and develop products that are beneficial to the society. Students\r\nshould not confine themselves to the syllabus and work on the latest technologies. Principal Dr. M.\r\nJagapathi Raju had said that it is very proud that SRKR is selected for google certificate course and\r\nstudents should make use of it and become interns at google. CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar, Associate\r\nProfessor Dr. Kameshwara Rao, P. Suryanarayana Raju took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320182439_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320182439_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-03-20 12:54:39'),
(323, '2023-03-17', NULL, 'TRANCE 2023', 'The Dept of ECE was going to conduct a National Level Symposium titled TRANCE 2023 on 25 th of\r\nMarch, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was inaugurated in\r\nthe campus by Secretary &amp; Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. Convener of this programme\r\nand HOD of ECE Dr. Uday Kumar had said that events like these will help the students to bring out\r\nthe hidden talents. Dr. Nagaraju and Dr. Mohan Reddy will act as Co-Ordinators and Ms. Prathima\r\nand Ms. Bharathi will act as co-conveners.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320192658_1.15.18.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320192658_1.15.18.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320192658_2.15.19 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320192658_2.15.19 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320192658_3.15.19.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320192658_3.15.19.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230320192658_4.15.20.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230320192658_4.15.20.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EC', '2023-03-20 13:56:58'),
(324, '2023-03-23', NULL, 'NSS Special Camp', 'The NSS wing of SRKR is conducting a special camp at Mogallu Village from 24 th to 31 st of this month, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The guest for the inauguration of this camp would be the DEO and other people representatives. Various awareness programmes would be conducted as a part of this camp. NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327173626_1.11.47.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327173626_1.11.47.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327173626_2.12.15.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327173626_2.12.15.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327173626_3.08.25.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327173626_3.08.25.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-27 12:06:26'),
(325, '2023-03-24', NULL, 'SANKETA 2023', 'The Mechanical Engg Dept was conducting National Level Technical Symposium SANKETA 2023 on 25 th and 26 th of this month, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. HOD of ME Dr. Brahma Raju had said that various events would be conducted to the students in this symposium. Dr. Bhadriraju will act as faculty coordinator.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327173845_1.12.14.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327173845_1.12.14.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'ME', '2023-03-27 12:08:45'),
(326, '2023-03-24', NULL, 'Inauguration Of NSS Camp', 'A special camp by NSS Unit of SRKR Engg College was inaugurated in Mogallu Village on Friday. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students should mingle themselves with the rural population in order to prepare various projects that can be benefitted to them. Students should take Alluri Sitarama Raju and AS Rao as their role models. Sarpanch of Mogallu Village Mrs. Krishna Kumari was being felicitated by the management. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya and other delegates took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174205_1.22.20.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174205_1.22.20.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174205_2.23.04.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174205_2.23.04.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-03-27 12:12:05'),
(327, '2023-03-24', NULL, 'Prize Distribution To HACKATHON Winners', '24 Hours Hackathon PRAJWALANA being conducted by the Dept of CSE had concluded and the winners were distributed with cash prizes. Speaking on this occasion Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that Hackathons will help to bring out the innate talent of the students. 45 teams across the state took part in this competitions. Vishnu Institute of Technology and SRKR Engg College bagged the top 3 places in this competitions. Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju, HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar, Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy, Dr. Sirisha, Mr. Mahesh took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174624_1.29.17.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174624_1.29.17.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174624_2.22.25.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174624_2.22.25.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174624_3.23.08.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174624_3.23.08.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230327174624_4.23.09.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230327174624_4.23.09.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-03-27 12:16:24'),
(328, '2023-03-29', NULL, 'Valedictory  Of SANKETA', 'The 2 Day National Symposium by Mechanical Dept Sanketa had concluded and the Principal of SRKR\r\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had graced the occasion as the chief guest. Speaking on this occasion he said\r\nthat multi-disciplinary courses play a major role in the research in science and technology. Convener\r\nof Sanketa Dr. Badri Raju had said that in future there are plans to conduct a multi-disciplinary\r\nworkshop for the students. Incharge HOD of Mechanical Dr. Suresh Babu expressed his happiness\r\nregarding students across the state participating in this event. Prizes were being distributed to the\r\nstudents who had won in various competitions.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230331182827_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230331182827_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'ME', '2023-03-31 12:58:27'),
(329, '2023-03-31', NULL, 'Closing  Ceremony Of NSS Camp', 'One Week NSS Camp at Mogallu village by NSS Unit of SRKR had ended on Friday. Speaking on this\r\noccasion, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that students who had identified various problems\r\nof the villagers in this week had to work on them and find apt solutions for the same. Sarpanch of\r\nthe village Ms. Krishna Kumari had appreciated the students for their awareness sessions on\r\nSwachbharat and various health related issues. Certificates were distributed to the students who\r\ntook part in this camp. NSS Coordinator Dr. Krishna Chaitanya, Dr. Ganesh, KNV Satyanarayana,\r\nKanakaraju took part in this event. Eye and Skin camp was organised on this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230403143634_1.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230403143634_1.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230403143634_2.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230403143634_2.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-03 09:06:34'),
(330, '2023-04-11', NULL, 'National Survey Day  Celebrations', 'The National Survey Day Celebrations were held at Civil Engg Dept, SRKR Engg College in association\r\nwith Institute of Engineers, Bhimavaram Local Centre. Speaking on this occasion Principal of SRKR Dr.\r\nM. Jagapathi Raju had said that Surveying plays a major role in the industrial development of the\r\ncountry. Surveying has been transformed from Chain Survey to Drone Survey today. The state Govt\r\nwhich has started new surveying is playing a key role now. Students should be able to learn and\r\nimplement the latest surveying techniques. HOD of Civil Dr. Prasad, HOD of ME Dr. Brahma Raju and\r\nLocal Centre Chairman Dr. Suresh Babu took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230411154338_1.16.40.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230411154338_1.16.40.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230411154338_2.16.41.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230411154338_2.16.41.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CV', '2023-04-11 10:13:38'),
(331, '2023-04-12', NULL, 'CSE Faculty Recieves Ph.D ', 'Assistant Professor of CSE Dept Mrs. DNSB Kavitha had received her Ph. D from Andhra University,\r\nPrincipal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. She was being felicitated by the management at the\r\ncollege. Speaking on this occasion Dr. Kavitha had said that she had done her research under the\r\nguidance of VC of AU Dr. Prasad Reddy and University Computer Science and Systems Engineering\r\nDept Dr. Venkata Rao. She had done her research on the topic √¢‚Ç¨ÀúPerformance Analysis of Machine\r\nLearning Class Fires for Settlement Analysis on Twitter Political Data√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. She was congratulated by CSE\r\nHOD Dr. Chandrasekhar and other faculty.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230414122021_1.03.22.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230414122021_1.03.22.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230414122021_2.05.24.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230414122021_2.05.24.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230414122021_3.33.14.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230414122021_3.33.14.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230414122021_4.33.15.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230414122021_4.33.15.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-04-14 06:50:21'),
(332, '2023-04-14', NULL, 'Students Placed With Top Packages', 'Final Year CSE Students P. Jahnavi and T. Nadiya Bhanu are placed in Morgan Stanley and Amazon with a CTC of 29.5LPA and 25.5LPA Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. They had also got internships at their respective companies for 6 months with 87K and 50K respectively. Speaking on this occasion, Principal had highlighted the placement statistics of the institution which are the best in the state as of now. The students were felicitated by the Principal, HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar and HOD of IT Dr. BHVSRK Raju and Placement Office Dr.Satyanarayana.Final Year CSE Students P. Jahnavi and T. Nadiya Bhanu are placed in Morgan Stanley and Amazon with a CTC of 29.5LPA and 25.5LPA Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. They had also got internships at their respective companies for 6 months with 87K and 50K respectively. Speaking on this occasion, Principal had highlighted the placement statistics of the institution which are the\r\nbest in the state as of now. The students were felicitated by the Principal, HOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar and HOD of IT Dr. BHVSRK Raju and Placement Office Dr. Satyanarayana.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114256_1.31.02.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114256_1.31.02.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114256_2.24.44.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114256_2.24.44.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-04-17 06:12:56'),
(333, '2023-04-15', NULL, 'FREEDOM FEST', 'The Dept of CSE and Technology Centre are conducting FREEDOM FEST under the aegis of SEWCHA FOUNDATION on 19 th and 20 th of this month, Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus. CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar and CSD HOD Dr. Suresh Babu had said that students participating in this fest will have the chance to participate in 4 workshops on emerging technologies like AI, Web Programming, Electronics etc.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_1. 15th April CSE and Tech Ph.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_1. 15th April CSE and Tech Ph.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_3.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_3.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_5.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_5.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_6.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_6.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230417114712_7.png\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230417114712_7.png\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-17 06:17:12'),
(334, '2023-04-17', NULL, 'SRKR INKS MOU With IDP Education India Pvt Ltd', 'SRKR had entered into an MOU with IDP Education India Pvt Ltd to facilitate the students research at International Level and increase the scope of employability, Inchare Principal of SRKR Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju had said. HOD of English Dr. Lakshmi had said that IDP had come forward to establish IELTS Centre at SRKR and students can get the required material and training from the institute. IDP Senior Area Manager Mr. Anil Kumar and others took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423084959_1.13.30.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423084959_1.13.30.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423084959_2.13.31.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423084959_2.13.31.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-23 03:19:59'),
(335, '2023-04-17', NULL, 'Students Get Placed In JSW', 'SRKR Students belonging to the core groups of ECE, EEE and ME were placed in JSW as Graduate Trainee Engineers with a package of 6.5LPA, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. The students were facilitated in the college by the Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju. Placements Dean Dr.Satyanarayana had said that 11 students from ECE, 4 from ME and 3 from ECE were placed in JSW.Dr. Padmarao, HOD of EEE Dr. Varma and HOD of ME Dr. Brahma Raju took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423085401_1.13.30..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423085401_1.13.30..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423085401_2.13.31..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423085401_2.13.31..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-23 03:24:01'),
(336, '2023-04-19', NULL, 'Workshop  On  \' Gender Sensitization And Emotional Health\'', 'A workshop on √¢‚Ç¨ÀúGender Sensitization and Emotional Health√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ was conducted at SRKR by the Women Empowerment Cell. Prominent Doctor and Social Activist Dr. Samaram attended the same as the\r\nchief guest. Speaking on this occasion, he said that Women Empowerment Teams should make sure that the Women are active. He said that it is very sad to see various attacks on women. Raja Ram Mohan Roy and Kandukuri Viresalingam contribution should not be forgotten. Principal of SRKR, Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that in the total placements of the institution, girls play a major role and the institute is fully giving support to women empowerment. The chief guest is being felicitated by the management. Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari, Inner Wheel Association District President Mrs. Sridevi, CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar and various faculty members\r\ntook part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423085859_1.31.25.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423085859_1.31.25.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423085859_2.31.26..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423085859_2.31.26..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423085859_3.31.26.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423085859_3.31.26.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-23 03:28:59'),
(337, '2023-04-20', NULL, 'FREEDOM FEST', 'Freedom Fest was being conducted at SRKR Engg College by Swecha Foundation for 2 days. Speaking on this occasion, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said that new technologies are emerging every day and so the students should update themselves as per the technologies. Swecha Foundation representatives had trained the students on 11 latest technologies. 450 students across Bhimavaram from various other colleges also participated in this workshop. Swecha Foundation representatives suggested the students to visit rural places and update the students there on latest technologies. CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar, CSD HOD Dr. Suresh Babu, Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy, Swecha Foundation representatives Sripathy Rai, Lakshman, Nagaraju, Rupesh took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423090743_1.10.35.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423090743_1.10.35.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423090743_2.10.36..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423090743_2.10.36..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423090743_3.10.36.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423090743_3.10.36.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CD', '2023-04-23 03:37:43'),
(338, '2023-04-20', NULL, 'SRKR  INKS MOU With Vasavi Women\'s  Club', 'SRKR had entered an MOU with Vasavi Women√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Club, Vijayawada. The documents have been exchanged between Club Secretary PD Rashmi, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and Women Empowerment Cell Coordinator Dr. Bhuvaneshwari. Speaking on this occasion the Principal had said that SRKR is committed to Women Empowerment and various activities regarding this are already being done in association with various clubs and NGOs. Dr. Bhuvaneshwari had said that as per this MOU SRKR will give assistance in bringing awareness among women and supporting them technically for a span of 5 years. Prominent Doctor Dr. Samaram, CSE Associate Professor Dr. Sirisha, Inner Wheel Secretary Mrs. Sridevi took part in this occasion.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423091324_1.01.23.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423091324_1.01.23.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-04-23 03:43:24'),
(339, '2023-03-20', NULL, 'SRKR Assistant PD Wins  Yoga  Championship', 'Mrs. G. Sarika, Asst PD of SRKR Engg College had got 1 st Place in the National Level Yoga Championship held at Narsapuram in the category of 30-35 years of age. She was being felicitated in the campus by Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju and PD Dr. Satyanarayana Raju. Principal had said that she should train the students also in yoga and make sure that they maintain their work life balance.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423093748_1.48.58 (1).jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423093748_1.48.58 (1).jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423093748_2.48.58.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423093748_2.48.58.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230423093748_3.48.59.jpeg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230423093748_3.48.59.jpeg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-04-23 04:07:48'),
(340, '2023-04-23', NULL, 'Civil Students Visit To Polavaram Project', 'SRKR Civil Students have visited Polavaram Project on Sunday under the leadership of CIVIL HOD Dr.\r\nPrasad, as per the suggestions of Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. Speaking on this occasion, the\r\nstudents have said that the Project is the pride of the country, they have observed various new\r\ntechnologies and phases that the project is undergoing and they feel that visiting such projects\r\nwould be very helpful in their academic career. Principal had said that the students of SRKR visit the\r\nproject every year so that they get to know the practical applications and insights. Faculty of Civil\r\nDept also accompanied the students in this visit.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230425233603_1.18.17.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230425233603_1.18.17.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230425233603_2.04.58.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230425233603_2.04.58.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CV', '2023-04-25 18:06:03'),
(341, '2023-04-26', NULL, 'ECE Student Wins National Level Hackathon', 'ECE final year student Ms. N. Joshitha had won National Level Hackathon and cash prize of 30K\r\nconducted by Virtusa, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. She was appreciated by the Secretary\r\nand Correspondent of SRKR Sri. Nishanth Varma. Speaking on this occasion Training and Placements\r\nDean Dr. Satyanarayana had said that prominent MNC Virtusa had conducted this hackathon at the\r\nNational Level where 68000 participated across the country. The top 100 were selected and divided\r\ninto 20 teams and conducted the final hackathon where 2 teams were selected and Joshitha is one\r\namong them. Joshitha had said that she created an app on Girl career. ECE HOD Dr. Uday Kumar and\r\nother staff members congratulated her on the achievement.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230426175145_1.25.07.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230426175145_1.25.07.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230426175145_2.25.27..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230426175145_2.25.27..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230426175145_3.25.27.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230426175145_3.25.27.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230426175145_4.46.41.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230426175145_4.46.41.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EC', '2023-04-26 12:21:45'),
(342, '2023-04-27', NULL, 'SRKR Students Selected  For JSW', 'Final Year Students of Civil Engineering Ms. Ms. K. Lakshmi Radha and Ms. T. Sri Naga Padma Bhavani\r\nManisha got selected to JSW with a package of 6.52 LPA, Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He\r\nsaid that 20 students from the core groups are already selected for JSW and this is really a great\r\nachievement from the students of core groups. The students were felicitated by Secretary and\r\nCorrespondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Training and Placements Dean Dr. Satyanarayana and\r\nHOD of Civil Dr. Prasad.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230427172935_1.39.14...jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230427172935_1.39.14...jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230427172935_2.39.14.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230427172935_2.39.14.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230427172935_3.48.23.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230427172935_3.48.23.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CV', '2023-04-27 11:59:35'),
(343, '2023-04-28', NULL, 'SRKR Students Shine  In Hackathon By Virtusa', 'Two CSE Final Year Students Mr. G. Venkatesh and Ms. R. Sravya had participated in the hackathon\r\nconducted by Virtusa √¢‚Ç¨ÀúNeural Hack Season 6√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ and got placements from Virtusa with 6.5LPA, Principal\r\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. Nearly 10,000 participants had participated in this hackathon across\r\nthe country out of which top 100 were selected and SRKR students are among the top 100. The\r\nstudents were felicitated in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth\r\nVarma. CSE HOD Dr. Chandrasekhar, Training and Placements Dean Dr. Satyanarayana and other\r\nfaculty appreciated the students.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502155653_1.24.03.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502155653_1.24.03.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502155653_2.24.04..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502155653_2.24.04..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502155653_3.24.04.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502155653_3.24.04.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502155653_4.50.24.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502155653_4.50.24.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-05-02 10:26:53'),
(344, '2023-04-29', NULL, 'Inter Bhimavaram Football League', 'Inter Bhimavaram Football League was being organised at SRKR Engg College in association with\r\nWest Godavari Football Association from May 1 st to 3 rd , Principal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju had\r\nsaid. The poster relating to the same was released in the campus by Secretary and Correspondent of\r\nSRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma. West Godavari Football Association President V. Hari Krishna and PD\r\nof SRKR Dr. Satyanarayana Raju had said that after the new district is formed this is the first time\r\nthat the tournament is being held and thanked SRKR for hosting the same. They have asked the\r\ninterested people to make use of this opportunity. Assistant PD G. Harimohan and Student\r\nCoordinators participated in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502160352_1.53.34.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502160352_1.53.34.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502160352_2.53.58..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502160352_2.53.58..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502160352_3.53.58.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502160352_3.53.58.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'PE', '2023-05-02 10:33:52'),
(345, '2023-05-01', NULL, 'SRKR INKS MOU With Carry Share Solutions', 'SRKR Engg College had entered into an MOU with the Start-up Company Carry Share Solutions Pvt\r\nLtd. The Documents relating to the same were exchanged between the Secretary and Correspondent\r\nof SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Carry Share Solutions CEO Mr. Pavan Kumar Raju. The company\r\nwill work with AICTE Idea Lab of SRKR and train the students, conduct workshops etc. This company\r\nis recognised by the Govt of India and is doing great work in the transport sector with its app.\r\nPrincipal of SRKR Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, Technology Centre Head Dr. Gopalakrishna Murthy took part\r\nin this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502161942_1.58.18.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502161942_1.58.18.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230502161942_2.11.02.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230502161942_2.11.02.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-05-02 10:49:42'),
(346, '2023-05-03', NULL, 'EEE Faculty Receives Ph.D', 'EEE Dept Assistant Professor Mr. A. Kumar Raja had received his doctorate from NIT Raipur, Principal\r\nDr. M. Jagapathi Raju had said. He was being felicitated in the college by the Principal and EEE HOD\r\nDr. Varma. Speaking on this occasion Mr. Kumar raja had said that he did his research under the\r\nguidance of Dr. M. Biswal from NIT Raipur on the topic √¢‚Ç¨ÀúSupervised First Zone Defence Protection\r\nScheme During Power Swing√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢. Mr. Raja was congratulated by the faculty on his achievement.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230503155602_1.48.52.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230503155602_1.48.52.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230503155602_2.48.53.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230503155602_2.48.53.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230503155602_3.55.36.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230503155602_3.55.36.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230503155602_4.58.03.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230503155602_4.58.03.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'EE', '2023-05-03 10:26:02'),
(347, '2023-05-04', NULL, 'Inter Bhimavaram Football League Winners \'Black Panthers\'', 'Inter Bhimavaram Football League which was being conducted from the last 3 days by District\r\nFootball Association and SRKR Engg College had concluded and √¢‚Ç¨ÀúBlack Panthers√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ are declared as the\r\nwinners. The valedictory ceremony was being attended by Vice President of SRKR Sri. SV Ranga Raju,\r\nPrincipal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju, PD Dr. Satyanarayana Raju, District Football Association President\r\nMr. V. Hari Krishna and other dignitaries.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230152_1.20.40..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230152_1.20.40..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230152_2.20.40.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230152_2.20.40.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-05-05 17:31:52'),
(348, '2023-05-04', NULL, 'SRKR Alumni Meet @ USA', 'The Alumni Meet of SRKR is going to be held at New Jersey, USA on 27 th of May 2023, said Secretary\r\nand Correspondent of SRKR Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi Raju. The\r\nstudents have formed into a group called as SAANA (SRKR Alumni Association of North America) and\r\nare planning this event in a big way. Communications regarding this were being sent to all the\r\nstudents by specially designed website and other sources. They said that it√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s a matter of great pride\r\nfor SRKR to see their students arranging this event at USA. The Management, Principal and other\r\nfaculty are going to attend this event at USA.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230501_1.23.22.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230501_1.23.22.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230501_2.23.52..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230501_2.23.52..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230501_3.23.52.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230501_3.23.52.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230501_4.24.22.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230501_4.24.22.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230505230501_5.19.51.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230505230501_5.19.51.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-05-05 17:35:01'),
(349, '2023-05-11', NULL, 'Roller Skating Coaching Camp', 'SRKR Engg College is conducting Roller Skating Coaching Camp for the children in association with\r\nLast Leo Academy of Visakhapatnam for one month. Speaking on this occasion, Principal Dr. M.\r\nJagapathi Raju had said that parents should make sure that their children are trained in various\r\nactivities during the summer vacation so that they will have a holistic growth. PD Dr. Satyanarayana\r\nRaju, Asst. PDs Dr. Hari, Ms. Sarika and Mr. Avinash took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517091746_1.57.25..jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517091746_1.57.25..jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517091746_2.57.25.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517091746_2.57.25.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-05-17 03:47:46'),
(350, '2023-05-12', NULL, 'Students Donate For The Ailing Student', 'The students of CSE Dept of SRKR formed a group among themselves named as √¢‚Ç¨ÀúHelping Hands CSE√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢\r\nand donated 14L to their friend Mr. D. Sri Ram Nayak who was suffering from cancer. The fund has\r\nbeen handed over to him by the Incharge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju and HOD of CSE Dr.\r\nChandrasekhar. Speaking on this occasion, they said that it was really a noble gesture from the\r\nstudents to donate he amt with the help of their friends and faculty and wished that the ailing\r\nstudents would be back to normalcy very soon. They applauded the efforts of the students in this\r\nnoble gesture. The students thanked the management for their support in this initiative.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_5.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_5.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517092643_6.45.55.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517092643_6.45.55.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', 'CS', '2023-05-17 03:56:43'),
(351, '2023-05-13', NULL, 'SRKR Management Thanks  Chief Minister Office', 'President of SRKR Sri. Sagi Prasad Raju, Secretary and Correspondent Sri. SRK Nishanth Varma and\r\nPrincipal of SRKR Sri. M. Jagapathi Raju had thanked CMO for responding voluntarily on the health\r\ncondition of the student. Speaking on this occasion Incharge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju and\r\nHOD of CSE Dr. Chandrasekhar had said that CMO had voluntarily responded on the health condition\r\nof Mr. Nayak by seeing in the newspapers and had come into contact with the Principals office and\r\nthe hospital in which the student is admitted. The students and staff thanked the CMO and wished\r\nthat the student would be back with good health.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517093219_1.57.47.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517093219_1.57.47.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517093219_2.57.48.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517093219_2.57.48.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230517093219_3.48.59.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230517093219_3.48.59.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-05-17 04:02:19'),
(355, '2023-05-26', NULL, 'Alumni Meet Of SRKR  On 27th May 2023', 'SRKR Alumni Meet is going to be held at New Jersey, USA on 27 th May, 2023 said Secretary and\r\nCorrespondent Sri. SRK Nishant Varma, GB Member Sri. Pratik Varma and Principal Dr. M. Jagapathi\r\nRaju from USA. It was a great moment of pride in the history of SRKR. SRKR President Sri. S. Prasad\r\nRaju and Incharge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju wished that the event would be a grand\r\nsuccess. This event is happening after 43 years of inception of SRKR Engg College.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230725203222_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230725203222_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230725203222_2.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230725203222_2.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230725203222_3.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230725203222_3.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li><li><a href=\"img/news/20230725203222_4.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230725203222_4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-07-25 15:02:22'),
(356, '2023-05-27', NULL, 'SRKR Non-Teaching Staff Union Starts Free Drinking Water Facility', 'The Non- Teaching Staff Union of SRKR had started a free drinking water facility for the common\r\npeople near the main gate. The same was inaugurated by Vice President Sri. SV Ranga Raju and\r\nIncharge Principal Dr. Muralikrishnam Raju. They said that the union takes this initiative every year\r\nand applauded them for this noble initiative. The union representative√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Sri. Ravi Kumar, Sri\r\nSuryanarayana Raju and others took part in this event.\n\n<ul class=\"gallery-list\"><li><a href=\"img/news/20230725204851_1.jpg\" class=\"image-popup\"><img src=\"img/news/20230725204851_1.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></li></ul>', '', '', '2023-07-25 15:18:51'),
